a throne is the place where a monarch sits when he or she is not on a throne . for example , a king on the other hand would sit on the right hand of the king or queen who is on the left.the word throne can also be used to refer to the monarchy or the crown itself.the throne is most commonly used in the western world . it is the place upon which a monarch sits when he or she is not on the other side of the throne .
saratov ( ) is a city located in russia on the volga river . it is the largest city in saratov oblast . it is 389 km from volgograd , 442 km from samara , and 858 km to the southeast of moscow .
 the acre is a measure of land that is used in the imperial and us customary systems . it is the area of one chain by one furlong ( 66 by 660 feet ) . it is equal to 10 square chains , of a square mile , or 43,560 square feet , and about 4,047 m , or about 40 % of a hectare . one recognized symbol for the acre is ac , but the word `` acre '' is also used as the symbol.the acre is a statute measure in the united states , in the united kingdom and in almost all countries of the former british empire : in most it is lawful to `` use for trade '' if given as supplementary information and is not used for land registration.in the united states both the international acre and the us survey acre are in use , but they differ by only two parts per million , see below . the most common use of the acre is to measure tracts of land.traditionally , in the middle ages , an acre was defined as the area of land that could be ploughed in one day by a yoke of oxen .
eutrochium maculatum , spotted joe-pyeweed , is a north american species of flowering plant in the sunflower family asteraceae . it is widespread through much of the united states and canada . it is the only species of the genus `` eutrochium '' found west of the great plains.this herbaceous perennial sometimes grows as high as . stems are sometimes completely purple , sometimes green with purple spots . one plant can produce numerous rose-purple flower heads in late summer . each head has 8-22 disc flowers but no ray flowers.it is a larval host to the clymene moth , the eupatorium borer moth , the ruby tiger moth , and the three-lined flower moth .
la punt - chamues-ch ( ; italian and official name until 1943 : `` ponte-campovasto '' ) is a municipality of the district maloja in the canton of graubünden in switzerland .
the 16th century begins with 1501 and ends with 1501 or 1600 .
silent hill : downpour is a 2012 survival horror video game . it was developed by vatra games and published by konami digital entertainment . it is the eighth video game in the `` silent hill '' series . it was released on march 6 , 2012 . the game is set in the fictional american town `` silent hill '' . `` silent hill : downpour '' got mixed reviews from gaming critics . they liked its atmosphere , story and returned to the series ' survival horror and exploration roots after the action-heavy linearity of `` '' . they did not like its monster design , combat and technical performance .
the 2020 presidential campaign of jay inslee began when inslee , the governor of washington , announced on march 1 , 2019 that he would be running for the democratic nomination . he was chair of the democratic governors association for the 2018 election cycle and was a co-chair of the united states climate alliance.on march 1 , 2019 , inslee announced his candidacy for president of the united states . he ended his presidential campaign on august 21 , 2019 .
mooresville is a large town located in south western section of iredell county , north carolina , united states and is a part of the fast-growing charlotte metro area . the population was 32,711 at the 2010 united states census .
joan antoni solans i huguet ( 15 october 1941 – 2 september 2019 ) was a spanish catalan architect . he was born in barcelona . he focused his career on urban planning . he was the architect of the new territorial planning of catalonia and some cities.huget died on 2 september 2019 at age 77 after being hit by a car in barcelona .
beggars banquet is a 1968 album by the rolling stones . it was their seventh british and american studio album , and was released in 1968 . `` beggars banquet '' was the group 's first studio album of new material in 5 years . songs like `` sympathy for the devil '' , `` street fighting man '' , `` sympathy for the devil '' , and `` beggars banquet '' became rock radio hits for decades.the album is one of the best-selling albums of all time , and ranks # 1 on rolling stone magazine 's 500 greatest albums of all time . `` rolling stone '' magazine ranked the album # 27 on their list of the `` 500 greatest albums of all time '' .the album was produced by jimmy miller , the band 's producer , and the primary songwriting partner of the band 's lead singer mick jagger ; together the two wrote all but one of the songs on the album .
norfolk is a city in the u.s. state of virginia . it is in the hampton roads metro area and along the chesapeake bay . it is part of the hampton roads metro area .
toypurina ( 1760–1799 ) was a medicine woman of the tongva nation . she is famous for her opposition of the colonial rule by spanish missionaries in california . she also opposed the planned 1785 rebellion against mission san gabriel .
robert gregory `` greg '' evers ( june 16 , 1955 – august 21 , 2017 ) was an american republican politician . he was a member of the florida senate from 2010 to 2016 , representing parts of northwest florida . before to his election to the senate , he served as a member of the florida house of representatives , representing the 1st district from 2001 to 2010.evers died on august 21 , 2017 in tallahassee , florida of a heart attack at the age of 62 .

kim chung-yum ( ; 3 january 1924 – 25 april 2020 ) was a south korean politician . under president park chung-hee , he was the longest serving chief presidential secretary in south korean history . he also was minister of finance and minister of commerce and industry , playing a leading role in the country 's miraculous economic development.kim died on 25 april 2020 , aged 96 .
mamenchisaurus is a sauropod dinosaur genus with several species , known for their remarkably long necks which made up half the total body length . it is known from numerous species which ranged in time from 160 to 145 million years ago , from the oxfordian age of late jurassic in china . the largest species , `` m. sinocanadorum '' , may have reached in length and possibly weighed 60-80 tonnes ( 66-88 short tons ) .
polygamy ( from greek , `` polygamía '' , `` state of marriage to many spouses '' ) is the practice of marrying multiple spouses . when a man is married to more than one wife at a same time , sociologists call this polygyny . when a woman is married to more than one husband at a time , it is called polyandry . if a marriage includes multiple husbands and wives , it is called group marriage.in contrast , monogamy is marriage consisting of only two parties . like `` monogamy '' , the term `` polygamy '' is often used in a `` de facto '' sense , applied regardless of whether the state recognizes the relationship . in sociobiology and zoology , researchers use `` polygamy '' in a broad sense to mean any form of multiple mating.worldwide , different societies variously encourage or outlawed polygamy . of societies which accept or accept polygamy , in most of cases the form accepted is polygyny . according to the ethnographic atlas , 1,231 societies noted , 588 had frequent polygyny , 453 had occasional polygyny , 186 were monogamous and 4 had polyandry ; although more recent research suggests polyandry may be more common than previously thought.the simplest form of polygamy is known as polyandry , and in most cases it has been accepted . although marriage is legally monogamous ( a person can only have one spouse , and bigamy is illegal ) , adultery is not illegal , leading to a situation of `` de facto '' polygamy being allowed , although without legal recognition for non-official `` spouses '' .in many places , polygamy is illegal in the united states , but it is allowed in a small number of countries , such as the united kingdom , australia , new zealand , and south africa , where it is recognized as a normal form of marriage .
 christopher jarvis haley hogwood ( 10 september 1941 – 24 september 2014 ) was an english conductor , harpsichordist , writer , and musicologist . he was the founder of the early music ensemble the academy of ancient music . he was an authority on historically informed performance and a leading figure in the early music revival of the late 20th century.haley hogwood died on 24 september 2014 , aged 74 .
killing me softly is a 2013 romantic comedy-drama movie . this movie is about female trafficking . this movie is set in 1964 in los angeles , california . this movie was released in the united states in september 2013 . it received mixed reviews from critics . roger ebert gave the movie three out of four stars . ``killing me softly '' was released in february 2013 .
wii music is a music video game for the wii game console . it was released in japan and north america in october 2008 , and in europe and australia in the following month . it was one of the first music games for the wii , and is one of the least commercially successful .
jasper county is a county found in the u.s. state of mississippi . as of the 2010 census , 17,062 people lived there .
sir william mcmahon ( 23 february 1908 – 31 march 1988 ) was the 20th prime minister of australia . he became prime minister at the age of 63 , making him the oldest non-interim prime minister to take office . his government stopped inflation and unemployment and was succeeded by john gorton as leader of the liberal party.mcmahon was born in sydney and raised in gorton , new south wales . he was the oldest non-interim prime minister ever in australian history.mcmahon was a member of the australian house of representatives from 1949 to 1950 , again from 1951 to 1956 and again from 1958 to 1966 . he was also minister for labour and national service from 1958 to 1966 , again from 1964 to 1966 and again from 1967 to 1969 . he was also australia 's treasurer ( 1969–1969 ) and minister for external affairs ( 1969–1969 ) . in 1971 gorton forced gorton to resign and mcmahon became prime minister.mcmahon became prime minister at the age of 63 , and is the oldest non-interim prime minister to take office . his government continued many of the policies of its last years , such as the phased withdrawal of australian troops from vietnam and unemployment . gough whitlam 's labor party defeated mcmahon in the 1972 federal election , ending 23 years of coalition rule . mcmahon resigned the liberal leadership and remained in parliament until 1982 .
dracophyllum is a genus of plants belonging to the family ericaceae , formerly epacridaceae . there are some one hundred or so species in the genus , mostly shrubs , but also cushion plants and trees , found in new zealand , australia and new caledonia .
machias is a town in and the county seat of washington county in downeast maine . as of the 2010 census , the town population was 2,221 .
barnum 's american museum was at the corner of broadway and ann street in new york city , united states , from 1841 to 1865 . the museum was owned by famous showman p. t. barnum , who purchased scudder 's american museum in 1841 . the museum offered both strange and educational attractions and performances .
drinker is a fictional character in the `` pink panther '' television series of the same name . she is ainker who enjoys drinking . she is seen as a smart woman in the pink panther movies . she is also in the pink panther movies .
kauai is the second oldest of the hawaiian islands , after niʻihau . it is in kauai county , hawaii . it is the fourth-largest of these islands . it is the 21st largest island in the united states . kauai is 105 miles ( 169 km ) across the kauai channel , northwest of oahu . the 2010 united states census population of the island was 67,091 . the most populous town was kapaa .
jim boyd ( 1956 – june 22 , 2016 ) was a native american singer-songwriter and actor . he was a member of the jim boyd band on the colville indian reservation in washington . boyd has performed in several groups , including xit , greywolf , and winterhawk . boyd sang four songs with lyrics by sherman alexie on the soundtrack for the 1998 movie `` smoke signals '' , and also appeared in alexie 's `` the business of fancydancing '' .
uses and gratifications theory ( ugt ) is an approach to understanding why and how people actively seek out specific media to satisfy specific needs . ugt is an audience-centered approach to understanding mass communication . it is different from other media effect theories that question `` what does media do to people ? ''
the saint petersburg philharmonic orchestra is the oldest symphony orchestra in russia . it was started in 1882 . the orchestra was first called the imperial music choir . it was performed for the court of alexander iii of russia . by the 1900s , the orchestra started to give public performances at the philharmonia and other places in russia . after the russian revolution , the orchestra was renamed to the state philharmonic orchestra of petrograd . in the 1920s , the orchestra began getting support from the state , and began to be known internationally . guest conductor appearances were made by bruno walter , ernest ansermet , and hans knappertsbusch during this time . the city of petrograd was renamed leningrad three days after vladimir lenin died . around this time , the orchestra was renamed the leningrad philharmonic orchestra . around this time , the orchestra was renamed the saint petersburg philharmonic orchestra . it became famous under the long time director of the orchestra , yevgeny mravinsky .
air jordan is a brand of basketball shoes . it was made by nike . it was created for former nba player and six-time nba finals mvp michael jordan .
the campeonato brasileiro série a is a football league which is top division in brazil .
the ordovician was the second of six periods of the palaeozoic era . it began 41.6 million years ago , and ended 41.6 million years ago.the ordovician is named after the welsh tribe of the ordovices . it was defined in 1879 to resolve a dispute between adam sedgwick and roderick murchison . they placed the same rock beds in northern wales into the cambrian and silurian systems . the ordovician received international approval in 1960 . it was adopted as an official period of the paleozoic era by the international geological congress.life continued to flourish during the ordovician as it did in the earlier cambrian period . the end of the period was marked by the ordovician–silurian extinction events . fish , the world 's first true vertebrates , continued to evolve , and those with jaws may first appeared late in the period . life had yet to diversify on land .
lee county is a county in the u.s. state of florida . as of 2000 , 613,924 people lived there . lee county was created in 1887 . its county seat is fort myers .
liberty x ( originally called liberty ) were a british-irish group . it had five members in it . they were formed by five finalists of `` popstars '' . they failed to make it into the group hear'say . liberty x went on to achieve ten consecutive uk top 20 singles . they were able to do greater commercial success than hear'say . following the release of two singles the group were forced to change their name due to another act already using the name liberty . however , they lost and therefore changed their name . the group released their first album thinking it over on may 27 , 2002 . it had their biggest single `` just a little '' . it was number one on the uk singles chart for two weeks . they released their second studio album `` being somebody '' on 3 november 2003 . it was not as successful as their debut . following disappointing sales the group were dropped and later signed with virgin . they released a final studio album `` x '' on 10 october 2005 . they disbanded in early 2007 . however , they re-formed a year later in 2008 , for a one-off appearance in belfast performing their biggest hits . this would be their final appearance as a band before reforming in 2012.on 18 october 2012 , it was announced that the group would be reforming for the itv2 documentary series `` the big reunion '' . the show , which aired from 31 january to 28 march 2013 , followed the groups rehearsing for two weeks ahead of one major comeback performance at the london hammersmith apollo on 26 february . lundon confirmed that liberty x would not continue following the series and that this would be their chance to `` say a proper goodbye to fans '' . however , on 2 february 2014 , the group announced via their facebook page that they had signed to 365 artists management `` for our future creative and business affairs . ''
'splosion man is a video game made by twisted pixel games for the xbox live arcade service . it was released on july 22 , 2009 . it was part of the 2009 xbox live summer of arcade . `` splosion man '' received positive reviews , and was voted by xbox live players as the best original xbla game of 2009 .
mardi gras , also known as shrove tuesday , is a tuesday in many countries . it is a holiday for people to celebrate the christian holiday of epiphany . it is usually celebrated before ash wednesday ( the day before the three kings day ) .
russell is the biggest city in russell county , kansas , united states . it is also the county seat of russell county . in 2010 , 4,506 people lived there .
cama is a municipality of the district of moesa in the canton of graubünden in switzerland .
hanau is a town of the main-kinzig-kreis in the state of hesse in germany . it is 25 km east of frankfurt am main . about 41,000 people lived there in 2015 .
roger david casement ( 1 september 1864 – 3 august 1916 ) , known as sir roger casement , cmg , between 1911 and 1916 , was a diplomat and irish nationalist . he worked for the british foreign office as a diplomat and later a humanitarian activist , poet and easter rising leader.as a young man , casement first worked for commercial interests before joining the british colonial service . in 1891 he was appointed as a british consul , a profession he followed for more than 20 years . influenced by the boer war and his investigation into colonial atrocities against indigenous peoples , casement grew to mistrust imperialism . after retiring from consular service in 1913 , he became more involved with irish republicanism and other separatist movements . during world war i he made efforts to gain german military aid for the 1916 easter rising that sought to gain irish independence.he was arrested , convicted and executed for high treason . he was stripped of his knighthood and other honours . before the trial , the british government circulated excerpts said to be from his private journals , known as the `` black diaries '' , which detailed homosexual activities . given prevailing views and existing laws on homosexuality , this material undermined support for clemency for casement . debates have continued about these diaries .
amsterdam airport schiphol ( dutch : `` fliegerhorst schiphol '' ) , also known simply as schiphol airport ( dutch : `` zaandamsterdam airport '' ) , is an airport in the province of north holland , the netherlands . it is about southwest of amsterdam . it was opened in 1916 as an airbase for the dutch army . after world war i , it was used as a military airbase . after world war ii it was used as a major civilian airbase . in 1940 it was captured by the german military and renamed after `` fliegerhorst schiphol '' . after the war it was rebuilt and is now the main airport of the netherlands . in 1949 it was decided that schiphol was to become the main airport of the netherlands . in 2011 it was voted the best airport in western europe .

tacoma is a city in the u.s. state of washington . it is the second largest city in the puget sound area . it is also the third largest city in the state . it is the county seat of pierce county.the city is on washington 's puget sound , southwest of seattle and northeast of the state capital , olympia . it is northwest of mount rainier national park . the population was 191,704 , according to the 2010 census.tacoma is the center of business activity for the south sound region , which has a population of around 1 million.tacoma is locally known as the `` city of destiny '' because the area was chosen to be the western terminus of the northern pacific railroad in the late 19th century . the decision of the railroad was influenced by tacoma 's neighboring deep-water harbor , commencement bay . by connecting the bay with the railroad , tacoma 's motto became `` when rails meet sails '' . commencement bay serves the port of tacoma , a center of international trade on the pacific coast and washington 's largest port . the city gained notoriety in 1940 for the collapse of the tacoma narrows bridge , which earned the nickname `` galloping gertie '' .tacoma is the county seat of pierce county . since the 1990s , downtown tacoma has undergone revitalization effort . developments in the downtown include the university of washington tacoma ; line t ( formerly tacoma link ) , the first modern electric light rail service in the state ; the state 's highest density of art and history museums ; and a restored urban waterfront , thea foss waterway.tacoma has been named one of the most livable areas in the united states . in 2006 , tacoma was listed as one of the `` most walkable '' cities in the country .
gérard paul alain feldzer ( born 10 february 1944 ) is a french consultant and aeronautical popularizer . he is a former french airline pilot , president of `` comité régional de tourisme d'île-de-france '' ( regional committee of île-de-france tourism ) since may 2010 , and vice-président of `` ports de paris '' ( ports of paris ) .he has also been regional advisor of île-de-france for `` europe écologie '' since march 2010 and a close friend of nicolas hulot .
joseph rené marcel pronovost ( june 15 , 1930 – april 26 , 2015 ) was a canadian professional ice hockey defenceman and coach . he played in 1,206 games over 20 national hockey league ( nhl ) seasons for the detroit red wings and toronto maple leafs between 1950 and 1970.pronovost was named to four post-season nhl all-star teams and played in 11 all-star games . he was a member of four stanley cup championship teams with the red wings , the first in 1950 , and won a fifth title with the maple leafs in 1967 . pronovost was inducted into the hockey hall of fame as a player in 1978 .

a geographical pole is the name for one of the two places on a rotating body ( planet , dwarf planet , natural satellite , sphere ... etc . ) where its axis of rotation intersects its surface . as with earth 's north and south poles , they are usually called that body 's `` north pole '' and `` south pole '' , one lying 90 degrees in one direction from the body 's equator and the other lying 90 degrees in the opposite direction from the equator.every planet has geographical poles . if the earth generates a magnetic field , it will also possess magnetic poles.perturbations in a body 's rotation mean that geographical poles wander slightly on its surface . the earth 's north and south poles , for example , move by a few metres over periods of a few years . as cartography requires exact and unchanging coordinates , the averaged locations of geographical poles are taken as fixed `` cartographic poles '' and become the points where the body 's great circles of longitude intersect .
barsha lekhi ( ) ( born may 5 , 1993 in saptari , nepal ) is a nepali model , beauty queen and an environmental activist . she was crowned as miss nepal 2016 . she won missosology people 's choice award 2016 . she represented nepal at miss international 2016 contest which was held in japan on october 27 , 2016.barsha finished her environmental science education from patan multiple campus and she has worked at nefin-redd/cc partnership program . currently she is pursuing her masters in environmental science from jawaharlal nehru university .
hervé forneri ( 24 april 1945 – 24 april 2019 ) , known professionally as dick rivers , was a french singer and actor . he began performing in the early 1960s . he was an important figure in introducing rock and roll music in france . he was a admirer of elvis presley.his stage name came from the character , deke rivers , that presley played in his second movie , `` loving you '' ( 1957 ) .

gelderland ( dutch : `` gelderland '' ) is a province of the netherlands . it is in the central eastern part of the country . it is the largest province in the netherlands by land area.gelderland is divided into six provinces : flevoland , limburg , north brabant , overijssel , south holland and utrecht . the german state of north rhine-westphalia is also part of gelderland . the capital is arnhem .
2019 was a common year starting on saturday of the gregorian calendar .
thursday is the day of the week between wednesday and friday . in the iso 8601 international standard , it is the fourth day of the week . in countries that adopt the sunday-first convention , it is the fifth day of the week .
the pim fortuyn list ( dutch : `` partij pim fortuyn '' ) , shortened to lpf , was a dutch political party.the lpf was founded in 2002 and dissolved in 2008 . the party leader was pim fortuyn . fortuyn was a former university professor.the party was eurosceptic , meaning they were against the european union.pim fortuyn had planned to contest the 2002 general election as leader of the livable netherlands ( ln ) party . he was dismissed as ln leader in february 2002 . the lpf gained support from many people.the lpf formed a coalition government with the christian democratic appeal ( cda ) and the people 's party for freedom and democracy ( vvd ) , but internal conflicts in the coalition led to a break-up and fresh elections after a few months.the lpf was right-wing populist and nationalist , and adhering to its own ideology of `` fortuynism '' according to some commentators .
ibuprofen is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug ( nsaid ) that is used for treating pain , fever and inflammation . this includes painful menstrual periods , migraines , and rheumatoid arthritis . it may also be used to close a patent ductus arteriosus in a premature baby . it can be used by mouth or intravenously.common side effects include heartburn and a rash . it is easier to take than other nsaids because it has fewer side effects such as gastrointestinal bleeding . it increases the risk of heart failure , kidney failure , and liver failure . at low doses , it does not appear to increase the risk of heart attack ; however , at higher doses it may cause asthma.ibuprofen can be given as nurofen or advil . it was first marketed in 1969 in the united kingdom and in the united states in 1974 . it is on the world health organization 's list of essential medicines .
coevorden is a city in the province of drenthe , the netherlands . in 2016 about 30,000 people were living in coevorden .
a tailor is a person who makes , repairs , or changes clothing in order to make them more attractive to men . famous examples are the tailor of gloucester , `` the emperor 's new clothes '' and `` the valiant little tailor '' .

fundamental forces . these are the electromagnetic force , the weak force , and the strong force . the model does not include the gravitational force , which is thought to be the force that holds the universe together . it also does not include the electromagnetic force , which is thought to be responsible for the strong force , and the weak force , which is thought to be the force that holds the universe together . the model says that the four forces are not strong enough to hold against gravity , and that the weak force is the force that holds the universe together . other forces are not the executive yuan is the executive branch of the government of the republic of china ( taiwan ) . its leader is the premier , who is appointed by the president of the republic of china.the premier may be removed by a vote of no-confidence by a majority of the legislative yuan , after which the president may either remove the premier or dissolve the legislative yuan and start a new election for legislators.unlike most presidential systems , the head of the executive branch is not the president . the premier is the head of government while the president is the head of state . the president may remove the premier .
marian lupu ( ; born 20 june 1966 ) is a moldovan politician . he was the president of the parliament of moldova between 2010 and 2013 . from this position he was acting president of the republic from 2010 until 2012 .
a monarchy is a form of government , in which a person , usually called a monarch , is the head of state for life , or until abdication.the political power and authority of the monarch may vary from purely symbolic ( crowned republic ) , to absolute monarchy , and can expand across the domains of the executive , legislative and judicial.a monarchy can be a polity through unity , personal union , vassalage or federation , and can carry various titles such as king , queen , emperor , raja , khan , caliph , tsar , sultan , or shah.in most cases the succession of monarchies is hereditary , often building dynastic periods , however elective and self-proclaimed monarchies are possible.archies were the most common form of government until the 20th century . today forty-five sovereign nations in the world have a monarch , including sixteen commonwealth realms that have elizabeth ii as the head of state .
the code of hammurabi is a well-preserved babylonian code of law of ancient mesopotamia , dated to about 1754 bc . it is one of the oldest deciphered writings of significant length in the world . the sixth babylonian king , hammurabi , enacted the code . a partial copy exists on a 2.25 meter-tall ( 7.5 ft ) stone stele . it consists of 282 laws , with scaled punishments , adjusting `` an eye for an eye , a tooth for a tooth '' .the code deals with matters of contract , establishing the wages to be paid to an ox driver or a surgeon for example . other provisions set the terms of a transaction , the liability of a builder for a house that collapses , or property that is damaged while left in the care of another . a third of the code addresses issues concerning household and family relationships such as inheritance , divorce , paternity , and reproductive behavior . a few provisions address issues related to military service.the code was discovered by modern archaeologists in 1901 , and its translation published in 1902 by jean-vincent scheil . this nearly complete example of the code is carved into a diorite stele in the shape of a huge index finger , tall . the code is inscribed in the akkadian language , using cuneiform script carved into the stele .
saludos amigos ( english for `` greetings , friends '' ) is a 1942 american animated movie produced by walt disney productions and distributed by rko radio pictures . it is the sixth disney animated movie and the first of the six movies produced by walt disney productions in the 1940s . it was first shown on february 6 , 1943 . `` saludos amigos '' was so popular that walt disney decided to make another movie about latin america , `` the three caballeros '' , to be produced two years later . at 42 minutes , it is disney 's shortest animated movie .
nicolas sébastien anelka ( born 14 march 1979 ) is a french football player . he plays for juventus and france national team .
glenn ljungström ( born 7 september 1974 ) is a swedish co-guitarist from nödinge-nol , for a swedish band called the resistance , since 2011 . he was also an ex-guitarist and composer in a few other swedish bands . he was most notably in melodic death metal band in flames from 1993 to 1997 , for which he was also an original member . he quit in flames to support his family with a more stable job . the other two bands that he took part in 1995 were in hammerfall until 1997 and lastly a side project he co-founded with jesper strömblad called dimension zero , which he remained in until 2003 , after which he quit that band as well .
bulk cargo is commodity cargo that is transported unpackaged in large quantities .
sarajevo is the capital city of bosnia and herzegovina . it is also the largest city in bosnia and herzegovina . the city has a population of 275,524 people . in 2011 , it was nominated to be the 2014 european capital of culture . it is on the miljacka river in the heart of the balkans .
wind gap is a borough in northampton county , pennsylvania , united states . wind gap is located in the lehigh valley region of the state . it is part of pennsylvania 's slate belt.the population of wind gap was 2,720 at the 2010 census .
perry is a city in the u.s. state of georgia . it is the county seat of houston county . the population was 13,839 at the 2010 census .
petrus plancius ( c. 1552 – may 15 , 1622 ) was a dutch astronomer , cartographer and clergyman . he was born as pieter platevoet in dranouter , now in heuvelland , west flanders . he studied theology in germany and england . at the age of 24 he became a minister in the dutch reformed church.plancius fled from brussels to amsterdam to avoid religious prosecution by the spanish inquisition after the city fell into spanish hands in 1585 . in amsterdam he became interested in navigation and cartography . because he had access to nautical charts recently brought from portugal , he was soon recognized as an expert on safe maritime routes to india and the nearby spice islands . this enabled colonies and port trade in both , including what would become the dutch east indies .
anita is a city in iowa in the united states .
warren is a city in ohio in the united states . it is the county seat of trumbull county . 41,558 people lived there in the 2010 census .
needamangalam taluk ( nidamangalam taluk ) is a taluk in thiruvarur district of the indian state of tamil nadu . the headquarters of the taluk is the town of needamangalam .

vincenzo bettiza ( 7 june 1927 – 28 july 2017 ) was a yugoslavian-born italian novelist , journalist and politician . he was born in sarajevo , kingdom of yugoslavia . he was a member of the communist party of yugoslavia . bettiza was a member of the european parliament for the party of deputies from 1993 to 1994.bettsiza died on 28 july 2017 in milan of respiratory failure at the age of 90 .
louis-claude daquin ( born paris , 4 july 1694 ; died paris , 15 june 1772 ) was a french composer . he was famous for his organ music , especially for harpsichord music . he was also organist and harpsichordist .

mecklenburg county is a county located in the southwestern region of the state of north carolina , in the united states . as of the 2010 census , the population was 919,618 . it increased to 1,110,356 as of the 2019 estimate , making it the second-most populous county in north carolina ( after wake county ) and the first county in the carolinas to surpass one million in population . its county seat and largest city is charlotte .
the united states naval criminal investigative service ( ncis ) is the main law enforcement agency of the united states department of the navy . it is responsible to investigate criminal activities involving the u.s. navy and u.s. marine corps . this includes national security , counterintelligence , counter-terrorism , cyber warfare , and the protection of u.s. naval assets worldwide.the vast majority of ncis personnel are civilian , with half being special agents . ncis agents are armed federal law enforcement investigators . they coordinate with other u.s. government agencies and have a presence in more than 41 countries and on u.s. navy vessels.ncis special agents are supported by analysts and other experts skilled in disciplines such as forensics , surveillance , surveillance countermeasures , computer investigations , physical security , and polygraph examinations .
lanas is a town and commune of the ardèche `` département '' , in the southern part of france .

rosalind elsie franklin ( 25 july 192016 april 1958 ) was an english chemist and x-ray crystallographer . her work was important in understanding of the molecular structures of dna ( deoxyribonucleic acid ) , rna ( ribonucleic acid ) , viruses , coal , and graphite . although her works on coal and viruses were appreciated in her lifetime , her contributions to the discovery of the structure of dna were largely recognised posthumously.franklin was educated at a private day school at norland place in west london , lindores school for young ladies in sussex , and st paul 's girls ' school , london . then she studied the natural sciences tripos at newnham college , cambridge , from which she graduated in 1941 . earning a research fellowship , she joined the university of cambridge physical chemistry laboratory under ronald george wreyford norrish , who disappointed her for his lack of enthusiasm . the british coal utilisation research association ( bcura ) offered her a research position in 1942 and started her work on coals . this helped her earn a ph.d. in 1945 . she went to paris in 1947 as a `` chercheur '' ( postdoctoral researcher ) under jacques mering at the laboratoire central des services chimiques de l'etat , where she became an accomplished x-ray crystallographer . she became a research associate at king 's college london in 1951 and worked on x-ray diffraction studies , which would eventually facilitate the discovery of the double helix structure of dna . in 1953 , after two years , owing to disagreement with her director john randall and more so with her colleague maurice wilkins , she was compelled to move to birkbeck college . at birkbeck , john desmond bernal , chair of the physics department , offered her a separate research team . she died in 1958 at age 37 of ovarian cancer.franklin is best known for her work on the x-ray diffraction images of dna , particularly photo 51 , while at king 's college london , which led to the discovery of the dna double helix for which james watson , francis crick and maurice wilkins shared the nobel prize in physiology or medicine in 1962 . watson suggested that franklin would have ideally been awarded a nobel prize in chemistry , along with wilkins , but because there was not yet a rule against posthumous awards , the nobel committee generally did not make posthumous nominations.after finishing her work on dna , franklin led pioneering work at birkbeck on the molecular structures of viruses . her team member aaron klug continued her research , winning the nobel prize in chemistry , winning the nobel prize in chemistry in 1982 .
robie creek is a census-designated place ( cdp ) of idaho in the united states .

in statistics , an estimator is a rule for calculating an estimate of a given quantity based on observed data . this includes the rule ( the estimator ) , the quantity of interest ( the estimand ) and its result ( the estimate ) .
john monckton ( born january 1 , 1980 ) is an american politician . he is a member of the republican party . he was born in los angeles , california . monckton was a member of the united states house of representatives for california 's 2nd congressional district from 1981 to 1997 . he was also a member of the house of representatives for california 's 4th congressional district from 1997 to 2001.he was a member of the united states house of representatives from california 's 13th congressional district from 1997 to 2001 . he was also a member of the house of representatives for california 's 13th congressional district from 2003 to 2010.he ran for the republican party nomination for president of the united states in 2012 and in 2014 . he was defeated in the general election by jimmy carter.monckton was a member of the united states house of representatives for california 's 13th congressional district from 2003 to 2010 . he was also a member of the house of representatives for california 's 14th congressional district from 2011 to 2014 .

the sino-soviet split was the breaking of political relations between the people 's republic of china ( prc ) and the union of soviet socialist republics ( ussr ) . it was caused by their different interpretations of marxism-leninism . their influence during the cold war ( 1945–1991 ) was very large . in the late 1950s and early 1960s , sino-soviet debates about the interpretation of orthodox marxism became specific disputes about the ussr 's policies of national de-stalinization and international peaceful coexistence with the western world . against that ideological background , china opposed the ussr 's policy of peaceful coexistence between the eastern bloc and the western bloc . in 1961 , nikita khrushchev denounced stalinism in the speech `` on the cult of personality and its consequences '' ( 25 february 1956 ) . sino-soviet split was a question of who would lead the revolution for world communism , and to whom the vanguard parties of the world would turn for political advice , financial aid , and military assistance : to china or to the soviet union ? in that vein , the prc and the prc competed for the leadership of world communism through the vanguard parties native to the countries in their spheres of influence.in the western world , the sino-soviet split made the bi-polar cold war into a tri-polar cold war , a geopolitical event as important as the erection of the berlin wall ( 1961 ) , the defusing of the cuban missile crisis ( 1962 ) , and the end of the vietnam war ( 1955–1975 ) , because the rivalry facilitated mao 's realisation of sino-american rapprochement with the 1972 nixon visit to china . moreover , the occurrence of the sino-soviet split voided the concept of monolithic communism , the western perception that the communist nations were collectively a unitary actor in post-second world war geopolitics , especially during the 1947–1950 period in the vietnam war , when the us intervened to the first indochina war ( 1946–1954 ) . historically , the sino-soviet split facilitated the marxist-leninist `` realpolitik '' of the late-period cold war ( 1956–1991 ) as well as the quad-polar geopolitics ( prc-uk-usa-ussr ) until the suez crisis of 1956 .
cotopaxi ( ) is one of the provinces of ecuador . the capital is latacunga . the province has the cotopaxi volcano .

bhimber ( ) is a town in azad kashmir , pakistan . it is the capital of bhimber district .
diatoms are a major group of algae , specifically microalgae , found in the oceans , waterways and soils of the world . living diatoms are a type of plankton called phytoplankton , the most common of the plankton types . diatoms also grow attached to benthic substrates , floating debris , and on macrophytes . they make up nearly half of the organic material found in the oceans.the shells of dead diatoms can reach as much as a half-mile ( 800 m ) deep on the ocean floor , and the entire amazon basin is fertilized every year by 27 million tons of diatom shell dust transported by transatlantic winds from the african sahara . much of it is from the bodélé depression , which was once made up of a system of fresh-water lakes.diatoms have two distinct shapes : a few ( `` centric diatoms '' ) are `` radially '' symmetric , while most ( `` pennate diatoms '' ) are broadly `` bilaterally '' symmetric . an individual cells range in size from 2 to 200 micrometers .
edward richard sprigg canby ( november 9 , 1817 – april 11 , 1873 ) was a career united states army officer and a union general in the american civil war.in 1861–1862 , canby commanded the department of new mexico , defeating the confederate general henry hopkins sibley at the battle of glorieta pass , forcing him to retreat to texas . at the war 's end , he took the surrender of generals richard taylor and edmund kirby smith.as commander of the pacific northwest in 1873 , he was assassinated during peace talks with the modoc , who were refusing to move from their california homelands . he was the only united states general to be killed during the indian wars.canby was regarded as an administrator , more than a leader . general ulysses s. grant believed that he lacked aggression , but declared him irreplaceable for his knowledge of army regulations and constitutional law .
it is the main character in stephen king 's 1986 horror novel `` it '' . the character is an ancient cosmic evil which preys upon the children of derry , maine , roughly every 27 years , using a variety of powers that include the ability to shapeshift , manipulate reality , and go unnoticed by adults . during the course of the story it primarily appears in the form of pennywise the dancing clown .
james mitchell ( born july 4 , 1980 ) is an american politician . he is a member of the republican party . mitchell was born in new york city . mitchell served as a member of the united states house of representatives for new york 's 1st congressional district from 2003 to 2010 . he was also a member of the house of representatives for new york 's 2nd congressional district from 2003 to 2010.mitchell was elected to the house of representatives in 2010 and 2011 . he was the republican nominee for the house of representatives in 2012 , but lost to bob jindal . mitchell was the republican nominee for governor of new york in the 2018 election .
barilium is a genus of iguanodontian dinosaur which was first described as a species of `` iguanodon '' by richard lydekker in 1888 , the specific epithet honouring the discoverer charles dawson.in 2010 it was reclassified as a separate genus by david norman . the generic name `` barilium '' is derived from greek `` barys '' , `` heavy '' , and latin `` ilium '' .

in quantum field theory , the casimir effect and casimir–polder force are physical forces arising from a quantized field . they are named after the dutch physicist hendrik casimir , who predicted them in 1948 . the casimir effect can be understood by the idea that the presence of conducting metals and dielectrics alters the vacuum value of the second-quantized electromagnetic field . since the value of this energy depends on the shapes and positions of the conductors and dielectrics , the casimir effect manifests itself as a force between such objects.any medium supporting oscillations has an analogue of the casimir effect . for example , beads on a string as well as plates submerged in turbulent water or gas illustrate the casimir force.in modern theoretical physics , the casimir effect plays an important role in the chiral bag model of the nucleon ; in applied physics it is important in some aspects of emerging microtechnologies and nanotechnologies .

galegeae is a tribe of the subfamily faboideae . the tribe is found mostly in the northern hemisphere , but can also be found in australia , africa , and south america . recent molecular phylogenetic work has determined that tribe galegeae is paraphyletic , and its members are scattered throughout the ir-lacking clade .

 galenus or claudius galenus ( ) ( c. 129 – c. 1222 ) , was a greek physician , surgeon , and philosopher in the roman empire . he is considered one of the greatest medical researchers of all time . galen influenced the development of various scientific disciplines , including anatomy , physiology , pathology , pharmacology , neurology , and philosophy.galen 's anatomical reports were based mainly on the dissection of monkeys . while dissecting them he discovered that their facial expressions were too much like those of humans . his anatomical reports were uncontested until 1543 , when printed descriptions and illustrations of human dissections were published in the seminal work `` de humani corporis fabrica '' by andreas vesalius.galen 's theory of the physiology of the circulatory system remained unchallenged until ca . 1242 , when ibn al-nafis published his book `` sharh tashrih al-qanun li’ ibn sina '' ( `` commentary on anatomy in avicenna 's canon '' ) , in which he reported his discovery of the pulmonary circulation.galen saw himself as a physician and a philosopher , as he wrote in his treatise titled `` the best physician is also a philosopher '' . galen was very interested in the debate between the rationalist and empiricist medical sects , and his use of direct observation , dissection and vivisection is a complex middle ground between the extremes of those two viewpoints . many of his works have been preserved and/or translated from the original greek , although many were destroyed and some credited to him are believed to be spurious . although there is some debate over the date of his death , galen was no younger than seventy when he died .
central pier is a pier in blackpool , england . it is one of three piers in the town of blackpool , and was built in 1868 .
william friedkin ( ; born august 29 , 1935 ) is an american movie and television director , producer and screenwriter . he is best known for directing the action thriller movie `` the french connection '' ( 1971 ) and the supernatural horror movie `` the exorcist '' ( 1973 ) , the former of which won five academy awards , including best picture , best adapted screenplay and best director . he also earned him a nomination for the academy award for best director .
typhoon francisco was a tropical cyclone that reached japan and the korean peninsula in august 2019 . the storm started from a trough over the open pacific ocean on july 29 . francisco became a tropical depression on august 1 . moving along a northwest course toward japan , it quickly gained strength and intensified over the following days . it reached typhoon strength on august 5 . it reached kyushu at peak strength with winds of 130 km/h ( 80 mph ) . the weakened storm traversed the korea strait before striking south korea on august 6 . turning toward the east , francisco became an extratropical cyclone on august 7 . it later impacted hokkaido before continuing across the northern pacific and dissipating.in anticipation of francisco hitting japan , officials in kyushu ordered evacuations for coastal residents in and around miyazaki . transportation across the region was disrupted , with flights and train service cancelled . the storm brought locally damaging winds and heavy rain . wind gusts up to downed trees and power lines , leaving 20,710 households without power . two people died and four others were injured in incidents related to the storm .
the arrondissement of altkirch is an arrondissement of france . it is part of the haut-rhin `` département '' in the grand est region . its capital , and prefecture of the department , is the city of altkirch .
 what i 've done is a 2007 song by linkin park . it was released as the first single from their third studio album `` minutes to midnight '' . `` what i 've done '' was released as a radio single on april 1 , 2007 , as a digital download on april 2 , 2007 , and as a cd single on april 30 . `` what i 've done '' was nominated for `` best hard rock performance '' at the 52nd grammy awards , but did not win . `` what i 've done '' was the main theme in the 2007 science fiction movie `` transformers '' and also appears on `` '' ( 2007 ) . it was certified five times platinum by the riaa . it is the band 's most successful song , though not necessarily most well-known , due to the fact that singles in the us used to have higher sales in general during the second-half of the 2000s . `` what i 've done '' was featured in the video game guitar hero world tour . in january 2011 , it was released in a linkin park dlc pack for `` rock band 3 '' .

ballater is a burgh in aberdeenshire , scotland . it is on the river dee , immediately east of the cairngorm mountains . ballater is known for its spring water , once said to cure scrofula . it has more than 1500 inhabitants .
 status of a combatant is the legal status of a person who has the right to engage in hostilities during an international armed conflict . the legal definition of `` combatant '' is found at article 43 ( 2 ) of additional protocol i ( ap1 ) to the geneva conventions of 1949 . it states that `` members of the armed forces of a party to a conflict ( other than medical personnel and chaplains covered by article 33 of the third convention ) are combatants , that is to say , they have the right to participate directly in hostilities . '' on the other hand , as a rule , are legal targets themselves for the opposite side regardless the specific circumstances at hand , they can be attacked regardless of the specific circumstances simply due to their status , so as to deprive their side of their support.in addition to having the right to participate in hostilities , combatants have the right to the status of prisoners of war when captured during an international armed conflict . `` while all combatants are obliged to comply with the rules of international law applicable in armed conflict , violations of these rules shall not deprive a combatant of his right to be a combatant or , if he falls into the power of an adverse party , of his right to be a prisoner of war . ''
will mcbride ( january 10 , 1931 – january 29 , 2015 ) was an american photographer . he worked in reportage , art photography and book illustration as well as a painter and sculptor . mcbride was born in springfield , massachusetts.mcbride died on january 29 , 2015 in springfield , massachusetts , aged 83 .
vrancea ( ) is a county ( judeţ ) in romania , with its seat at focșani .
dachau was a nazi concentration camp during world war ii . the camp opened in march 1933 and was intended to hold political prisoners . it is near the town of dachau , about northwest of munich in the state of bavaria , in southern germany.the main camp was liberated by american forces on april 29 , 1945 . prisoners lived in constant fear of brutal treatment and terror detention including standing cells , floggings , the so-called tree or pole hanging , and standing at attention for extremely long periods.there were 32,000 documented deaths at the camp , and thousands that are undocumented . about 10,000 of the 30,000 prisoners were sick at the time of liberation .
smith county ( standard abbreviation : sm ) is a county in the u.s. state of kansas . in 2010 census , 3,853 people lived there . its county seat is smith center . the county is named after maj. j. nelson smith , who was part of the 2nd colorado cavalry , killed in action at the battle of westport on october 21 , 1864.the geographic center of the contiguous united states is within the county , near lebanon .

valparai ( originally known as poonachimalai ) is a taluk and hill station in the coimbatore district of tamil nadu , india . it consists of anamalai tiger reserve ( earlier known as indira gandhi wildlife sanctuary and national park ( igwls & np ) and prior to that as anaimalai wildlife sanctuary ) . it is located above sea level on the anaimalai hills range of the western ghats . the foothill starts exactly from monkey falls which is at a distance of to valparai . the route to valparai from the foothills consists of 40 hairpin bends . the kerala state border town of malakkappara is at a distance of 26 miles from valparai . while major portions of the land are owned by private tea companies , large forest areas continue to be out of bounds .
microsoft powerpoint is a computer program made by microsoft . powerpoint was first released on april 20 , 1987 for macintosh computers . microsoft bought powerpoint for $ 14 million three months after it appeared . powerpoint is one of many programs run by the company microsoft . it can be identified by its trademark orange , p , and logo . it offers users many ways to display information from simple presentations to complex multimedia presentations . powerpoint became a part of the microsoft office suite first offered in 1989 for macintosh and in 1990 for windows . powerpoint included several microsoft apps . beginning with powerpoint 4.0 ( 1994 ) , powerpoint was integrated into microsoft office development , and adopted common components and a converged user interface.powerpoint 's market share was very small at first , prior to introducing a version for microsoft windows , but grew rapidly with the growth of windows and of office . since the late 1990s , powerpoint 's worldwide market share of presentation software has been estimated at 95 percent.powerpoint was originally designed to provide visuals for group presentations within business organizations , but has come to be very widely used in many other communication situations , both in business and beyond . the impact of this much wider use of powerpoint has been experienced as a powerful change throughout society , with strong reactions including advice that it should be used less , should be used differently , or should be used better.powerpoint was originally designed to provide visuals for group presentations within business organizations , but has come to be very widely used in many other communication situations , both in business and beyond . the impact of this much wider use of powerpoint has been experienced as a powerful change throughout society , with strong reactions including advice that it should be used less , should be used differently , or should be used better.the first powerpoint version ( macintosh 1987 ) was used to produce overhead transparencies , the second ( macintosh 1988 , windows 1990 ) could also produce color 35mm slides . the third version ( windows and macintosh 1992 ) introduced video output of virtual slideshows to digital projectors , which would over time completely replace physical transimation and slides . a dozen major versions since then have added many additional features and modes of operation and have made powerpoint available available beyond apple macintosh and microsoft windows , adding versions for ios , android , and web access .

ambiguity is a concept of ambiguity . it is a situation where the meaning of a word or phrase is not explicitly defined . it makes several plausible interpretations . a common aspect of ambiguity is uncertainty . it is an attribute of any idea or statement whose meaning can not be definitively resolved according to a rule or process with a finite number of steps.the `` ambi- '' part of the term reflects an idea of `` two '' , as in `` two meanings '' .the concept of ambiguity is generally contrasted with vagueness . in ambiguity , specific and distinct interpretations are permitted . with information that is vague , it is difficult to form any interpretation at the desired level of specificity . for example , the same piece of information may be ambiguous in one context and unambiguous in another .
riom-parsonz is a former municipality of the district albula in the canton of graubünden in switzerland.it was created on 1 january 1979 when the former municipalities of riom and parsonz merged into the new municipality of surses .
cheney is a commune . it is in the yonne department in the center of france .
iron ores are rocks and minerals from which metallic iron can be extracted . the ores are usually rich in iron oxides and vary in color from dark grey , bright yellow , or deep purple to rusty red . iron is usually found in the form of magnetite ( , 72.4 % fe ) , hematite ( , 69.9 % fe ) , goethite ( , 62.9 % fe ) , limonite ( , 55 % fe ) or siderite ( , 48.2 % fe ) .ores containing very high quantities of hematite or magnetite are known as `` natural ore '' or `` direct shipping ore '' . this means they can be fed directly into iron-making blast furnaces . iron ore is the raw material used to make pig iron , which is one of the main raw materials to make steel—98 % of the mined iron ore is used to make steel .
melissa ellen gilbert ( born may 8 , 1964 ) is an american actress , television director , producer and politician . she was the president of the screen actors guild from 2001 to 2005.from 1974 to 1984 , she starred as laura ingalls wilder , the second oldest daughter of charles ingalls ( played by michael landon ) . during the run of `` little house '' , gilbert appeared in several popular television movies , including `` the diary of anne frank '' and `` the miracle worker '' .in 2016 , gilbert ran for u.s. congress as a democrat in michigan 's 8th congressional district and she won the democratic primary . she later dropped out because of head and neck injuries .

a java virtual machine ( jvm ) is a virtual machine that allows a computer to run java programs as well as programs written in other languages that are also compiled to java bytecode .
an overlord in the feudal system was a lord of a certain estate that belonged to a tenant-in-chief . the title of an overlord was held by the monarch , who in most cases was the king or queen . the title of an overlord was usually held by a knight or military administrator . in the feudalism of england , land was usually given to a tenant-in-chief .
asier del horno ( born 19 january 1981 ) is a spanish football player . he plays for athletic bilbao .
actinium is a chemical element . it has the chemical symbol ac . it has the atomic number 89 . it is a soft silvery-white radioactive metal . it reacts rapidly with oxygen and moisture in air . this produces a white coating of actinium oxide . it is a transition metal.actinium was discovered in 1899 by french chemist andré-louis debierne . friedrich oskar giesel later independently isolated it in 1902 . he also discovered that it was already known . he gave it the name emanium .
john joseph horgan ( born august 7 , 1959 ) is a canadian politician . he is the 36th and current premier of british columbia since 2017.he has been leader of the british columbia new democratic party since 2014 and the member of the legislative assembly ( mla ) for the constituency of langford-juan de fuca since 2005.on march 17 , 2014 , he announced his candidacy for leadership of the bc ndp in the 2011 leadership election , finishing third.horgan was acclaimed to the position on may 1 , 2014 and was officially inaugurated as party leader on may 5 , 2014.on may 9 , 2017 , premier christy clark 's liberal government was reduced to 43 seats , one seat short of a majority . on may 29 , 2017 , it was announced that the ndp and green party had reached a confidence and supply agreement in which the greens would support an ndp minority government for four years . following a non-confidence motion on june 29 , 2017 , which was won ( 44–42 ) by the combined votes of the ndp and green members , lieutenant governor judith guichon turned down clark 's request for a snap election and invited the ndp to form a minority government.horgan replaced clark as the premier of british columbia . horgan is the first ndp premier of the province since ujjal dosanjh in 2001 .
gnetum is a genus of gymnosperms . it is the only genus in the family gnetaceae and order gnetales . they are tropical evergreen trees , shrubs and lianas . unlike other gymnosperms , they have vessel elements in the xylem . some species have been proposed to be the first plants to be insect-pollinated . their fossils occur in association with extinct pollinating scorpionflies.molecular phylogenies based on nuclear and plastid sequences from most of the species indicate hybridization among some of the southeast asian species . fossil-calibrated molecular-clocks suggest that the `` gnetum '' lineages now found in africa , south america and southeast asia are the result of ancient long-distance dispersal across seawater .
karol cyryl modzelewski ( 23 november 1937 – 28 april 2019 ) was a polish historian , writer , politician and academic . he was one of the leading figures of the democratic opposition in the polish people 's republic from the 1960s to the 1980s . modzelewski was born in warsaw.modzelewski died on 28 april 2019 in warsaw , at the age of 81 .

the following is a list of deaths that should be noted in june 2018 . for deaths that should be noted before the month that the world is in , please see `` months '' . names under each date are noted in the order of the alphabet by last name or pseudonym . deaths of non-humans are noted here also if it is worth noting.each listing of a death must have a source . if no reference is included , the death notice will be removed . the following are the requirements of adding a name to the list in its order : name , age , where they came from , what the person is known for , cause of death ( if known ) and a source .

the bosnia and herzegovina national football team is the national football team of bosnia and herzegovina .
leukodystrophies is a rare disease of the brain . it degenerates white matter in the brain . the word `` leukodystrophy '' comes from the greek roots `` leuko '' , `` white '' , `` dys '' , `` abnormal '' and `` troph '' , `` growth '' . leukodystrophies are caused by imperfect growth or development of the myelin sheath , the fatty insulating covering around nerve fibers.leukodystrophies may be classified as hypomyelinating or demyelinating diseases , depending on whether the damage is present before birth or occurs after . other demyelinating diseases are usually not congenital and have a toxic or autoimmune cause.when damage occurs to white matter , immune responses can lead to inflammation in the central nervous system ( cns ) , along with loss of myelin . the degeneration of white matter can be seen in an mri scan and used to find leukodystrophy . leukodystrophy is characterized by specific symptoms including decreased motor function , muscle rigidity , and eventually degeneration of sight and hearing.while the disease is fatal , the age of onset is a key factor , as infants have a typical life expectancy of 2–8 years , while adults live more than a decade after onset . treatment options are limited , although hematopoietic stem cell transplantations using bone marrow or cord blood seem to help in certain types while further research is being done.the incidence of leukodystrophies is estimated at 1 in 7,600 . the majority of types involve the inheritance of an x-linked recessive , or x-linked dominant trait , while others are the result of spontaneous mutation rather than genetic inheritance .
the al-shams ( ) was an islamist paramilitary wing in east pakistan . it was made up of local bengalis and muhajirs that along with the pakistan army and the al-badr , was accused of conducting a mass killing campaign against bengali nationalists , civilians , religious and ethnic minorities during 1971 . the group was banned by the independent government of bangladesh , but most of its members had fled the country during and after the indo-pakistani war of 1971 , which led to bangladesh 's independence .
a multitude of languages are used in canada . according to the 2011 canadian census , english and french are the mother tongues of 56.0 % and 21.4 % of canadians respectively . many canadians have working knowledge of english while 29.8 % have a working knowledge of french.the official languages act of 1969 , both english and french have official federal status throughout canada . all government services , including the courts , and all federal legislation is enacted bilingually . new brunswick is the only canadian province that has both english and french as its official languages .
occitan is a romance language . it is spoken in southern france , in the occitan valleys , and in the regions of calabria and italy . it is also spoken in the linguistic enclave of guardia piemontese ( calabria , italy ) .occitan is one of the two official romance languages in france . the other is french . the other is spanish.occitan is written in the latin alphabet by its native speakers . the alphabet is made up of four letters : a , b , c , d , e , and f. it is written in the roman alphabet , like french , spanish , and latin . these letters are arranged in similar ways so that the sounds of the language are usually different from those of other romance languages . for example , the english alphabet has a lower vowel sound , like `` ch '' in french , `` ch '' in spanish , and `` t '' in french , like `` t '' in french , but `` t '' in french , like `` t '' in french , `` t '' in german , and `` t '' in french.occitan is one of the few romance languages that is still spoken in parts of southern france . the northern and easternmost dialects of occitan have more morphological features . for example , the northern and easternmost dialects of occitan have more nasal sounds ; their last consonant is more like `` ca/ga- '' instead of `` ca/ga- '' ; the front-rounded sound instead of a consonant , whereas the southernmost dialects have more features in common with the ibero-romance languages ( e.g . betacism ; voiced fricatives between vowels in place of voiced stops ; - '' ch '' - in place of `` it '' - ) , and gascon has a number of unusual features not seen in other dialects , like loss of between vowels ; and intervocalic `` -r- '' and final `` -t/ch '' in place of medieval -- .

army burn hall college is a private school founded by missionary society of mill hill ( mhm ) in abbottabad , pakistan in 1943 . originally established as a boarding school for boys , it was given to the pakistan army education corps in 1977 . it was renamed as army burn hall college in 1977 and has since expanded to multiple single-sex campuses for boys and girls in the city offering education up to the master 's level .

caroline patricia lucas ( born 9 december 1960 ) is a british politician . she is the leader of the green party of england and wales and has been the member of parliament ( mp ) for brighton pavilion since the 2010 general election.she was the first leader of the green party in 2008 and was elected to the constituency of brighton pavilion in 2010 , becoming the party 's first mp . she stood down as party leader in 2012 to spend more time on an ultimately successful campaign to be re-elected as an mp .
sven gösta ågren ( august 3 , 1936 – june 24 , 2020 ) was a finnish author . he won the finlandia prize in 1988 for `` jär '' . he was known for his left-wing sympathies , which can be seen in his autobiographical work about the rural `` proletariat '' .he published poems , essays and biographies . among the literary prizes awarded to him was the finlandia prize for fiction for the poetry collection jär ( 'here ' ) in 1989 . he was born in ostrobothnia , on the west coast of finland.gösta ågren died on june 24 , 2020 in helsinki , aged 83 .

gumi is a japanese word that means `` light '' or `` very light '' . it is the japanese word for light . it is the most common japanese word for light .
tierra del fuego ( spanish for `` land of fire '' ) is an archipelago off the southernmost tip of south america , across the strait of magellan . the archipelago has the main island , isla grande de tierra del fuego , with an area of , and a group of many islands , including cape horn and diego ramírez islands.tierra del fuego is divided between chile and argentina . europeans first explored the islands during ferdinand magellan 's expedition of 1520 ; `` tierra del fuego '' and similar namings stem from sightings of the many bonfires that the natives built . settlement by those of european descent and the great displacement of the native populations did not begin until the second half of the 19th century , at the height of the patagonian sheep farming boom and of the local gold rush . today , petroleum extraction dominates economic activity in the north of tierra del fuego , while tourism , manufacturing , and antarctic logistics are important in the south .

wcw monday nitro is a professional wrestling show produced by world championship wrestling ( wcw ) . it was first shown on tnt on september 4 , 1995 . it was later shown on the wwf 's `` monday night raw '' . the show was created by eric bischoff and ted turner . it was the monday night wars , a television ratings battle between the wwf and wcw . the new world order ( nwo ) were a group of professional wrestlers that wanted to take over wcw . `` nitro '' was the most popular show from the beginning . it was succeeded by `` raw '' , which was seen as the most popular show on the wwf . however , `` nitro '' was not as popular as `` raw '' , because the nwo storyline was becoming less popular . on april 1998 , a few weeks after stone cold steve austin won his first wwf championship , `` raw '' beat `` nitro '' in the ratings for the first time in almost two years .
buangkok mrt station ( ne9 ) is an underground mass rapid transit ( mrt ) station on the north east mrt line in sengkang , singapore .
ryan wayne white ( december 6 , 1971 – april 8 , 1990 ) was an american teenager . he was born in kokomo , indiana . he became a national poster child for hiv/aids in the united states after not returning to school following a diagnosis of aids.as a hemophiliac , he became infected with hiv from a contaminated factor viii blood treatment and , when diagnosed in december 1984 , was given six months to live . doctors said he was no risk to other students as aids is not an airborne disease and spreads through body fluids . but aids was not understood by the general public at the time . when white tried to return to school , many parents and teachers in howard county rallied against his attendance due to concerns of the disease spreading through bodily fluid transfer.a lengthy administrative appeal process ensued , and news of the conflict turned ryan into a popular celebrity and advocate for aids research and public education . surprising his doctors , ryan white lived five years longer than predicted . he died on april 8 , 1990 , one month before his high school graduation .
north mississippi allstars is an american southern rock band from hernando , mississippi . the band was formed in 1996 .
raymond crawford ( born 13 july 1936 ) is an english former international footballer . he played as a striker in a career that saw him score over 300 goals at club level .
tropical storm fay was the sixth named storm of the 2008 atlantic hurricane season . fay formed on august 15 as a strong tropical wave . it passed over the dominican republic , cuba , puerto rico , and the florida keys . it moved slowly through the florida keys until it moved northward into the gulf of mexico . fay then moved onto land near naples , florida.fay then turned north and made landfall in the florida peninsula . it then turned northeast and went into the atlantic ocean near melbourne.fay then moved west across the panhandle . it then moved due west across the panhandle . it reached gainesville and panama city , florida.fay zigzagged from water to land . this makes fay the first storm in florida four times to hit land in florida . thirty-six people were blamed on fay . the storm also resulted in one of the most tornadoes ever recorded on a tropical cyclone . fay also caused many tornadoes in the united states . three of these were rated as ef2 . damage from fay was heavy . this has been estimated at $ 560 million .
dame elizabeth rosemond taylor ( february 27 , 1932 – march 23 , 2011 ) was an english actress , businesswoman , and humanitarian . she began her career as a child actress in the early 1940s . she was one of the most popular stars of classical hollywood in the 1950s . she continued her career successfully into the 1960s , and remained a well-known public figure for the rest of her life . in 1999 , the american film institute named her the seventh greatest female screen legend .

`` single ladies ( put a ring on it ) '' is a 2008 song by american r & b singer beyoncé . it was the fourth single from her third studio album `` i am ... sasha fierce '' ( 2008 ) . it was released as a single on october 13 , 2008 . it showed the contrast between beyoncé and her onstage alter ego sasha fierce . the song explores men 's refusal to propose or commit . in the song , the female protagonist is in a club to celebrate her single status . `` single ladies '' won three grammy awards in 2010 , including song of the year . several news media sources named it as one of the best songs of 2008 , while some considered it one of the best songs of the decade . it topped the us `` billboard '' hot 100 chart for four non-consecutive weeks and has been certified quadruple-platinum by the recording industry association of america ( riaa ) . the song charted among the top ten in the singles category in several other countries . globally , it was 2009 's seventh best-selling digital single with 6.1 million copies sold thus becoming one of the best-selling singles of all time .
alaska airlines is the largest airline in the united states . it is based in seatac , washington . it was founded in 1937 . it is the eighth largest airline in the world when measured by fleet size , scheduled passengers carried , and the number of destinations served . alaska and its regional partners horizon air and skywest airlines operate a large domestic route network . it runs from the pacific northwest and alaska to over one hundred destinations in the contiguous united states , hawaii , canada , costa rica , and mexico .

in cryptography , a key distribution center ( kdc ) is part of a cryptosystem intended to reduce the risks inherent in exchanging keys . kdcs often operate in systems within which some users may have permission to use certain services at some times and not at others .
frederick franklin ( 1840–1873 ) was a united states navy sailor . he received the medal of honor for actions during the 1871 korean campaign .

 private damages ( or exemplary damages ) are damages usually awarded to the defendant for outrageous conduct . they may also be used to reform or deter the defendant and others from engaging in conduct similar to that which formed the basis of the lawsuit . the purpose of punitive damages is not to compensate the plaintiff . the plaintiff will receive all or some of the punitive damages award . latin american court systems often give punitive damages in limited cases . for example , punitive damages awarded to one party in a us case would be difficult to get recognition for in a european court in which punitive damages may be considered to violate ordre public .
 is a province in the region of apulia in italy .

lewis & clark college is a private liberal arts college in portland , oregon . it was founded in 1867 as the albany collegiate institute in albany , oregon . the college was relocated to portland in 1938 and in 1942 adopted the name lewis & clark college after the lewis and clark expedition . it has an undergraduate college of arts and sciences , a school of law , and a graduate school of education and counseling .
in physical sciences , mechanical energy is the sum of potential energy and kinetic energy . it is the macroscopic energy associated with a system . the principle of conservation of mechanical energy states that if an isolated system is subject only to conservative forces , then its mechanical energy is constant . if an object moves in the opposite direction of a conservative net force , the potential energy will increase ; and if the speed ( not the velocity ) of the object changes , the kinetic energy of the object also changes.in all real systems , however , nonconservative forces , such as frictional forces , will be present , but if they are small , the mechanical energy changes little and its conservation is a useful approximation .
