michelle `` shelly '' jenneke ( ; born 23 june 1993 ) is an australian hurdler and model . she won a silver medal for the 100 m hurdles at the 2010 summer youth olympics and the 100 m hurdles at the 2016 australian athletics championships to qualify for the rio olympic games.in 2012 , she received worldwide media attention after her pre-race warm-up dance went viral on the internet . she was featured in the 2013 `` sports illustrated '' swimsuit issue .
a breviary ( latin : `` breviarium '' ) is a liturgical book used in christianity for praying the canonical hours .
the alster ( ) is a right tributary of the elbe river in northern germany . it has its source near henstedt-ulzburg , schleswig-holstein . it flows somewhat southwards through much of the free and hanseatic city of hamburg and joins the elbe in central hamburg .
babozai ( often spelled : `` babuzai '' ) is a town and union council of mardan district in the khyber pakhtunkhwa province of pakistan . it is at 34°50'0n 72°8'0e and has an altitude of 1754 metres ( 5757 feet ) .
siouxsie and the banshees was a punk rock band . it was formed in 1976 in london , england by singer siouxsie sioux and bass guitarist steven severin.siouxsie and the banshees were a very big influence on the punk rock music scene in the 1980s . they had a big influence on the gothic music scene.siouxsie and the banshees 's first album , `` the scream '' , was released in 1978 . in 1980 , they changed their musical direction and became `` almost a different band '' with `` kaleidoscope '' . `` juju '' ( 1981 ) also reached the top 10 in the uk albums chart . in 1988 , the band made a breakthrough in north america with the album `` peepshow '' . there was a lot of support from alternative rock radio stations . they became a mainstream hit in the us in 1991 with the single `` kiss them for me '' .
burglary ( also called breaking and entering and sometimes housebreaking ) is breaking and entering a building or other areas to do something illegal there . usually that crime is theft , but most jurisdictions include others within the ambit of burglary.to commit burglary is to `` burgle '' , a term back-formed from the word `` burglar '' , or to `` burglarize '' .
princess charlotte of cambridge ( charlotte elizabeth diana ; born 2 may 2015 ) is a member of the british royal family . she is the second child and only daughter of prince william , duke of cambridge , and catherine , duchess of cambridge . she is fourth in the line of succession to the british throne.princess charlotte was born at st mary 's hospital in london on 2 may 2015 . she is the third child and only daughter of prince william , duke of cambridge and catherine , duchess of cambridge .
ælfweard ( c. 902 – august 2 , 924 ) was the second son of edward the elder . he was the eldest born to his second wife ælfflæd .
an inventor is a person who creates or discovers a new thing . it becomes known as an invention . the word `` inventor '' comes from the latin verb `` invenire '' , `` invent- '' , to find . the system of patents was created to encourage inventors by giving them limited term , limited monopoly on inventions that were thought to be novel , non-obvious , and useful . although inventing is closely associated with science and engineering , inventors are not engineers nor scientists .
dastilbe is an extinct genus of bony fish from the aptian .
netball is a kind of ball sport . it is played in more than 80 countries . it was developed in england in the 1890s . it is played by two teams of seven people . it is most popular in schools . it is played by women . according to the inf , netball is played by more than 20 million people in more than 80 countries . netball is not played at the olympic games.games are played on a rectangular court with raised goal rings at each end . each team tries to score goals by passing a ball down the court and shooting it through its goal ring . players are assigned positions . these positions are assigned to certain places . during general play , a player with the ball can hold on to it for only three seconds before shooting for a goal or passing to another player . the winning team is the one that scores the most goals . netball games are 60 minutes long . variations have been developed to increase the game 's pace and appeal to a wider audience .
the 2014 fifa world cup final took place on 13 july 2014 at the maracanã stadium in rio de janeiro , brazil to determine the 2014 fifa world cup champion . germany defeated argentina 1–0 in extra time , with the only goal being scored by mario götze . götze collected andré schürrle 's cross from the left on his chest before volleying a high left-footed shot into the net.the match was the third final between the two countries , a world cup record , after their 1986 and 1990 matches , and billed as the world 's best player ( lionel messi ) versus the world 's best team ( germany ) .before the match , germany had reached the world cup final seven times ( six times as west germany from 1954 to 1990 ) , winning three ( 1954 , 1974 , 1990 ) and was runners-up four times ( 1966 , 1982 , 1986 , 2002 ) ; argentina had reached four finals , winning twice ( 1978 , 1986 ) and placing second twice ( 1930 , 1990 ) .the result marked germany 's fourth world cup title and their first world cup title as a unified nation . the victory meant that three world cup final have been won by teams from the same continent , following italy in 2006 and 2010 respectively , the first time this has happened in world cup history . it was also the first time that three consecutive world cup finals were still tied after 90 minutes . the final marked the first time a world cup hosted in the americas was not won by a team from the continent.the winning german team , miroslav klose , became the top scorer in world cup history .
the is an art museum in kyoto , japan.the museum is also known as momak ( museum of modern art , kyoto ) .
the premier of yukon ( or unofficially , the premier of the yukon ) is the first minister for the canadian territory of yukon . the post is the territory 's head of government and `` de facto '' chief executive , although its powers are considerably smaller than that of a provincial premier.the office was created in 1978 .
tula ( `` tulaùlula '' ) is a town and `` comune '' ( municipality ) in the province of sassari in sardinia , italy . as of 2016 , 1,664 people lived there . its area is 56.85 km² . it is 9 meters above sea level .
a hearse is a large vehicle , especially a car , used to carry the dead body of a person in a coffin/casket at a funeral , wake , or memorial service . they range from deliberately anonymous vehicles to very formal heavily decorated vehicles .
metallurgy is the study of metals and how they behave . it can include the chemical properties of metals , their mixtures ( the way they behave ) , and their mixtures ( the way they behave ) .the science of metallurgy can be divided into two broad categories : chemical metallurgy and physical metallurgy . chemical metallurgy is concerned with reducing and oxidation of metals , and the chemical performance of metals . chemical metallurgy involves extraction of metals , thermodynamics , electrochemistry , and chemical degradation ( corrosion ) . in contrast , physical metallurgy studies the mechanical properties of metals , their properties , and their physical performance of metals . topics studied in physical metallurgy include crystallography , material characterization , mechanical metallurgy , phase transformations , and failure mechanisms.historically , metallurgy has focused on the production of metals . metal production begins with the processing of metals to extract the metal , and includes the mixture of metals to make alloys . in contrast , physical metallurgy focuses on the mechanical properties of metals , the physical properties of metals , and the physical performance of metals . topics studied in physical metallurgy include crystallography , material characterization , mechanical metallurgy , phase transformations , and failure mechanisms.ferrous metallurgy involves processes and alloys based on iron . non-ferrous metallurgy involves processes and alloys based on iron . the production of ferrous metals accounts for 95 percent of world metal production.modern metallurgists work in both emerging and traditional areas as part of an interdisciplinary team alongside material scientists , and other engineers . some traditional areas include mineral processing , metal production , heat treatment , failure analysis , and the joining of metals ( including welding , brazing , and soldering ) . emerging areas for metallurgists include nanotechnology , superconductors , composites , biomedical materials , electronic materials ( semiconductors ) , and surface engineering .
the škoda fabia is a automobile produced by škoda auto since 1999 . it is the successor of the felicia , which was discontinued in 2001 . the fabia was available in hatchback , estate and saloon body styles . in 2007 , the second generation was offered in hatchback and estate versions .
the national flag of anguilla , a british overseas territory , consists of a blue ensign with the british flag in the canton , charged with the coat of arms of anguilla .
the elder scrolls iv : oblivion is an action role-playing video game . it was made by bethesda game studios and published by bethesda softworks.the game was released for microsoft windows and xbox 360 in march 2006 . it was released for playstation 3 in march 2007 . in march 2007 , it was released for the playstation 3 in march 2007 . the game takes place in a fictional province of cyrodiil . in this game , oblivion 's main story is about the player 's efforts to stop a fanatical cult ( `` mythic dawn '' ) that plans to open portal gates to an evil realm known as `` oblivion '' .the game continues the open-world tradition of the older games by allowing the player to travel anywhere in the game world at any time and to ignore or postpone the main storyline indefinitely.the main story revolves around the player character 's efforts to stop a fanatical cult known as the `` mythic dawn '' that plans to open portal gates to a demonic realm known as `` oblivion '' .the game continues the open-world tradition of the older games by allowing the player to travel anywhere in the game world at any time and to ignore or postpone the main storyline indefinitely . a perpetual objective for players is to improve their character 's skills . early in the game , seven skills are selected by the player as major skills for their character , with those remaining termed as minor skills.upon release , `` oblivion '' was well received by critics and has won a number of industry and publication awards . it was praised for its impressive graphics , infinite game world , and schedule-driven npcs , and is now considered one of the greatest games ever made .
badfinger was a rock band from swansea , england . they were active from the 1960s to the 1980s . their best-known lineup was pete ham , mike gibbins , tom evans , and joey molland . they are probably best known for their influence on the 1970s power pop genre.badfinger had four consecutive worldwide hits from 1970 to 1972 : `` come and get it '' ( written and produced by paul mccartney , 1970 ) , `` no matter what '' ( produced by mal evans , 1970 ) , `` day after day '' ( produced by george harrison , 1971 ) , and `` baby blue '' ( produced by todd rundgren , 1972 ) . their song `` without you '' ( 1970 ) has been recorded many times , and became a uk number-one hit for harry nilsson and , decades later , a uk number-one for mariah carey.after apple records folded in 1973 , badfinger struggled with a host of legal , managerial and financial issues , leading to ham taking his own life in 1975 . over the next three years , the surviving members struggled to rebuild their personal and professional lives against a backdrop of lawsuits , which tied up the songwriters ' royalty payments for years .
the fairly oddparents is an american animated television series created by butch hartman for nickelodeon . the show follows timmy turner , a 10-year-old boy with two fairy godparents named cosmo and wanda , and a 16-year-old babysitter named vicky.it was produced by frederator studios ( 2001–2017 ) , nickelodeon animation studio , and billionfold inc. ( 2008–2017 ) .the series began as shorts on nick 's animation showcase , `` oh yeah ! cartoons '' , that aired from 1998 to 2001 . it was later picked up as a half-hour series on march 30 , 2001 , due to its popularity . it ended on november 25 , 2006 , totaling five seasons , but resumed production in 2008 . production of the series ceased again after hartman left nickelodeon in february 2018 .
 abdel rahman al-suqami ( june 28 , 1976 – september 11 , 2001 ) was named by the fbi as one of the hijackers of american airlines flight 11 in the september 11 , 2001 attacks . suqami was born in saudi arabia and grew up in the united states , where he is believed to have been a member of al-qaeda . on september 11 , 2001 , suqami boarded american airlines flight 11 and participated in the hijacking of the plane so that it could be crashed into the north tower of the world trade center as part of the coordinated attacks .
challis is a city of custer county in the state of idaho in the united states .
robert yale lary , sr. ( november 24 , 1930 – may 11 , 2017 ) was an american football player , businessman , and politician . he was born in fort worth , texas.lary played 11 seasons in the national football league ( nfl ) , all with the detroit lions , from 1952 to 1953 and from 1956 to 1964 , missing the 1954 and 1955 seasons due to military service as an army second lieutenant in korea.he played at the safety , punter , and return specialist positions , appeared in nine pro bowl games , and was a first-team all-nfl player five times . he led the nfl in punting three times , and at the time of his retirement in 1964 , his 44.3 yard punting average ranked second in nfl history , trailing only sammy baugh . he also totaled 50 nfl interceptions for 787 return yards , both of which ranked fifth in nfl history at the time of his retirement.lary died on may 11 , 2017 in austin , texas at the age of 86 .
terza rima is a stanza form that was first used by italian poet dante alighieri . it is a three-line stanza with rhyme scheme .
otto loewi ( 3 june 1873 – 25 december 1961 ) was a german-born british pharmacologist who discovered the role of acetylcholine as an endogenous neurotransmitter . for his discovery he was awarded the nobel prize in physiology or medicine in 1936 , which he shared with sir henry dale , who was a lifelong friend who helped to inspire the neurotransmitter experiment .
the fresh film festival ( ) is a festival for young people . it is held in limerick , ireland each spring . it has been held since 1997 . the festival also known as ireland 's young movie of the year . it screens movies made by young people between the ages of 7 and 18 .
andrew hill card jr. ( born may 10 , 1947 ) is an american politician . he was white house chief of staff under president george w. bush from 2001 to 2006 , as well as head of bush 's white house iraq group . card served as united states secretary of transportation under president george h. w. bush from 1992 to 1993.card announced his resignation as chief of staff on march 28 , 2006 , effective april 14 , 2006 . card was the acting dean of the bush school of government and public service , at texas a & m university .
sienna is an earth pigment . it is a yellowish-green colour . when heated , it becomes a reddish brown and is called `` burnt sienna '' . it was created in the renaissance . along with umber , it was one of the first pigments to be used by humans.sienna is found in many cave paintings . since the renaissance , it has been one of the brown pigments most widely used by artists.the first recorded use of `` sienna '' as a colour name in english was in 1760.sienna is one of the traditional pigments used by artists . the name comes from the city-state of siena , where it was produced during the renaissance .
publius cornelius scipio africanus ( 236/235 bc – 183 bc ) was a roman general who later became a consul . many say he was one of the greatest military commanders and strategists of all time . his main achievements were during the second punic war . he is best known for defeating hannibal at the final battle of zama ( near modern zama , tunisia ) in 202 bc . the victory was one of the feats that earned him the agnomen africanus.scipio 's conquest of carthaginian iberia ended the battle of ilipa ( near alcalá del río , spain ) in 206 bc against hannibal 's brother mago barca . although considered a hero by the roman people , primarily for his victories against carthage , africanus had many enemies , especially cato the elder , who hated him deeply . in 187 bc , he was even tried alongside his brother for bribes during the roman–seleucid war . he retired from rome and settled in his villa in liternum .
turn left , turn right ( ) is a 2003 joint chinese-singaporean romance movie , filmed in taipei , taiwan . it was produced and directed by johnnie to and wai ka-fai , the film stars takeshi kaneshiro and gigi leung . the story is based on the illustrated book `` a chance of sunshine '' by taiwanese author jimmy liao , who makes a cameo appearance with his wife and daughter in the movie . it is also the first chinese-language asian movie ever from produced and distributed by warner bros.the original graphic novel was first published in 1999 . the characters in the novel were not given names , both characters were only referred to as `` him '' and `` her '' . chinese title of the book translates to `` turn left , turn right '' , `` a chance of sunshine '' is the original english title of the book , on the newer published editions the english title is shown as `` turn left , turn right '' . the book consists of a series of detailed illustrated images , with a small amount of text in poetry style . the film has managed to include every single image in the book with a high level of accuracy , although some are fleeting , possibly due to the fact that it was shot in taipei .
in physics , chemistry , and electronic engineering , an electron hole ( often simply called a hole ) is the lack of an electron at a position where one could exist in an atom . holes are not actually particles , but rather quasiparticles ; they are different from the positron , the antiparticle of the electron.in a normal atom or crystal lattice , the negative charge of the electrons is balanced by the positive charge of the atomic nuclei . the absence of an electron leaves a net positive charge at the hole 's location.holes in a metal or semiconductor crystal lattice can move through the lattice as electrons can , and act similarly to positively-charged particles . they play an important role in the operation of semiconductor devices such as transistors , diodes and integrated circuits .
the division of fremantle is an australian electoral division in western australia . it was one of the 75 divisions set up for the first federal election in 1901 . it is named after the fremantle river , which runs through the division.the division is located in the south-west of western australia , and includes the towns of perth , north stradbroke , perth , north stradbroke , north stradbroke island , south stradbroke island and parts of geelong .
bob kelly abreu ( born march 11 , 1974 in caracas , venezuela ) is a venezuelan professional baseball player . he currently plays as an outfielder for the los angeles dodgers of the major league baseball ( mlb ) .abreu has also played for the houston astros , philadelphia phillies , new york yankees , los angeles angels of anaheim , los angeles dodgers , and new york mets .
 ( 昭和の妖怪 , `` devil of shōwa '' ) is a japanese manchukuo politician . known for his brutal rule of the japanese puppet state manchukuo in northeast china , kishi was called `` shōwa no yōkai '' ( 昭和の妖怪 ; `` devil of shōwa '' ) .
antonín leopold dvořák ( born prague , 8 september 1841 ; died prague , 1 may 1904 ) was a czech-american composer . he was one of the greatest composers of the 19th century . dvořák was the successor to bedřich smetana , who was a famous composer of symphonic music from bohemia . dvořák was the first czech composer to compose a symphony . he wrote nine symphonies and a cello concerto , but he wrote a lot of other works as well . the cello concerto is one of his best-known works , and people say that he is the greatest cello composer of all time . dvořák also wrote chamber music , orchestral music and chamber music .
colonie is a town in albany county , new york , united states . it is the most populous suburb of albany , new york . as of the 2010 census , the town had a total population of 81,591 .
the imja khola is a tributary of the dudh kosi in nepal . it drains the slopes of mount everest . the khumbu glacier melts into the lobujya ( lobuche ) river , which flows southward as the imja khola to its confluence with the dudh kosi at tengboche.the imja khola collects water from the imja glacier through the dingboche valley .
didi kempot ( born didik prasetyo ; 31 december 1966 – 5 may 2020 ) was an indonesian singer-songwriter . he wrote some 700 songs , mainly in his native javanese language . from indonesia , didi was also popular in suriname and the netherlands , both of which have a javanese diaspora . he was born in jombang , suriname.kempot died on 5 may 2020 in jombang due to covid-19 , aged 54 .
anthony john hrkac ( born july 7 , 1966 ) is a canadian retired professional ice hockey right winger . he played a career total of 18 seasons in the national hockey league ( nhl ) . he played for the chicago blackhawks , new jersey devils , pittsburgh penguins , los angeles kings , new york islanders , st. louis blues and the new jersey devils . he was born in sarnia , ontario and is of croatian and ukrainian ancestry .
rio arriba county is a county in the u.s. state of new mexico . as of the 2010 census , the population was 40,246 . its county seat is tierra amarilla .
wells is a town in york county , maine . it was founded in 1643 . it is the third-oldest town in maine . the population in 2010 was 9,589 . wells beach is a popular summer destination .
south west trains ( swt ) is a british train operating company owned by stagecoach . they operated the `` south western '' rail franchise from 1996 until 2007 .
sir george houston reid ( 25 february 1845 – 12 september 1918 ) was the 4th prime minister of australia . he was premier of new south wales from 1894 to 1899 . before he was premier , reid was premier of new south wales from 1894 to 1899 . he was from the free trade party . reid was born in johnstone , renfrewshire , scotland.reid died on 12 september 1918 in sydney , new south wales from heart failure , aged 85 .
video camera tubes were devices based on the cathode ray tube that were used in television cameras to capture television images . several different types of tubes were in use from the early 1930s to the 1980s .
valdir joaquim de moraes ( november 23 , 1931 – january 11 , 2020 ) was a brazilian football player . he played as a goalkeeper . he spent all his playing career with palmeiras from 1958 to 1969 . he was born in rio de janeiro.de moraes died on january 11 , 2020 from multiple organ failure in rio de janeiro , aged 88 .
`` sunday bloody sunday '' is a 1983 song by irish rock band u2 . it is the first track from their 1983 album `` war '' and was released as the third single from the album in the netherlands and west germany . `` sunday bloody sunday '' is known for its militaristic drumbeat , harsh guitar , melodic harmonies and strong vocals . it is one of u2 's most well-known songs and has been played in many of their live concerts .
paracetamol ( or acetaminophen ) is a medicine used to treat pain and fever . it is also used to treat mild to moderate pain relief . it is the most commonly used medication for pain and fever in both the united states and europe . it is often sold in combination with other medications , such as in many cold medications . paracetamol is also used for severe pain , such as cancer pain and pain after surgery , in combination with opioid pain medication . it is usually used either by mouth or rectally.paracetamol was first made in 1877 . it is the most commonly used medication for pain and fever in both the united states and europe . it is on the world health organization 's list of essential medicines . paracetamol is available as a generic medicine , with brand names including tylenol and panadol . in 2017 , it was the 25th-most commonly prescribed in the united states , with more than 24 million prescriptions .
davao city is a city in the philippines . it is in the province of davao del sur . davao city is the third largest city in the philippines , after quezon city and manila . it is the capital of mindanao province .
aveluy is a commune . it is in the region hauts-de-france in the somme department in the north of france .
fort scott is a city in bourbon county , kansas , united states . it is south of kansas city , on the marmaton river . in 2010 , 8,087 people lived there . it is the home of the fort scott national historic site and the fort scott national cemetery . fort scott is named for gen. winfield scott .
valentina vasilevna tolkunova ( , 12 july 1946 – 22 march 2010 ) was a soviet and russian singer . she was given the title of honored artist of rsfsr ( 1979 ) and people 's artist of the rsfsr ( 1987 ) . her performances exhibited a kindhearted mood and sincerity . her voice was noted for its clarity .
roblox is an online game platform and game creation system . it allows users to program games and play games created by other users . it was created by david baszucki and erik cassel in 2004 . it was released in 2006 . the platform hosts user-created games of multiple genres coded in the programming language lua . `` roblox '' is free-to-play , with in-game purchases available through a virtual currency called `` robux '' . `` roblox '' has over 164 million monthly active users . it is played by over half of all children aged under 16 in the united states . `` roblox '' has received generally positive reviews from critics from critics .
kett 's rebellion was a rebellion in norfolk , england , during the reign of edward vi . it began on 8 july 1549 . a group of rebels destroyed fences . one of their targets was yeoman robert kett . but instead of resisting the rebels , kett agreed to their demands and offered to lead them . kett and his forces set up camp on mousehold heath to the north-east of the city on 12 july . the rebels stormed norwich on 29 july and took the city . on 1 august the rebels defeated a royal army led by the marquess of northampton who had been sent by the government to stop the rebellion . kett 's rebellion ended on 27 august . the rebels were defeated by an army under the leadership of the earl of warwick at the battle of dussindale . kett was captured , held in the tower of london , tried for treason , and hanged from the walls of norwich castle on 7 december 1549 .
lanark is a small town in the central belt of scotland . the name is believed to come from the cumbric `` '' meaning `` clear space , glade '' .lanark is traditionally the county town of lanarkshire , though there are several larger towns in the county . lanark railway station and coach station have frequent services to glasgow . there is little industry in lanark and some people work in glasgow and edinburgh . its shops serve the local agricultural community and surrounding villages . there is a large modern livestock auction market on the outskirts of the town .

moutiers-sur-le-lay is a commune . it is found in the region pays de la loire in the vendée department in the west of france .
er maria rilke ( 4 december 1875 – 29 december 1926 ) was a german-austrian poet and novelist . he is `` widely recognized as one of the most lyrically intense german-language poets '' . he wrote both verse and highly lyrical prose.rilke 's writings include one novel , several collections of poetry and several volumes of correspondence in which he invokes images that focus on the difficulty of communion with the ineffable in an age of disbelief , solitude and anxiety . these themes position him as a transitional figure between traditional and modernist writers.rilke traveled extensively throughout europe ( including russia , spain , germany , france and italy ) and , in his later years , settled in switzerland – settings that were key to the genesis and inspiration for many of his poems.while rilke is most known for his contributions to german literature , over 400 poems were originally written in french and dedicated to the canton of valais in switzerland . among english-language readers , his best-known works include the poetry collections `` duino elegies '' ( ' ) and `` sonnets to orpheus '' ( ' ) , the semi-autobiographical novel `` the notebooks of malte laurids brigge '' ( ' ) , and a collection of ten letters that was published after his death under the title `` letters to a young poet '' ( ' ) .
eli lilly and company is an american pharmaceutical company . they are headquartered in indianapolis , indiana . they are famous for being the first company to mass-produce the polio vaccine , and insulin . they are also the first pharmaceutical companies to produce human insulin using recombinant dna .
bill morey ( december 19 , 1919 – december 10 , 2003 ) was an american character actor . he was best known for playing oscar in the 1990s sitcom , `` the john larroquette show '' .morey was born on december 19 , 1919 in new york city , new york . he studied at the university of southern california . morey died on december 10 , 2003 in los angeles , california from heart failure , aged 89 .
swinton is a town and civil parish in south yorkshire , england . in 2001 there were 14,559 people living in swinton .
condé-sur-ifs is a commune . it is found in the region basse-normandie in the calvados department in the northwest of france .
the penalty shootout is a way of determining the winner in sports matches that would otherwise be in the game . the rules for penalty shootouts are different in different sports . however , the usual form is similar to penalty shots in that a single player takes one shot on goal from a certain spot . the only defender being the goalkeeper . if the result is still tied , the shootout usually continues on a goal-for-goal basis . the one that scores a goal is the winner . this may continue until every player has taken a shot , after which players may take extra shots , until the tie is broken , and is also known as sudden death .
national harbor is a census-designated place ( cdp ) in prince george 's county , maryland , united states . the population was 3,788 at the 2010 census .
 is a japanese television network . it was established in 2002 .
the bbc symphony orchestra ( bbc so ) is an orchestra based in london . it was started in 1930 . it is one of the four major orchestras of the united kingdom that does not have its own conductors . the orchestra was started by the bbc and the conductor thomas beecham in 1928 . beecham left the bbc in the next year . the task of assembling and training the orchestra fell to the bbc 's director of music , adrian boult . among its guest conductors in its first years was arturo toscanini . he said it was the finest orchestra he had ever conducted . after world war ii boult tried to maintain standards , but the senior management of the post-war bbc did not pay the orchestra the money to meet competition from new and well-funded rivals.after boult 's retirement from the bbc in 1950 , the orchestra went through a fallow period . boult 's successor , sir malcolm sargent , was popular with the public but did not have good rapport with his players . sargent 's successor , rudolf schwarz , made little public impact , and the bbc appointed high-profile chief conductors in the 1960s and 1970s . these included antal doráti , colin davis , pierre boulez and gennady rozhdestvensky . the bbc so remained underfunded and did not attract enough good players to rival the leading london orchestras.as a result of initiatives begun in the 1960s by the bbc controller of music william glock , performing standards gradually began to rise . under andrew davis in the 1990s and jiří bělohlávek in the 2000s , the orchestra prospered . by the second decade of the 21st century , the orchestra was once again regarded by critics as of first class status .
beatboxing ( also beat boxing or b-boxing ) is a form of vocal percussion . it involves the art of mimicking drum machines , typically a tr-808 synthesizer , using one 's mouth , lips , tongue , and voice . it may also involve vocal imitation of turntablism , and other musical instruments . beatboxing today is connected with hip-hop culture , often referred to as `` the fifth element '' of hip-hop , although it is not limited to hip-hop music . the term `` beatboxing '' is sometimes used to refer to vocal percussion in general .
nièvre is a department found in the center of france in the bourgogne-franche-comté region . it is named after the nièvre river , a tributary of the oise . its prefecture is the city of nièvre .
sharlto copley ( born 27 november 1973 ) is a south african actor . he played wikus van der merwe in the academy award-nominated science fiction movie `` district 9 '' , howling mad murdock in the 2010 adaptation of `` the a-team '' , agent c.m . kruger in the science fiction movie `` elysium '' , james corrigan in the science fiction horror movie `` europa report '' and king stefan in the dark fantasy adventure movie `` maleficent '' .he also played the title character in the science fiction movie `` chappie '' , as jimmy in `` hardcore henry '' , and starred in two seasons as christian walker of the tv series `` powers '' .sharlto is married to fellow south african actress and fashion model tanit phoenix .
kavala is a greek city . it is the capital of kavala prefecture which is one of 51 prefectures of greece . kavala is located on the bay of kavala . 51,068 people lived there according to 2001 census .
the history of baseball started in the 18th century , when boys and amateur fans played a baseball-like game by their own informal rules using homemade equipment . the popularity of the sport grew and amateur mens ' ball clubs were formed in the 1830-50s . semi-professional baseball clubs followed in the 1860s , and the first professional leagues arrived in the post-american civil war .
in baseball , a triple is the act of a batter safely reaching third base after hitting the ball , with neither the benefit of a fielder 's misplay ( see error ) nor another runner being put out on a fielder 's choice . a triple is sometimes called a `` three-bagger '' or `` three-base hit '' . for statistical and scorekeeping purposes it is denoted by 3b .
morissen is a former municipality of the district of surselva in the canton of graubünden in switzerland.on 1 january 2013 the former municipalities of cumbel , degen , lumbrein , morissen , suraua , vignogn , vella , and vrin merged into the new municipality of lumnezia .
roger walkowiak ( 2 march 1927 – 6 february 2017 ) was a french road bicycle racer . he won the 1956 tour de france . he was a professional rider from 1950 until 1960 . he was born in boulogne-billancourt , france.walker died on 6 february 2017 at the age of 89 .

hans modrow ( born 27 january 1928 ) was the last communist premier of east germany . he took office in the middle of the peaceful revolution and was the `` de facto '' leader of the country for much of the winter of 1989 and 1990.after the end of communist rule and reunification of germany , he was singled out by the new government and convicted of electoral fraud and perjury by the dresden district court in 1995 .
anxiety is an emotion . it is characterized by an unpleasant state of inner turmoil . it is accompanied by nervous behavior such as pacing back and forth , somatic complaints , and rumination . it is the unpleasant feelings of dread over anticipated events.the term was first used in 1966 by the english psychologist and psychiatrist nicholas hall .

in descriptive statistics , the interquartile range ( iqr ) is a measure of statistical dispersion . it is equal to the difference between 75th and 25th percentiles , or between upper and lower quartiles , iqr = `` q '' − `` q '' . in other words , the iqr is the first quartile subtracted from the third quartile ; these quartiles can be clearly seen on a box plot on the data . it is a trimmed estimator , defined as the 25 % trimmed range , and is a commonly used robust measure of scale .
hiroshi umemura ( born february 22 , 1972 ) is a japanese mixed martial artist . he competed in the bantamweight and featherweight division .
bedford heights is a city in ohio in the united states . it is in cuyahoga county .
ralph jimmy schulz ( 22 october 1968 – 25 november 2019 ) was a german technology executive and politician . he was a member of the bundestag from 2009 to 2013 and again from 2017 until his death in 2019 . schulz founded and sold an internet service provider called cyber solutions gmbh . he was born in bonn , germany.schulz died on 25 november 2019 in bonn after a long-illness at the age of 49 .

lucio urtubia jiménez ( 18 february 1931 – 18 july 2020 ) was a spanish anarchist . he was known for his practice of expropriative anarchism . urtubia carried out bank robberies and forgeries throughout the 1960s and 1970s . he was born in san sebastián , spain.urtubia died on 18 july 2020 in san sebastián from heart failure , aged 89 .
rashtriya swayamsevak sangh ( rss ) is an indian right-wing , hindu nationalist , paramilitary organization . the organization promotes the ideals of upholding indian culture and the values of a civil society . it spreads the ideology of hindutva , to `` strengthen '' the hindu community . it drew initial inspiration from european right-wing groups during world war ii . gradually , rss grew into a prominent hindu nationalist umbrella organisation . it has several affiliated organisations that established numerous schools , charities , and clubs to spread its ideological beliefs.the rss was banned once during british rule , and then thrice by the post-independence indian government , first in 1948 when nathuram godse , who claimed to have left rss in 1946 over ideological differences , assassinated mahatma gandhi ; then during the emergency ( 1975–1977 ) ; and for a third time after the demolition of babri masjid in 1992 .
the rainbow lorikeet ( `` trichoglossus moluccanus '' ) is a species of lorikeet . it is found in australia . it is common along the eastern seaboard , from northern queensland to south australia . its habitat is rainforest and coastal bush and woodland areas.the rainbow lorikeet has been introduced to perth , western australia ; tasmania ; auckland , new zealand ; and hong kong .
redevelopment is a new construction on a site that had previously been built . it is a process of land development uses to revitalize the physical , economic and social fabric of urban space .
an electricity meter ( also called an electrical meter or energy meter ) is a meter that measures the amount of electric energy used by a house , business , or an electrically powered device .
the hertz ( symbol hz ) is the si unit of frequency . it is one cycle per second . it is named after heinrich rudolf hertz , the first person to prove the existence of electromagnetic waves.the hertz is often used to describe sine waves , and to describe the clock speeds at which computers and other electronics are driven .
a carillon is a musical instrument . it is found in the bell tower ( belfry ) of a church or municipal building . it is made up of at least 23 cast bronze , cup-shaped bells , which are played serially to produce a melody , or together to play a chord . a carillon-like instrument with fewer than 23 bells is called a chime.the largest carillon in the world , with 120 bells , is in the palace of mafra in portugal.the carillon is the second heaviest of all living musical instruments , behind only the largest pipe organs . the heaviest carillon in the world ( at riverside church in new york city ) weighs over , whereas the wanamaker organ in philadelphia weighs .
 control engineering is a field of engineering that applies control theory to design systems to desired behaviors in control environments . control systems engineering uses sensors and detectors to measure the output performance of the process being controlled . these measurements are used to provide corrective feedback helping to achieve the desired performance . systems designed to perform without requiring human input are called automatic control systems ( such as cruise control for regulating the speed of a car ) .
henneveux is a commune . it is found in the region nord-pas-de-calais in the pas-de-calais department in the north of france .
josephine caroline gertrude mary faith harber ( 29 june 1914 – 30 june 1990 ) , better known as lynne carol , was a welsh actress . she was best known for playing busybody martha longhurst in the soap opera `` coronation street '' from the second episode in 1960 until the character was killed off in 1964 .
the north island , also officially named te ika-a-māui , is one of the two main islands of new zealand . it is separated from the larger but much less populous south island by cook strait . the island 's area is 212,000 square kilometres , making it the world 's 14th-largest island . about % of new zealand 's population lives in the north island .
newark is a city in the u.s. state of texas .
in mathematics , the lowest common denominator or least common denominator ( abbreviated lcd ) is the lowest common multiple of the denominators of a set of fractions . it simplifies adding , subtracting , and comparing fractions .
jonathan harshman winters iii ( november 11 , 1925 – april 11 , 2013 ) was an american comedian , actor , author , and television host . he was known for his role as grandpa smurf in `` the smurfs '' . he voiced papa smurf in `` the smurfs '' .winters was born on november 11 , 1925 in brooklyn , new york city , new york . he was married to dorothy winters from 1951 until his death in 2013 . they had four children . winters died on april 11 , 2013 in his home in santa barbara , california from natural causes , aged 88 .
a prefix is an affix added to the beginning of a word to change it into another word . for example , when the prefix `` un- '' is added to the word `` un- '' , it creates the word `` happy '' . in english , this is also called a preformative .
the lamborghini huracán is a sports car that is built by lamborghini . the huracán replaced the lamborghini gallardo in 2014 . the huracán has 610 metric horsepower and 4 wheel drive . the lp stands for `` longitudinale posteriore '' , which refers to the longitudinal mid-rear engine position .

 of japanese literature was influenced by influences from chinese literature , and were often written in classical chinese . indian literature also had an influence through the spread of buddhism in japan . eventually , japanese literature developed into a separate style , although the influence of chinese literature and classical chinese literature remained.after japan 's reopening of its ports to western trading and diplomacy in the 19th century , western literature has influenced the development of modern japanese writers . there have been two nobel prizes so far , as of 2020 .
sajid nawaz khan ( ) is a pakistani politician who has been the member of the national assembly of pakistan , since june 2013 .
bankstown bunker , formerly known as air defence headquarters sydney ( adhq sydney ) , is a heritage-listed defunct royal australian air force ( raaf ) operations facility . it is located on the corner of marion and edgar street , in condell park , city of canterbury-bankstown , new south wales , australia . it was designed by allied works council and built from 1943 to 1944 by stuart bros pty ltd of sydney.it is also known as air defence headquarters ruin sydney ( former ) , no . 1 fighter section headquarters , 1fshq , bankstown bunker and raaf no . 1 installation bankstown ; no . 101 fighter sector .

sir richard rodney bennett ( 29 march 1936 – 24 december 2012 ) was an english composer of movie , tv and concert music , and also a jazz pianist and occasional vocalist . he was based in new york city from 1979 until his death in 2012 .
the blackout is a british post-hardcore band formed in 2003 . they released their first ep `` the blackout ! the blackout ! the blackout ! '' in october 2007 the band released their debut album , `` we are the dynamite '' . their second record , `` the best in town '' , was released on 25 may 2009 in europe and 23 june 2009 in the us , both via epitaph records . the band 's third album , titled `` hope '' , was released on 4 april 2011 , and charted at number 27 in the uk album chart . their fourth studio album , titled `` start the party '' , was released on 21 january 2013 . the blackout 's final release was a five track ep entitled `` wolves '' , with their final release being held in their hometown of merthyr tydfil on saturday 28 march 2015 .
joseph walsh ( 1 may 1943 – 9 november 2014 ) was an irish fianna fáil politician . he served as minister for agriculture and food from 1992 to 1994 and 1997 to 2004 . he served as a teachta dála ( td ) for cork south-west constituency from 1977 to 1981 and 1982 to 2007 . he was a senator elected by the cultural and educational panel from 1981 to 1982 .

hamilton hill is a dc comics character . he is a known mayor of gotham city and an adversary of batman.hamilton hill was the mayor of gotham city from 1967 to 1977 .
bernt `` sump-hugo '' andersson ( 5 september 1933 – 6 january 2020 ) was a swedish football player and manager . he played as a midfielder . he made 91 allsvenskan appearances for djurgårdens if and scored 19 goals . he was born in stockholm.andersson died on 6 january 2020 in stockholm at the age of 86 .
action comics is an american comic book/magazine series . it introduced superman , one of the first major superhero characters . the publisher was originally known as national allied publications , and later as national comics publications and as national periodical publications , before taking on its current name of dc comics.its original incarnation ran from 1938 to 2011 and stands as one of the longest-running comic books with consecutively numbered issues . a second volume of `` action comics '' beginning with issue # 1 ran from 2011 to 2016 . `` action comics '' returned to its original numbering beginning with issue # 957 ( aug. 2016 ) .
sommarkrysset ( `` summer cross '' ) is a television program in sweden . it is shown live from the gröna lund amusement park in stockholm during the summer . it was first shown on 3 june 2005.the tv show was famous for their early bookings of music artists such as lady gaga , dua lipa , rita ora , jason mraz , ava max and ava max.the program consists of live performances by famous artists in front of a live audience while viewers can call in and win a certain amount of money . to have the chance to win this money , the viewer first has to figure out a word which is obtained by entering the answers to questions ( one letter in each box ) on a piece of graph paper with 5x5 squares like a crossword.the program was created by peter settman 's baluba productions and is produced settman 's baluba television.the lotto draw is usually broadcast live with as a presenter . annika duckmark has also been a regular presenter .
ram dass ( born richard alpert ; april 6 , 1931 – december 22 , 2019 ) , also known as baba ram dass , was an american spiritual teacher , psychologist , and author . his best known book , `` be here now '' ( 1971 ) , helped popularize eastern spirituality and yoga with the baby boomer generation in the west . he authored or co-authored twelve more books on spirituality over the next four decades , including `` grist for the mill '' ( 1977 ) , `` how can i help ? '' ( 1985 ) , and `` polishing the mirror '' ( 2013 ) .dass was born in boston , massachusetts . he studied at harvard university . dass died of a stroke in maui , hawaii on december 22 , 2019 at the age of 88 .
keitele is a large lake in central finland . the area of the lake is 493.59 km² . it is the 9th largest lake in the country . the lake is divided into three regions , ylä- , keski- , and ala-keitele . keski-keitele is the largest . water in the lake is clear and in excellent condition . the towns of äänekoski and viitasaari are located on the shores of keitele.the northernmost part of the lake is called ylä-keitele . a big part of ylä-keitele belongs to natura 2000 protection program because of its clear water and natural condition .
bleach is the first album by the american grunge band nirvana . it was released on june 15 , 1989 by sub pop . after the release of its debut single `` love buzz '' on sub pop in november 1988 , nirvana practiced for two to three weeks in preparation for recording a full-length album . `` bleach '' did not chart upon its original indie label release , but was well received by critics .
a transfer case is a part of the drivetrain of four-wheel drive vehicles . it transfers power from the transmission to the front and rear axles by means of drive shafts .
the little colonel is a 1933 american science fiction movie directed by william a. wellman and based on the 1933 novel of the same name by joseph hayes . it stars william a. wellman , william a. wellman , william a. wellman and was distributed by metro-goldwyn-mayer .
lincoln heights jail is a former jail building complex in the lincoln heights neighborhood of los angeles , california . it is located near to the los angeles river and is about southwest of the lincoln/cypress station . the original building built in the late 1920s is known for its art deco style . the jail was designated an los angeles historic-cultural monument on november 30 , 1993 .
lars olof jonathan söderblom , born 15 january 1866 in uppsala , sweden , dead 12 july 1931 in uppsala , sweden was a swedish clergyman . he was the church of sweden archbishop of uppsala between 1914 and 1931 . he was awarded the 1930 nobel peace prize .
the centre étienne desmarteau is a multi-purpose complex center with two ice rinks in montreal , quebec , canada .
refining is the process of purification of a 1 ( 1 ) substance or 2 ( 2 ) form . the term is usually used of a natural resource which is almost in usable form , but which is more useful in its pure form . for example , most types of natural petroleum will burn straight from the ground , but it will burn poorly and quickly clog an engine with residues and by-products.the refining of liquids is often done by distillation or fractionation . this process is useful , for example , for isolating different fractions of petroleum . gases can be refined in this way as well , by being cooled and/or compressed until they liquefy . gases and liquids can also be refined by extraction with a selective solvent that dissolves either the substance of interest , or the unwanted impurities.many solids can be refined by growing crystals in a solution of the impure material . the regular structure of the crystal tends to favor the desired material and exclude other kinds of particles.chemical reactions are often used to remove impurities of particular types.the use of silicon and other semiconductors in electronics depends on precise control of impurities . the zone melting process developed by william gardner pfann was used to produce pure germanium , and subsequently float-zone silicon became available when henry theuerer of bell labs adapted pfann 's method to silicon.types of materials that are usually refined :
the gaslight anthem is an american alternative rock band formed in 2006 in new brunswick , new jersey by brian fallon , alex rosamilia and alex levine . fallon is the singer and plays the rhythm guitar , alex rosamilia plays the lead guitar and backing vocals and benny horowitz plays the drums .
edgard varèse ( born la côte-st-andré , france , 22 december 1883 ; died new orleans , 6 november 1965 ) was a french composer . he was one of the greatest composers of the 20th century . he was an important influence on other 20th century composers such as mozart , beethoven , mozart and tchaikovsky .

john allen astin ( born march 30 , 1930 ) is an american movie , television , stage , and voice actor . he is known for his role as gomez addams in `` the addams family '' .astin was born on march 30 , 1930 in los angeles , california . he studied at the university of california , los angeles . astin was married to patty duke from 1954 until they divorced in 1969 . then he was married to joan astin from 1970 until they divorced in 1979 . then he was married to patricia duke from 1980 until they divorced in 1990 . then he was married to joan astin from 1992 until they divorced in 1993 . he has a son , sean astin .
palm beach is a town in the u.s. state of florida . it is in palm beach county .
the toronto streetcar system is a network of ten streetcar routes in toronto , ontario , canada . it is operated by the toronto transit commission ( ttc ) . it is the third busiest light rail system in north america . much of the streetcar route network dates from the 19th century . most of toronto 's streetcar routes operate on street trackage shared with vehicular traffic . streetcars stop on demand at frequent stops like buses.toronto 's streetcars provide most of the downtown core surface transit service . four of the ttc 's five most used surface routes are surface routes . in 2011 , ridership on the streetcar system totalled over 165 million .
belgian chocolate ( , ) is chocolate made in belgium . it is a major industry since the 19th century , and today is an important part of the nation 's economy and culture.the raw materials used in chocolate production do not originate from belgium . most cocoa is produced in africa , central america , and south america . the country has an association with the product that dates to the early 17th century . the industry expanded massively in the 19th century , getting an international reputation . it became one of the commodity 's most important producers in europe . although the industry has been regulated by law since 1894 , there is no universal standard for the chocolate to be labelled `` belgian '' . the most commonly accepted standard dictates that the actual production of the chocolate must take place in belgium .
arctic monkeys are an english rock band from sheffield.the band was formed in 2002 . the members are alex turner ( lead vocals , guitar , keyboards ) , jamie cook ( guitar , keyboards ) , nick o'malley ( bass guitar , backing vocals ) , matt helders ( drums , backing vocals ) , and jamie cook ( guitar , keyboards ) . they have released four studio albums , `` whatever people say i am , that 's what i 'm not '' ( 2006 ) , `` favourite worst nightmare '' ( 2007 ) , `` humbug '' ( 2009 ) , `` suck it and see '' ( 2011 ) , and `` am '' ( 2013 ) .
matthew tyler oakley ( born march 22 , 1989 ) is an american youtuber , actor , activist and author . oakley 's work has been dedicated to lgbt rights , lgbt rights , and social issues including health care , education , and the prevention of suicide among lgbt youth . oakley regularly posts material on various topics , including queer politics , pop culture and humor .
the winter war was a war between the soviet union ( ussr ) and finland . it began with a soviet invasion of finland on 30 november 1939 , three months after the outbreak of world war ii . it ended three and a half months later with the moscow peace treaty on 13 march 1940 . the league of nations said that the attack was illegal and expelled the soviet union from the organisation.the soviets made several demands . these included the protection of leningrad from the finnish border . when finland refused , the ussr invaded . most sources conclude that the soviet union had intended to conquer all of finland . they also made the molotov-ribbentrop pact 's secret protocols as evidence of this . other sources argue against the idea of the full soviet conquest.hostilities ended in march 1941 with the signing of the moscow peace treaty . finland ceded 11 % of its territory , representing 30 percent of its economy , to the soviet union .
stoke on tern is a village in shropshire , england . it is on the river tern . the civil parish is called stoke upon tern .
jacob tremblay ( ; born october 5 , 2006 ) is a canadian actor . he is known for his starring role as jack newsome in `` room '' ( 2015 ) . he won the critics ' choice movie award for best young performer and the canadian screen award for best actor.in 2017 , he starred as august pullman , a child with treacher collins syndrome , in the drama `` wonder '' , and in 2019 he headlined the r-rated comedy movie `` good boys '' .
dr. hannibal lecter is a fictional character in a series of suspense novels by thomas harris . he is a respected baltimore forensic psychiatrist , as well as a cannibalistic serial killer . after he is caught and incarcerated for his crimes , he consults with the fbi to help them in finding other serial killers.lecter was introduced in the 1981 thriller novel `` red dragon '' . the novel and its 1988 sequel , `` the silence of the lambs '' , feature lecter as one of the main enemies . in the third novel , `` hannibal '' ( 1999 ) , lecter becomes a protagonist . his role as the antihero occurs in the fourth novel , `` hannibal rising '' ( 2006 ) , which explores his childhood and development into a serial killer.the first movie adapted from the harris novels was `` manhunter '' ( 1986 , based on `` red dragon '' ) , which features brian cox as lecter , spelled `` lecktor '' .anthony hopkins won an academy award for his portrayal of the character in `` the silence of the lambs '' ( 1991 ) . he would reprise the role in `` hannibal '' in 2001 and in a second adaptation of `` red dragon '' made in 2002 under the original title.the most recent movie adapted from the harris novels is `` hannibal rising '' ( 2007 ) , in which lecter is played by gaspard ulliel . harris himself wrote the screenplay for this movie.the nbc television series `` hannibal '' debuted in 2013 , and focuses on the development of the relationship between lecter and will graham , an fbi profiler . in the series , lecter is played by danish actor mads mikkelsen , who won a saturn award for his performance.in 2003 , hannibal lecter ( as played by hopkins ) was chosen by the american film institute as the greatest villain in american cinema . in june 2010 , `` entertainment weekly '' named him one of the 100 greatest characters of the last 20 years .
the cook , the thief , his wife & her lover is a 1989 american crime drama movie directed by peter greenaway and starring richard bohringer , michael gambon , helen mirren , alan howard . it was distributed by 20th century fox .
the president of the senate of spain is the speaker of the spanish senate , the upper house of spain 's cortes generales.the current office was established by the 1978 constitution , however , the position has a tradition of almost 200 years , since its creation in 1834 when it was called president of the house of peers.as of the 14th term of the cortes generales , the current officeholder is pilar llop , a member of the socialist parliamentary group representing madrid .
robert budd dwyer ( november 21 , 1939 – january 22 , 1987 ) was an american politician . he served as state treasurer of the commonwealth of pennsylvania . he served from 1965 to 1971 as a republican member of the pennsylvania house of representatives and from 1971 to 1981 as a member of the pennsylvania state senate representing the state 's 50th district. dwyer then served as the 30th treasurer of pennsylvania from january 20 , 1981 , to january 22 , 1987 , when he committed suicide during a live press conference.in 1986 , dwyer was found guilty on 11 counts of conspiracy , mail fraud , perjury , and interstate transportation in aid of racketeering , and was scheduled to be sentenced on january 23 , 1987 . on january 22 , dwyer called a news conference in the pennsylvania state capital of harrisburg where he fatally shot himself with a .357 magnum revolver in front of reporters . dwyer 's suicide was broadcast later that day to a wide television audience.throughout dwyer 's trial and after his conviction , dwyer maintained that he was not guilty of the charges for which he was convicted , and that his conviction resulted from political persecution .
miikka sakari kiprusoff ( born october 26 , 1976 in vantaa , finland ) is a professional finnish ice hockey goaltender . he currently plays for the san jose sharks of the national hockey league ( nhl ) . he has also played for the calgary flames and the san jose sharks .
in the history of christianity , docetism ( from the `` dokeĩn '' `` to seem '' , `` dókēsis '' `` apparition , phantom '' ) is the claim that the phenomenon of jesus , his historical and bodily existence , and above all the human form of jesus , was mere semblance without any true reality . broadly it is taken as the belief that jesus only seemed to be human , and that his human form was an illusion.the word `` dokētaí '' ( `` illusionists '' ) referring to early groups who denied jesus ' humanity , first occurred in a letter by bishop serapion of antioch ( 197–203 ) , who discovered the doctrine in the gospel of peter , during a pastoral visit to a christian community using it in rhosus , and later condemned it as a forgery . it appears to have arisen over theological contentions concerning the meaning , figurative or literal , of a sentence from the gospel of john : `` the word was made flesh '' .docetism was unequivocally rejected at the first council of nicaea in 325 and is regarded as heretical by the catholic church , eastern orthodox church , coptic orthodox church of alexandria and the orthodox tewahedo , and many protestant denominations that accept and hold to the statements of these early church councils .
kossuth is a village in alcorn county , mississippi , united states . the population was 209 at the 2010 census .
ventura , officially the city of san buenaventura , is the county seat of ventura county , california .
uncle tom 's cabin ; or , life among the lowly is a novel written by harriet beecher stowe . it was published in 1852 by macmillan . it is said to have `` helped lay the groundwork for the civil war '' . the book is about slavery in the united states . `` uncle tom 's cabin '' was the best-selling novel of the 19th century . it was published after 1855 . it helped fuel the abolitionist cause in the 1850s .
patrick layton paulsen ( july 6 , 1927 – april 24 , 1997 ) was an american comedian and satirist . he was known for his roles on several of the smothers brothers television shows , and for his satirical campaigns for president of the united states between 1968 and 1996.paulsen was born on july 6 , 1927 in new york city , new york . he was raised in brooklyn , new york . paulsen studied at brooklyn college . paulsen was never married and had no children . paulsen died on april 24 , 1997 in new york city from a heart attack , aged 77 .
le plantay is a commune . it is found in the region auvergne-rhône-alpes in the ain department in the east of france .
charles leonard kunz ( august 18 , 1896 – march 16 , 1958 ) was an american-born british musician popular during the british dance band era . he became a pianist.kunz was born in new york city , new york on august 18 , 1896 . he was raised in london , england . kunz died on march 16 , 1958 in london , england from unknown causes , aged 73 .
the list of atlantic hurricanes in the 18th century includes all known atlantic tropical cyclones from 1700 to 1799 . although not all of the data for every storm that occurred are available , some parts of the coastline were populated enough to give data of hurricane occurrences .
the 1917–18 nhl season was the first season of the national hockey league ( nhl ) . the league was formed after the suspension of the national hockey association ( nha ) . play was held in two halves , december 19 to february 4 , and february 6 to march 6 . the canadiens won the first half , and toronto the second half . the montreal wanderers withdrew early in january 1918 after their rink , the westmount arena , burned down . toronto won the nhl playoff and then won the stanley cup by defeating the pcha 's vancouver millionaires three games to two in a best-of-five series .
chris mcnally ( born april 5 , 1988 ) is an american politician . he is the u.s. representative for . mcnally was elected in the 2018 general election . he is a member of the republican party . mcnally was born in los angeles , california .
a cytotoxic t cell ( also known as t , cytotoxic t lymphocyte , ctl , t-killer cell , cytolytic t cell , cd8+ t-cell or killer t cell ) is a t lymphocyte ( a type of white blood cell ) which kills cancer cells , cells that are infected ( particularly with viruses ) , or cells that are damaged in other ways.most cytotoxic t cells express t-cell receptors ( tcrs ) that can recognize a specific antigen . an antigen is a molecule capable of stimulating an immune response and is often produced by cancer cells or viruses.antigens inside a cell are bound to class i mhc molecules , and brought to the surface of the cell by the class i mhc molecule , where they can be recognized by the t cell . if the tcr is specific for that antigen , it binds to the complex of the class i mhc molecule and the antigen , and the t cell destroys the cell.in order for the tcr to bind to the class i mhc molecule , the former must be accompanied by a glycoprotein called cd8 , which binds to the constant portion of the class i mhc molecule . because of this , these t cells are called cd8+ t cells.the affinity between cd8 and the mhc molecule keeps the t cell and the target cell bound closely together during antigen-specific activation . cd8+ t cells are recognized as t cells once they become activated and are generally classified as having a pre-defined cytotoxic role within the immune system . however , cd8+ t cells also have the ability to make some cytokines .
songs in a minor is the first studio album by american singer-songwriter alicia keys . it was released on june 5 , 2001 by j records . despite its title `` jane doe '' is the only song on the album actually in the key of a minor . `` songs in a minor '' debuted at number one on the `` billboard '' 200 chart . keys did her first headlining concert tour , entitled the songs in a minor tour .
23rd street is a station on the bmt broadway line of the new york city subway . located at the intersection of 23rd street , broadway , and fifth avenue in the flatiron district of manhattan.it is served by the r , w and w trains.behind the station is times square.this station is for r , q and w trains.after this station , the next stations will be 57th street 23rd street and times square 23rd street .
paktika ( ) is one of the thirty-four provinces of afghanistan . it is in the eastern part of the country . there are about 413,800 people . the capital is sharana .
taiwan is a mountainous island of taiwan . the island has the largest number and density of high mountains in the world . there are 286 mountain summits over above sea level on the island , with yushan ( jade mountain - in chinese ) being the tallest mountain in both taiwan and east asia . mountaineering is one of the most popular activities for many taiwanese climbers . a list of 100 peaks of taiwan was made in 1971 , which lists the one hundred mountains over 3,000 m for mountaineering on the island .
samiuela ʻakilisi pōhiva ( 7 april 1941 – 12 september 2019 ) was a tongan pro-democracy activist and politician . pohiva , the leader of the democratic party of the friendly islands ( dpfi ) . he was the prime minister of tonga from 2014 until his death in 2019 . he was born in tonga.pōhiva died on 12 september 2019 at a hospital in paris from problems caused by diabetes , aged 78 .
barry michael boughner ( born january 29 , 1948 in delhi , ontario ) is a canadian former professional ice hockey left winger . he played 20 national hockey league games with the oakland seals/california golden seals between 1969 and 1971 , going scoreless with 11 penalty minutes . he also played in the minor leagues , retiring in 1975.boughner served as head coach for the niagara falls flyers of the ontario hockey association for a portion of the 1979–80 season .
stephen lewis ( 17 december 1926 – 12 august 2015 ) , credited early in his career as stephen cato , was an english actor , comedian , director , screenwriter and playwright . he was best known for his roles as inspector cyril `` blakey '' blake `` on the buses '' , clem `` smiler '' hemmingway in `` last of the summer wine '' , and harry lambert in `` oh , doctor beeching ! `` , although he also appeared in many stage and movie roles.lewis died on 12 august 2015 at the age of 88 .
belen ( ; ) is the second most populous city in valencia county , new mexico , united states , after its county seat , los lunas . the population was 7,269 at the 2010 census .
in chemistry , a leaving group is a molecular fragment that departs with a pair of electrons in heterolytic bond cleavage . leaving groups can be anions , cations or neutral molecules , but in either case it is crucial that the leaving group be able to stabilize the additional electron density that results from bond heterolysis.common anionic leaving groups are halides such as cl , br , and i , and sulfonate esters such as tosylate ( tso ) . fluoride ( f ) is a leaving group in the nerve agent sarin gas.common neutral molecule leaving groups are water and ammonia . leaving groups may also be positively charged cations ( such as h released during the nitration of benzene ) ; these are also known specifically as electrofuges .
the secretary of state for business , energy and industrial strategy is a cabinet member of the british cabinet . it is the head of the department for business , energy and industrial strategy . it is most commonly known as the business secretary . alok sharma is the current secretary of state for business , energy and industrial strategy since february 2020 .
alfred lothar wegener ( 1 november 1880 – 1 november 1930 ) was a german polar researcher and geophysicist . he was born in freiburg , germany.wegener was known for his achievements in meteorology and as a pioneer of polar research , but today he is most remembered as the originator of the theory of continental drift by hypothesizing in 1912 that the continents are slowly drifting around the earth.his hypothesis was controversial and widely rejected by mainstream geology until the 1950s , when numerous discoveries such as palaeomagnetism provided strong support for continental drift , and hence a substantial basis for today 's model of plate tectonics . wegener was involved in several expeditions to greenland to study polar air circulation before the existence of the jet stream was accepted . expedition participants made many meteorological observations , and were the first to overwinter on the inland greenland ice sheet and the first to bore ice cores on a moving arctic glacier.wegener died on november 1 , 1930 at the age of 73 .
saint-girons-d'aiguevives is a commune . it is found in the region aquitaine in the gironde department in the southwest of france .
mia amor mottley ( born 1 october 1965 ) is a barbadian politician and attorney . she is the 8th prime minister of barbados since 2018 . she is also the leader of the barbados labour party ( blp ) . mottley is the eighth person to hold the position of prime minister in barbados . she is also the first woman to hold this position .

ballao ( `` ballàna '' ) is a town and `` comune '' ( municipality ) in the province of sud sardegna in sardinia , italy . as of 2016 , 4,570 people lived there . its area is 56.23 km² . it is 5 meters above sea level .
annie up is the second studio album by american country group pistol annies . the album was released on september 13 , 2003 .
northport is a historic maritime village on the north shore of long island , new york . it was originally designated great cow harbour by 17th-century english colonists . the area was officially renamed northport in 1837 . as of 2010 , the village has a population of around 7,401 .
the volta river is a river in west africa . it flows south into ghana from the bobo-dioulasso highlands of burkina faso . the main part of the river are the black volta , the white volta , and the red volta . in the northwest , the black volta forms the international borders between the ivory coast , ghana , and burkina faso . the volta flows southward along akwapim-togoland highlands , and it empties into the atlantic ocean at the gulf of guinea at ada foah . it has a smaller tributary river , the oti , which enters ghana from togo in the east .
nadine gordimer ( 20 november 1923 – 13 july 2014 ) was a south african writer , political activist and recipient of the 1991 nobel prize in literature . she was recognized as a woman `` who through her magnificent epic writing has – in the words of alfred nobel – been of very great benefit to humanity '' .
togiola talalelei tulafono ( born february 28 , 1947 ) is an american samoan politician . he was the 56th governor of american samoa . he is a member of the democratic party.tulafono was lieutenant governor when , on march 26 , 2003 , governor tauese pita fiti sunia died . he then became acting governor and officially became governor on april 7 , 2003 . he was elected to a full 4-year term in the november 2004 gubernatorial elections and was re-elected in the november 2008 gubernatorial election.tulafono did not run for governor in 2012 as he was term-limited and could not seek a third consecutive term .
eusébio da silva ferreira ( ; 25 january 1942 – 5 january 2014 ) was a portuguese football player . he played for portugal national team and the portugal national team.eusébio was known for his speed , technique , athleticism and his ferocious right-footed shot . he is considered by many as one of the greatest footballers of all time .

baked beans is a food made from white beans which are parboiled and then baked at a low temperature for a long time in some sort of sauce . this is the usual preparation of the dish in the united states when not using canned beans . in the united kingdom the dish is sometimes baked , but usually stewed in a sauce . canned baked beans are not baked , but are cooked through a steam process .
caliban is the second biggest moon of uranus . it was found on september 6 , 1997 by brett j. gladman , philip d. nicholson , joseph a. burns , and john j. kavelaars using the 200-inch hale telescope together with sycorax and given the designation s/1997 u 1.designated uranus xvi , it was named after the monster character in william shakespeare 's play `` the tempest '' .
ellen o'kane tauscher ( november 15 , 1951 – april 29 , 2019 ) was an american politician . she was a member of the democratic party . she was the u.s. representative for california 's 10th congressional district from 1997 until her resignation in 2009 upon joining the state department , where she served as the under secretary of state for arms control and international security affairs until february 2012 . she then served as special envoy for strategic stability and missile defense at the state department until august 31 , 2012.she was the vice-chairwoman of the democratic leadership council from 2001 to 2005.after leaving the state department , she became a number of publicly held corporate and non-profit board positions , including serving on the boards of edison international/southern california edison ( eix ) in rosemead , california , and ehealth ( ehth ) in mountain view , california .
the hazel dormouse or common dormouse ( `` muscardinus avellanarius '' ) is a small mammal and the only living species in the genus muscardinus .
sisseln is a municipality of the district of laufenburg in the canton of aargau in switzerland .
the volvo s60 is a car produced by volvo from 2000 to 2009 . it is available as a hatchback or estate . it is built on the volvo p2 platform . the second generation was produced from 2000 to 2010 and had a facelift in 2010 .
automation is the use of control systems to shift machinery , processes in factories , boilers and heat treating ovens , switching on telephone networks , steering and stabilization of ships , aircraft and vehicles with less human help.automation covers applications ranging from a thermostat controlling a boiler , to a large industrial control system with tens of thousands of input measurements and control signals . in control complexity it can range from simple on-off control to multi-variable high-level algorithms .
charles cecil ( born 11 august 1962 ) is a british video game designer and co-founder of revolution software.cecil is currently managing director of revolution and managing director of game republic .
