in a musical composition , a chord progression or harmonic progression is a succession of chords . chord progressions are the foundation of harmony in western musical music . they are the foundation of western popular music styles ( e.g. , pop music , rock music ) and traditional music ( e.g. , blues and jazz ) . in these genres , chord progressions are the defining feature on which melody and rhythm are built. chord progressions have the function of establishing or contradicting a tonality , the technical name for what is commonly understood as the `` key '' of a song or piece . chord progressions are usually expressed by roman numerals in classical music theory . for example , the common chord progression i-vi-ii-v.in many styles of popular and traditional music , chord progressions are expressed using the name and `` quality '' of the chords . for example , the previously mentioned chord progression , in the key of c major , would be written as c major-a minor-d minor-g major in a fake book or lead sheet . in the first chord , c major , the `` c '' indicates that the chord is built on the root note `` c '' , and the word `` major '' indicates that a major chord is built on this `` c '' note.rock and blues musicians also often refer to chord progressions using roman numerals . this makes transposing a song to a new key . for example , rock and blues musicians often think of the 12-bar blues as consisting of i , iv , and v chords . so , a simple version of the 12-bar blues might be expressed as i-i-i-i , iv-iv-i-i , v-iv-i-i . by thinking of this blues progression in roman numerals , a backup band or rhythm section could be asked by a bandleader to play the chord progression in any key of c major , or if the bandleader asked the bandleader to play this chord progression in the key of c-c–c–c–c , f-f–c , g-f–c–c–c–c . if the bandleader wanted the song in g major , the chords would be g-g-g–g , c-c–g–g–g , d-c–g–g–g. and so on.some pop and rock songs from the 1980s to the 2010s have fairly simple chord progressions . funk emphasizes the groove and rhythm as the key element , so entire funk songs may be based on one chord . some punk and hardcore punk songs use only a few chords . on the other hand , bebop jazz songs may have 32-bar song forms with one or two chord changes every bar .
jatxou is a commune of the pyrénées-atlantiques `` département '' in the southwestern part of france .
lake titicaca is a large , deep , freshwater lake in the andes . it is on the border of bolivia and peru . it is often called the `` highest navigable lake '' in the world . it is the largest lake in south america .
merenschwand is a municipality of the district muri in the canton of aargau in switzerland.the municipality of benzenschwil merged on 1 january 2012 into merenschwand .
curt stern ( august 30 , 1902 – october 23 , 1981 ) was a german-born american geneticist . he was born in hamburg , germany.stern won the wolf prize in medicine in 1980 and the nobel prize in physiology or medicine in 1990.stern died on october 23 , 1981 in new york city from a heart attack , aged 85 .
lorscheid is a municipality in the trier-saarburg district , in rhineland-palatinate , germany . as of 31 december 2018 , 956 people lived there .

karpathos is an island of greece . it is the second largest of the dodecanese islands . it is in the southeastern part of the aegean sea . it is surrounded by the smaller island saria .
edward charles `` shy '' meyer ( born december 11 , 1928 ) is a retired united states army general . he served as the 29th chief of staff of the united states army from 1981 through 1985 .
robert gibson ( born november 9 , 1935 ) is a former pitcher in major league baseball . he played for the st. louis cardinals from 1959 to 1975 . he was nicknamed `` gibby '' and `` hoot '' ( after actor hoot gibson ) .gibson wrote an autobiography , `` pitch by pitch '' , with lonnie wheeler .
the denisovans ( or denisova hominins ) are an extinct species or subspecies of the archaic human that lived in asia during the middle and middle paleolithic ( possibly surviving as late as 30,000–14,500 years ago in new guinea ) . denisovans are known from few remains , and most of what is known about them comes from dna evidence . there have been many different species discovered . `` homo denisova '' , `` h. altaiensis '' , or `` h. sapiens denisova '' is a relative of the neanderthal man.the first denisovan individual was identified in 2010 based on mitochondrial dna ( mtdna ) from a juvenile female finger bone from siberian denisova cave . nuclear dna ( ndna ) indicates close affinities with neanderthals . the cave was also periodically inhabited by neanderthals , but is unclear whether they ever cohabited in the cave. additional specimens from denisova cave were later discovered , as was a single specimen from the baishiya karst cave on the tibetan plateau in china . this indicates they lived in a wide variety of habitats , including forests , tundras , mountains and jungles . dna evidence suggests they had dark skin , eyes , and hair , and had a neanderthal-like build and facial features . however , they had larger molars which are somewhat like middle to late pleistocene archaic humans and australopithecines.denisovans apparently interbred with modern humans , with about 3–5 % of the dna of melanesians and aboriginal australians and around 6 % in papuans deriving from denisovans . denisovans may have interbred with modern humans in new guinea as recently as 15,000 years ago . there is also evidence of interbreeding with the local neanderthal population , with about 17 % of the denisovan genome from denisova cave deriving from them . a first generation hybrid nicknamed `` denny '' was discovered with a denisovan father and a neanderthal mother . 4 % of the denisovan genome comes from an unknown archaic human species which diverged from modern humans over one million years ago .
ragnar arthur granit ( 30 october 1900 – 12 march 1991 ) was a finnish-swedish scientist who was awarded the nobel prize in physiology or medicine in 1967 along with haldan keffer hartline and george wald `` for their discoveries concerning the primary physiological and chemical visual processes in the eye '' .
questacon - the national science and technology centre , is on the southern shore of lake burley griffin in canberra , australia . it is a large centre with more than 200 interactive exhibits relating to science and technology . it has many science programs that are devoted to inspiring the children of australia to love science .
sir peter neville luard pears ( 22 june 1912 – 3 april 1986 ) was an english tenor . his career was closely associated with the composer benjamin britten , his personal and professional partner for nearly forty years.pears ' musical career started slowly . he was at first unsure whether to concentrate on playing or singing . he met britten in 1937 . he threw himself whole into singing.once he met britten , pears wrote many concert and operatic works with pears 's voice in mind . the singer played roles in more than ten operas by his britten . in the concert hall , pears and britten were celebrated recitalists , known in particular for their performances of lieder by schubert and schumann . together they recorded most of the works written for pears by britten , as well as a wide range of music by other composers . working with other musicians , pears sang an extensive repertoire of music from four centuries , from the tudor period to the most modern times.with britten , pears was a co-founder of the aldeburgh festival in 1947 and the britten-pears school in 1972 . after britten died in 1976 , pears remained an active participant in the festival and the school , where he was director of singing . his voice had a distinctive timbre , not to all tastes , however he could use his voice very well in singing many musical styles .
edgar lawrence doctorow ( january 6 , 1931 – july 21 , 2015 ) was an american novelist , editor , and professor . he was best known for his works of historical fiction . he has been described as one of the most important american novelists of the 20th century.he wrote twelve novels , three volumes of short fiction and a stage drama . he is known for his award-winning novels `` ragtime '' ( 1975 ) , `` billy bathgate '' ( 1989 ) , and `` the march '' ( 2005 ) .
 mayweather ( april 24 , 1961 – march 17 , 2020 ) was an american boxing trainer and professional boxer . he competed from 1981 to 1999 . he was a two-weight world champion , having held the wba and lineal super featherweight titles from 1983 to 1984 , and the wbc light welterweight title from 1987 to 1989 . additionally he held the ibo light welterweight title in 1994 , and the ibo welterweight title from 1994 to 1995.mayweather was born in grand rapids , michigan . he was a part of the mayweather boxing family : his brothers are floyd mayweather sr. and jeff mayweather , and his nephew is floyd mayweather jr.mayweather jr. was his trainer from 2000 to 2012 . he was one of the biggest names in the sport of boxing.on march 17 , 2020 , mayweather died of a heart attack at the age of 58 .
the arrondissement of nancy is an arrondissement of france , in the meurthe-et-moselle department , grand est region . its capital is the city of nancy .
ivan john clark ( born 1 november 1932 ) is an english actor , director , producer and writer . clark is probably best known for his role as just william in theatre and radio in the late 1940s and as the former husband of actress lynn redgrave.he is known for his roles in `` a better place '' at dublin 's gate theatre ( 1973 ) , `` the two of us '' ( 1975 ) , `` saint joan '' ( 1977–78 ) , and a tour of `` california suite '' ( 1976 ) .in 1981 , he co-directed the cbs television series `` house calls '' , which redgrave starred in alongside wayne rogers.in 1993–94 clark produced and directed the one-woman play , `` shakespeare for my father '' .
the yellow-lipped sea krait ( `` laticauda colubrina '' ) , also known as the banded sea krait , is a species of venomous sea snake found in tropical oceanic waters . the snake has distinctive black stripes and a yellow snout , with a paddle-like tail for use in swimming.it spends much of its time underwater in order for it to hunt . it then returns to land to digest , rest , and reproduce . it has a neurotoxic venom which it uses to prey on eels and small fish . because of its affinity to land , yellow-lipped sea kraits often encounter humans , but the snakes are not aggressive and only attack when feeling threatened .
loriol-du-comtat is a commune . it is found in the region provence-alpes-côte d'azur in the vaucluse department in the south of france .
conrad gessner ( march 26 , 1516 – december 13 , 1565 ) was a swiss physician , naturalist , bibliographer , and philologist . he was born in zürich , switzerland . he is regarded as the father of modern scientific bibliography , zoology and botany . he was the first to describe a species of plant or animal in europe .
bc place is a sports stadium in vancouver , british columbia , canada . it is the home of the vancouver whitecaps of major league soccer and the bc lions of the canadian football league . it is also the home of bc pavilion corporation , a crown corporation of the province.the stadium was built in 1983 as an indoor structure with an air-supported roof . it was the largest of its kind in the world when it was opened . after the 2010 winter olympics , bc place was closed for 16 months . this was part of a big revitalization of the stadium . it was replacing the inflatable roof with a retractable roof supported by cables . once it was completed , the stadium 's new roof was also the largest of its type .
the independent is a british newspaper . it was started in 1986 as a national morning printed newspaper published in london . it began as a broadsheet and changed to tabloid format in 2003 . the last printed edition was published on saturday 26 march 2016 , leaving only the online edition.the newspaper was owned by tony o'reilly 's irish independent news & media from 1997 until it was sold in 2010 .
freightliner trucks is an american truck manufacturer . it was founded in 1929 as the truck-manufacturing division of consolidated freightways . the company was established in 1942 as freightliner corporation.freightliner produces a range of vans , medium-duty trucks , and heavy-duty trucks . under its freightliner custom chassis subsidiary , the company produces bare chassis and cutaway chassis for multiple types of vehicles . the company popularized the use of cabover ( coe ) semitractors . the freightliner argosy later became the final example of the type sold in north america.the company is headquartered in portland , oregon . vehicles are currently manufactured in cleveland and mount holly , north carolina .
beauty and the beast : the enchanted christmas is a 1997 direct-to-video animated disney direct-to-video movie . it is a sequel to the 1991 disney animated movie `` beauty and the beast '' . the movie sold 7.6million vhs tapes in 1997 . this is the first of two followups to `` beauty and the beast '' that were released , with the other being `` belle 's magical world '' ( 1998 ) .
hornick is a city in iowa in the united states . it is in woodbury county .
charmes-sur-rhône is a commune in the ardèche `` département '' in southern france .
ramona is a town in the southeastern part of the u.s. state of south dakota . it is located in lake county , and 174 people lived there at the 2010 census . ramona became a town in 1881 .
lakeside is a census designated place ( cdp ) in san diego county , california . the population was 20,648 at the 2010 census .

lubumbashi ( former names : ( french ) and ( dutch ) ) is a city in the southeastern part of the democratic republic of the congo and is the second-largest in the country , the largest being the capital , kinshasa .
a sideboard , also called a buffet , is an item of furniture . it is used in the dining room for serving food , for displaying serving dishes , and for storage . it usually consists of a set of cabinets , or cupboards , and one or more drawers , all topped by a wooden surface for holding food , serving dishes , or lighting devices . the words `` sideboard '' and `` buffet '' are somewhat interchangeable . if the item has short legs , or a base that sits directly on the floor with no legs , it is more likely to be called a `` sideboard '' ; if it has longer legs it is more likely to be called a `` buffet '' .the earliest versions of the sideboard familiar today made their appearance in the 18th century , but they gained most of their popularity during the 19th century as households became wealthy enough to dedicate a room solely to dining.sideboards were made in a range of decorative styles and were decorated with costly veneers and inlays . in later years , sideboards have been placed in living rooms or other areas where household items might be displayed.the custom sideboard was first introduced in the united states during the american revolution . it was a decorative item , designed to look like a single piece of wood . however , modern versions from the late 18th or early 19th centuries are the most sought-after and most costly . some of the earliest production of sideboards arose in england , france , poland , belgium and scotland . later , american designs arose . characteristic materials used in historic sideboard manufacture include mahogany , oak , pine , and walnut .
martijn gerard garritsen ( ) , professionally known as martin garrix , is a dutch dj and record producer from amstelveen . his most known singles are `` animals '' , `` in the name of love '' and `` scared to be lonely '' . he was ranked number one on dj mag 's top 100 djs list for three consecutive years ( 2016 , 2017 , and 2018 ) .he has performed at music festivals such as coachella , electric daisy carnival , ultra music festival , tomorrowland , and creamfields . in 2014 he headlined the 1st edition of ultra south africa making this his first major festival . in the same year he became the youngest dj to headline 2014 ultra music festival at the age of 17 . he was a resident dj at spain 's hï ibiza ( 2017 ) and ushuaïa ibiza ( 2016 and 2018 ) . he founded the label stmpd rcrds in 2016 , months after leaving spinnin 's records and before signing with sony music .
kenneth lee wregget ( born march 25 , 1964 ) is a canadian retired professional ice hockey goaltender . wregget won the stanley cup in 1992 with the pittsburgh penguins .
teays valley is a census-designated place ( cdp ) in putnam county , west virginia , united states . as of the 2010 census , the msa had a population of 287,702 .
aberdeen is a city in the southeastern part of the u.s. state of south dakota . it is the county seat of brown county , and 26,091 people lived there at the 2010 census . aberdeen is the third largest city in south dakota , after sioux falls and rapid city . aberdeen is also considered a college town , because it is the home of northern state university and presentation college .
laura jeanne reese witherspoon ( born march 22 , 1976 ) is an american actress . she was born in new orleans , louisiana and raised in nashville , tennessee . she played elle woods in `` legally blonde '' ( 2001 ) . she also played june carter cash in the musical movie `` walk the line '' ( 2005 ) . she won an academy award for best actress for her role in `` walk the line '' ( 2005 ) .witherspoon won a golden globe award for best actress for her role in `` walk the line '' ( 2005 ) . she also won a screen actors guild award for best actress for her role in the movie `` water for elephants '' ( 2011 ) .witherspoon produced and stars in the hbo drama series `` big little lies '' ( 2017–present ) . she also co-founded the production company type a films . witherspoon won a primetime emmy award for outstanding limited series in 2019.witherspoon also owns a clothing company called draper james . she is currently chair of the children 's defense fund ( cdf ) . she was named global ambassador of avon products in 2007.witherspoon co-founded the production company type a films in 2000 . the company has since merged with hello sunshine , a media firm which witherspoon also co-founded .
the abdomen , or `` tummy '' , is the part of the body between the thorax and pelvis . it is sometimes also called the stomach or midriff.the abdomen is the front part of the abdominal segment of the trunk . the area occupied by the abdomen is called the abdominal cavity . in some animals , it is the back part of the body .
anicadu is a village in pathanamthitta district , kerala state , india .
siobhán emma donaghy ( born 14 june 1984 ) is an english singer-songwriter . she is a founding member of the girl group sugababes . donaghy left the sugababes in 2001 and released her debut solo album , `` revolution in me '' , on 23 september 2003 . her second studio album , `` ghosts '' , was released on 25 june 2007.on 20 july 2012 , donaghy and her former sugababes colleagues , buena and buchanan , confirmed their reunion . the original trio were not able to release music under the name `` sugababes '' as it was still owned by the management company . they instead released music under the new name , mutya keisha siobhan .
eleanor of provence ( c. 1223 – 25 june 1291 ) was a french noblewoman . she was the wife of henry iii of england . she was queen consort from 1236 until his death in 1272 . she was regent of england from 1253 until 1253.eleanor was born in provence , france . she had nine children . edward i of england was her first king.eleanor died on 25 june 1291 in london , england from breast cancer , aged 59 .
networking hardware , also known as network equipment or computer networking devices , are electronic devices which are required for communication and interaction between devices on a computer network . specifically , they mediate data transmission in a computer network . units which are the last receiver or generate data are called hosts , end systems or data terminal equipment .
walk with me is the third studio album by british singer jamelia . it was released by emi controlled parlophone records in september 2006 . the album contains the singles `` something about you '' , `` beware of the dog '' and `` no more '' .
a cooperative is an association of people who share their common economic , social , and cultural needs . they want to do this through a jointly-owned enterprise.this may include : research by the worldwatch institute found that in 2012 about one billion people in 96 countries had become members of at least one cooperative . the turnover of the largest three hundred cooperatives in the world reached $ 2.2 trillion.cooperative businesses are usually more economically resilient than many other forms of enterprise . twice the number of co-operatives ( 80 % ) surviving their first five years compared with other business models ( 41 % ) . cooperatives often have social goals . they aim to do this by investing a proportion of trading profits back to their communities . for example , retail co-operatives in the uk invested 6.9 % of their pre-tax profits in the communities in which they trade as compared with 2.4 % for other rival supermarkets.since 2002 cooperatives have been different on the internet through the use of a .coop domain .
sarosh homi kapadia ( 29 september 1947 – 4 january 2016 ) was an indian politician and lawyer . he was the thirty-eighth chief justice of india from 30 november 1993 until 4 january 2016 . kapadia was born in hyderabad , british india.kapadia died on 4 january 2016 at a hospital in hyderabad after a long-illness , aged 68 .
the blockade runners of the american civil war were steam ships that were used to get through the union blockade that extended some along the atlantic and gulf of mexico coastlines and the lower mississippi river . the confederate states were largely without industrial capability and could not provide the quantity of arms and other supplies needed to fight against the industrial north . blockade runners built in scotland and england met this need and imported guns , ordnance and other supplies that the confederacy desperately needed . to get through the blockade , these ships , built in british ship yards and specially designed for speed , had to cruise undetected , usually at night , through the union blockade . the typical blockade runners were privately owned vessels often operating with a letter of marque issued by the confederate states of america . if spotted , the blockade runners would attempt to outmaneuver or simply outrun any union ships on blockade patrol , very often successfully.these vessels also carried cargoes to and from neutral ports , often in nassau and cuba . neutral merchant ships in turn carried these cargoes , usually coming from or destined to england or other points abroad . outbound ships chiefly exported cotton , tobacco and other goods for trade and revenue . while also carrying important mail and correspondence to suppliers and other interested parties in europe , most often in england . inbound ships usually brought badly needed supplies and mail to the confederacy , and most of the guns and other ordnance of the confederacy were imported from england via blockade runners . some blockade runners made many successful runs , while many others were either captured or destroyed . historians estimated that an estimated 2,500–2,800 attempts were made to run the blockade , with at least an 80 % success rate . by the end of the civil war , the union navy had captured more than 1,100 blockade runners and had destroyed or run aground another 355 ships .
cranbrook is a city in the canadian province of british columbia . cranbrook is on the west side of the kootenay river at its confluence with the st. mary 's river . it is the largest city in the region known as the east kootenay . cranbrook had 19,259 people living there in 2011 .
the swedish bandy association ( ) is the governing body of bandy in sweden . it organizes the bandy leagues , elitserien and allsvenskan for men and damallsvenskan for women , and the men 's and women 's national teams . it was established in stockholm on 5 april 1925 . it is based in stockholm , and moved from katrineholm . it is a founding member of fib , federation of international bandy.bandy was introduced 1895 in sweden by all round athlete clarence von rosen . he picked the game up during a visit in bandy 's home country great britain . he started the first bandy club in sweden , stockholm hockeyklubb . first in 1905 bandy was organized within swedish ballgame association and a year later within swedish football association . at a meeting april 5 , 1925 , the swedish bandy association was formed representing 49 clubs.since 1931 , the swedish bandy association regularly arranges national leagues in sweden . swedish bandy champions is a title held by the winners of the final . the final is played in march .
leonardo wilhelm dicaprio ( born november 11 , 1974 ) is an american actor . he was born in los angeles , california and is of italian descent . he has starred in many movies , including `` titanic '' ( 1997 ) , `` the departed '' ( 2006 ) , `` revolutionary road '' ( 2008 ) , `` inception '' ( 2010 ) , `` django unchained '' ( 2012 ) , `` the departed '' ( 2006 ) , `` blood diamond '' ( 2006 ) , `` the revenant '' ( 2006 ) , `` revolutionary road '' ( 2008 ) , `` inception '' ( 2010 ) , `` django unchained '' ( 2012 ) , `` the wolf of wall street '' ( 2013 ) and `` once upon a time in hollywood '' ( 2019 ) . he won an academy award for best original screenplay for the remake of `` once upon a time in hollywood '' ( 2019 ) .
a hippie ( sometimes spelled hippy ) is a 1960s american counterculture . it began in the united states during the mid-1960s , and spread to other countries around the world . the word `` hippie '' came from `` hipster '' , and was used to describe beatniks who moved to new york city 's greenwich village and san francisco 's haight-ashbury district . the term `` hippie '' first found popularity in san francisco with herb caen , who was a journalist for the `` san francisco chronicle '' .in 1967 , the human be-in in golden gate park , san francisco , and monterey pop festival popularized hippie culture , leading to the summer of love on the west coast of the united states , and the 1969 woodstock festival on the east coast.hippies created their own communities , listened to psychedelic music , embraced the sexual revolution , and used drugs such as marijuana and lsd to explore altered states of consciousness . in the united kingdom in 1970 , many gathered at the gigantic isle of wight festival with around 400,000 people , and in later years , mobile `` peace convoys '' of new age travelers made summer pilgrimages to free music festivals at stonehenge and elsewhere . in australia , hippies gathered at nimbin for the 1973 aquarius festival and the annual cannabis law reform rally or mardigrass . `` piedra roja '' festival was held in chile , was held in 1970 . hippie and psychedelic culture influenced 1960s and early 1970s youth culture in iron curtain countries in eastern europe .
launay-villiers is a commune of 574 people ( 1999 ) . it is found in the region pays de la loire in the mayenne department in the northwest of france .
gerald alan freedman ( june 25 , 1927 – march 17 , 2020 ) was an american theatre director , librettist , and lyricist . he was born in new york city . he was a college dean . freedman was known for directing the 1978 version of `` pretty baby '' . he also directed the 1979 movie `` pretty baby '' .f freedman died on march 17 , 2020 in new york city at the age of 93 .
`` take this waltz '' is a song by canadian singer-songwriter leonard cohen , originally released as part of the 1986 federico garcía lorca tribute album `` poets in new york '' and as a single.the song was later included in cohen 's 1988 studio album `` i 'm your man '' , in a slightly re-arranged version ( with addition of violin and jennifer warnes 's duet vocals , both absent from the 1986 version ) .the song 's lyrics are a loose translation , into english , of the poem `` pequeño vals vienés '' ( little viennese waltz ) by the spanish poet federico garcía lorca ( one of cohen 's favorite poets ) . the poem was first published in lorca 's seminal book `` poeta en nueva york '' .the song reached number one in spain in 1986 .
cher is a department in the centre-val de loire region of france in the centre-val de loire region . it is named after the cher river , a tributary of the nouvelle-aquitaine river.its prefecture is laon .
lari michele white cannon ( ; may 13 , 1965 – january 23 , 2018 ) was an american country music singer and actress . she was born in knoxville , tennessee.white first became known in 1988 as a winner on `` you can be a star '' , a talent competition which aired on the nashville network . a recording contract with rca records nashville followed a year later , producing three studio albums , a greatest hits package , and several chart singles , with three of her singles having reached top ten : `` that 's my baby '' and `` that 's how you know ( when you 're in love ) '' at no . 10 , and `` now i know '' at no . 5.a fourth studio album was released in 1998 on lyric street records , followed by two more releases on her own label , skinny white girl. overall , white charted twelve times on the `` billboard '' country music charts.white was also married to nashville-based songwriter chuck cannon until her death in january 2018 .
kfum örebro is an ymca association in örebro in sweden . it was established in 1890 . the club won the swedish women 's juniors national volleyball championship in 1990 . between 1996-2001 the club won the swedish national women 's volleyball championship . the men 's floorball team played in the swedish top division during the 1990 's .
beth hart ( born january 24 , 1972 ) is an american singer-songwriter and musician . she is best known for her 1999 single `` screamin ' for my supper '' . her first album `` live in amsterdam '' was released in 1999.hart was born in los angeles , california .
the 1992 republican national convention was held in the astrodome in houston , texas , from august 17 to august 20 , 1992 . the convention nominated president george h. w. bush and vice president dan quayle for reelection.it was bush 's fourth consecutive appearance as a candidate on a major party ticket ; only bush and franklin d. roosevelt have been nominated on four presidential tickets . richard m. nixon and roosevelt have been nominated five times , but not consecutively .
 the battle of valverde was a battle of the american civil war . it was fought on february 20 to february 21 , 1862 .
linköpings aik is a sports club in the town of linköping in sweden . it was established on 22 october 1908 . the club runs orienteering . it earlier even ran bandy and soccer . the men 's bandy team played in the swedish top division in 1931. the men 's soccer team played in the swedish third division during the seasons of 1928-1929 and 1929-1930 .
this article contains the results of the 2016 republican presidential primaries and caucuses . it is the process by which the republican party selected delegates to attend the 2016 republican national convention from july 18-21.a simple majority ( 1,237 ) of the total delegate votes ( 2,472 ) was required to become the party 's nominee . the nominee was donald trump of new york.the process began on march 23 , 2015 , when texas senator ted cruz became the first presidential candidate to announce his intentions to seek the office of united states president . that summer , 17 major candidates were recognized by national and state polls . it is the largest presidential candidate field for any single political party in american history.the large field made possible the fact that the 2016 primaries were the first since 1968 ( and the first in which every state won at least one state ) in which more than three candidates won at least one state.when voting began in the 2016 iowa caucuses , twelve major candidates were being considered . these included former governor mike huckabee of arkansas , former senator rick santorum of pennsylvania , governor chris christie of new jersey , businesswoman and former hewlett-packard chief executive officer carly fiorina , former governor jim gilmore of virginia , governor jeb bush of florida , former neurosurgeon and johns hopkins university director of pediatric neurosurgery ben carson , senator marco rubio of florida , senator ted cruz of texas , governor john kasich of ohio , and businessman and ceo donald trump of new york.after poor results from the first-in-the-nation caucus , ben carson dropped out of the race , santorum also ended his campaign after a poor performance in iowa , and subsequently polling poorly leading into the new hampshire primary . christie , who put nearly all of his campaign 's resources into the critical state of new hampshire , withdrew on february 10 , 2016 after finishing sixth in the state . following christie 's announcement , fiorina suspended her campaign , which was unable to gain traction . gilmore , who severely lacked funding , campaign infrastructure , and support , surprised many political journalists by staying in the race as far as he did ; he dropped out shortly after the new hampshire primary . after super tuesday , carson announced that there would be `` no path forward '' for his bid for the presidency , effectively ending his campaign . on march 15 , 2016 , rubio dropped out from the race , leaving three active candidates ( cruz , kasich , and trump ) . trump 's resounding victory in the indiana primary on may 3 , 2016 , prompted cruz 's exit from the race . the following day , trump became the presumptive republican nominee after kasich dropped out . trump was formally nominated by the delegates of the 2016 republican national convention on july 19 , 2016 , and started the general election on november 19 , 2016 , to defeat democratic nominee hillary clinton in the general election on november 8 , 2016 , to become the 45th president of the united states .
eddie thomson ( 25 february 1947 – 21 february 2003 ) was a scottish football player and coach . he played as a defender for heart of midlothian and aberdeen in scotland , san antonio thunder in the united states and sydney city in australia . he also coached sydney city and sydney olympic before working with the australia national team .
john william finn ( july 24 , 1909 – may 27 , 2010 ) was a united states navy sailor . he received the medal of honor which is the united states military 's highest decoration . he received it for his actions during the attack on pearl harbor in world war ii . as a chief aviation ordnanceman stationed at naval air station kaneohe bay he earned the medal by manning a machine gun from an exposed position throughout the attack , despite being repeatedly wounded.he continued to serve in the navy and in 1942 was commissioned an ensign . in 1947 he was reverted to chief petty officer , eventually rising to lieutenant before his 1956 retirement . in his later years he made many appearances at events celebrating veterans . at the time of his death , finn was the oldest living medal of honor recipient , the last living recipient from the attack on pearl harbor , and the last united states navy recipient of world war ii .
nuclear weapons testing , uranium mining and export , and nuclear power have often been the subject of public debate in australia , and the anti-nuclear movement in australia has a long history . its origins date back to the 1972–73 debate over french nuclear testing in the pacific and the 1976–77 debate about uranium mining in australia.several groups concerned with nuclear issues were established in the mid-1970s , including the movement against uranium mining and campaign against nuclear energy ( cane ) , friends of the earth and the australian conservation foundation . the movement suffered a setback in 1983 when the newly elected labor government failed to implement its stated policy of stopping uranium mining . by the late 1980s , the price of uranium had fallen , the costs of nuclear power had risen , and the anti-nuclear movement seemed to have won its case ; cane was disbanded in 1988.about 2003 , proponents of nuclear power advocated it as a solution to global warming and the australian government began taking an interest . anti-nuclear campaigners and some scientists in australia argued that nuclear power could not significantly substitute for other power sources , and that uranium mining itself could become a significant source of greenhouse gas emissions.as of 2015 , australia has no nuclear power stations and five uranium mines , four of which are in south australia .
the satanic bible is a book by anton lavey . it was published in 1969 . it was the first book to talk about satanism , and is thought to be the foundation of his philosophy and dogma.the book is made of four books : the book of satan , the book of lucifer , the book of the book of belial , and the book of the book of leviathan . `` the satanic bible '' does not contain the same keys as in the christian bible , so it is not thought to be sacred to christianity . however , laveyan satanists consider it as an authoritative text . it is a contemporary text that has attained the virtues of exploring one 's own nature and instincts. believers have been described as `` atheistic satanists '' because they believe that god is not an external entity . instead , something that each person creates is a projection of their own personality—a benevolent and stabilizing force in their life.there have been thirty printings of `` the satanic bible '' , selling over a million copies .

 biggers ( william watts biggers ; june 2 , 1927 – february 10 , 2013 ) was an american novelist and co-creator of the long-running animated television series `` underdog '' .biggers was born on june 2 , 1927 in new york city , new york . he studied at williams college . biggers died on february 10 , 2013 in his home in los angeles , california from natural causes , aged 86 .

glasgow central station ( ) is one of two main rail terminals in glasgow , scotland . the station was opened by the caledonian railway on 1 august 1879 and is one of 20 managed by network rail.it is the northern terminus of the west coast main line ( north of london euston ) , and for inter-city services between glasgow and england . the other main station in the centre of the city is .
 aerogel is a porous porous substance that is derived from a gel and has been replaced with a gas . the result is a solid with extremely low density and very low thermal conductivity . nicknames include `` frozen smoke '' , `` solid smoke '' , `` solid air '' , `` solid cloud '' and `` blue smoke '' because of its translucent nature and the way light scatters in the material.aerogels were first created by samuel stephens kistler in 1931 , as a result of a bet with charles learned over who could replace the liquid in `` jellies '' with gas without causing shrinkage . aerogels are produced by getting the liquid component of a gel through supercritical drying . this allows the liquid to be slowly dried off . this allows the solid matrix in the gel to collapse from capillary action , as would happen with conventional evaporation.the first aerogels were produced from silica gels . kistler 's later work involved aerogels based on alumina , chromia and tin dioxide . carbon aerogels were first developed in the late 1980s.aerogels are not a single material with a set chemical formula ; instead , the term is used to group all materials with a certain geometric structure .
poilly-sur-tholon is a commune . it is found in the yonne department in the center of france .
james albert smith leach ( born october 15 , 1942 ) is an american academic and former politician . he served as ninth chair of the national endowment for the humanities from 2009 to 2013 . he was a member of the u.s. house of representatives from iowa from 1977 to 2007 . leach lost his 2006 re-election bid to democrat dave loebsack .
marsing is a city in idaho in the united states . it is in owyhee county .
the autism rights movement , also known as the autistic culture movement or the neurodiversity movement , is a social movement that emphasizes a neurodiversity model . it says that the autism spectrum should be accepted as a natural expression of the human genome , rather than a `` disease '' to be cured.autistic rights or neurodiversity advocates believe that the autism spectrum should be accepted as a natural expression of the human genome , and accommodated like any other condition ( the social model of disability ) . this perspective is different from two other views : the medical perspective , that autism is caused by a genetic defect and should be addressed by targeting the autism gene ( s ) , and fringe theories that autism is caused by environmental factors such as vaccines .
cor is a city in iowa in the united states .
a birthday cake is a cake that is eaten on a birthday . it is usually layer cakes with frosting and is served with small lit candles on top . the cake is usually decorated with birthday wishes and the name of the person making the cake .
touchstone pictures is an american movie distribution label owned by walt disney studios motion pictures . it was established on february 15 , 1984 , by then-disney ceo ron w. miller as touchstone films . touchstone operated as an active movie production division of walt disney studios during the 1980s through the early 2010s . most of the company 's pg-13 and r-rated movies were released under the touchstone label . in 2009 , disney entered into a five-year , thirty picture distribution deal with dreamworks pictures by which dreamworks would be released through the touchstone banner .

jennifer coolidge ( born august 28 , 1961 ) is an american movie , television , stage , voice actress and comedian . she is known for her roles in `` american pie '' , `` cinderella story '' , `` best in show '' , `` for your consideration '' and in `` mascots '' .coolidge was born on august 28 , 1961 in chicago , illinois . she studied at northwestern university . coolidge was married to jim carter until they divorced in 2000 . they had two children . coolidge now lives in los angeles , california .
ralph herrick andrews ( december 17 , 1927 – october 16 , 2015 ) was an american television producer . he was best known for producing the 1960s game show `` you do n't say ! `` , the 1970s game show `` celebrity sweepstakes '' , and the original 1987 version of `` lingo '' . andrews was born in chicago , illinois.andrews died on october 16 , 2015 in santa monica , california at the age of 88 .
asma jilani jahangir ( ; 27 january 1952 – 11 february 2018 ) was a pakistani human rights lawyer and social activist . she was born in lahore , pakistan . she co-founded and chaired the human rights commission of pakistan . jahangir was known for playing a prominent role in the lawyers ' movement and served as the united nations special rapporteur on freedom of religion or belief and as a trustee at the international crisis group .
the british rail class 201 ( or 6s ) six-car diesel-electric multiple units ( demus ) were built from 1957-1958 at eastleigh railway works and underframes were built at ashford.the southern region class 201-207 demus are nicknamed 'thumpers ' because of the noise they made while in motion , due to the four cylinder engines.these units were built for the london-hastings line , with a narrow body profile to accommodate the restricted tunnel loading gauge on that line .
de graff is a city in swift county , minnesota , united states . the population was 115 at the 2010 census .
titan a.e . is a 2000 american animated science fiction adventure movie directed by don bluth and gary goldman and starring the voices of matt damon , bill pullman , drew barrymore , john leguizamo , nathan lane , janeane garofalo , ron perlman and tone loc . its title refers to the spacecraft central to the plot with `` a.e . '' meaning `` after earth '' . the animation of the movie combines 2d traditional hand-drawn animation with the use of computer-generated imagery .
gene barry ( eugene klass , june 14 , 1919 – december 9 , 2009 ) was an american stage , movie , and television actor . he was known for his roles in `` bat masterson '' and in `` burke 's law '' . he won a tony award.barry was born on june 14 , 1919 in new york city , new york . he was raised in new york city , new york . barry studied at the actors studio . barry was married to dorothy lee from 1945 until they divorced in 1949 . then he was married to carol barry from 1949 until his death in 2009 . he had four children . barry died on december 9 , 2009 in los angeles , california from heart failure , aged 92 .
edinburgh trams is a tramway in edinburgh , scotland . it is a line between york place in the new town and edinburgh airport , with 16 stops . construction began in june 2008 . it opened on 31 may 2014 .
quarten is a municipality in sarganserland in the canton of st. gallen in switzerland . it is above lake walensee .
chartres is a commune in france , the prefecture of the eure-et-loir department . it is in the nouvelle-aquitaine region . it is also the capital of the `` arrondissement '' of chartres and of the `` arrondissement '' of chartres .
in aesthetics , the uncanny valley is a hypothesis that an object looks like a human being . the hypothesis says that if an observer looks at an object like a human , will feel emotional reactions related to that object . the hypothesis is that it is possible that the person who looks like a human will feel a felt emotion related to looking at the human .
david h. levy ( born may 22 , 1948 ) is a canadian amateur astronomer , science writer and discoverer of comets and minor planets . he co-discovered comet shoemaker-levy 9 in 1993 , which collided with the planet jupiter in 1994 .
andre agassi ( born april 29 , 1970 ) is an american retired tennis player . he was born in las vegas , nevada . he was once ranked number 1 in the world . he is known as `` the punisher '' because of two bulging discs in his back that interfered with the nerve in his knees.agassi won the 1996 summer olympics . he was known as `` the punisher '' because he was nicknamed `` the punisher '' by the fans . he retired from professional tennis in 2006 because of sciatica . he is married to tennis player steffi graf.when agassi was growing up , he had spondylolisthesis ( vertebral displacement ) and a bone spur that interfered with the nerve in his back .
lothar matthäus ( born 21 march 1961 ) is a former german football player . he has played for west germany national team .
ellen tyne daly ( born february 21 , 1946 ) is an american actress . she is best known for playing detective mary beth lacey in `` cagney & lacey '' and alice henderson in `` christy '' . she won an emmy award in 1996 for her role in `` judging amy '' .daly was born in brooklyn , new york .
karl-josef rauber ( born 11 april 1934 ) is a french cardinal of the catholic church . he served as a papal nuncio from 1982 until his retirement in 2009 . rauber was born in boulogne-billancourt , france . rauber was ordained a roman catholic priest in 1953 . he was elevated to the cardinalate by pope john paul ii in 1979 .
jörg stübner ( 23 july 1965 – 24 june 2019 ) was a german football player . he played for east germany national team .
a choco pie is a korean snack cake . it is made of two small round layers of cake with marshmallow filling and a chocolate covering .
roebuck `` pops '' staples ( december 28 , 1914 – december 19 , 2000 ) was an american gospel and r & b musician . he was an `` pivotal figure in gospel in the 1960s and 1970s , '' he was an accomplished songwriter , guitarist and singer . he was the patriarch and member of singing group the staple singers , which included his son pervis and daughters mavis , yvonne , and cleotha .
stevie wonder live is a 1970 live album by american singer-songwriter stevie wonder on the tamla label . it was his second live collection . it was released during the crossroads of wonder 's career as he was preparing to negotiate a new contract with motown that gave him artistic control over his work.the m.c . heard on the recording is veteran detroit dj scott regen , who can also be heard on `` temptations live ! '' and `` four tops live ! `` .
hargicourt is a former commune . it is in the region picardie in the somme department in the north of france . on 1 january 2019 , it was merged into the new commune of trois-rivières .
the kea ( `` nestor notabilis '' ) is a species of large parrot in the nestoridae family.the kea is known for their intelligence and curiosity , both vital to their survival in a harsh mountain environment . kea can solve logical puzzles , such as pushing and pulling things in a certain order to get to food , and will work together to achieve a certain objective . they have been filmed preparing and using tools.the kea nests in burrows or crevices among the roots of trees . they are known for their intelligence and curiosity , both vital to their survival in a harsh mountain environment .
göran per-eric `` pelle '' lindbergh ( may 24 , 1959 – november 11 , 1985 ) was a swedish professional ice hockey goaltender who played parts of five seasons in the national hockey league ( nhl ) for the philadelphia flyers . lindbergh died at age 26 in a single-car accident five months after leading the flyers to the 1985 stanley cup finals and winning the vezina trophy as the nhl 's top goaltender .
connerré is a commune . it is found in the region pays de la loire in the sarthe department in the west of france .
urost is a commune of the pyrénées-atlantiques `` département '' in the southwestern part of france .
university of dhaka ( ) is the oldest university in bangladesh . it was established in 1921 . nawab sir khwaja salimullah played a pioneering role in establishing the university in dhaka . he gave 600 acres of land from his estate for this purpose . on the first day of july 1921 the university of dhaka opened its doors to students with sir p.j . hartog as the first vice-chancellor of the university . it has made significant contributions to the modern history of bangladesh.after the partition of india , it became the focal point of progressive and democratic movements in pakistan . its students and teachers played a central role in the rise of bengali nationalism and the independence of bangladesh in 1971 .
year 1059 ( mlix ) was a common year starting on friday ( link will display the full calendar ) of the julian calendar .
dwight lyman moody ( february 5 , 1837 – december 22 , 1899 ) was an american evangelist . he was connected with the holiness movement . he founded the moody church , northfield school and mount hermon school in massachusetts ( now northfield mount hermon school ) , moody bible institute and moody publishers . one of his most famous quotes was “faith makes all things possible ... love makes all things easy .” he gave up his lucrative boot and shoe business to devote his life to revivalism , working first in the civil war with union troops through ymca in the united states christian commission . in chicago , he built one of the major evangelical centers in the nation , which is still active . working with singer ira sankey , he toured the country and the british isles , drawing large crowds with a dynamic speaking style that preached god 's love , kindness and forgiveness rather than hellfire and condemnation .
stephanie murphy ( born đặng thị ngọc dung ; september 16 , 1978 ) is an american politician from the state of florida . she is a member of the united states house of representatives for florida 's 7th congressional district since january 3 , 2016.murphy is the first vietnamese-american woman and the second vietnamese-american overall ( after republican joseph cao of louisiana ) to be elected to congress .

sir patrick head ( born 5 june 1946 ) is a former engineering director of the williams formula one team.for 27 years from head was technical director at williams grand prix engineering , and responsible for many innovations within formula one . head oversaw the design and construction of williams cars until may 2004 when his role was handed over to sam michael .
cashion is a town in the u.s. state of oklahoma .
ostafrikasaurus is a genus of spinosaurid theropod dinosaur from the upper jurassic of what is now tanzania . it is known only from fossil teeth discovered sometime between 1909 and 1912 , during an expedition to the tendaguru formation by the natural history museum of berlin . eight teeth were originally thought to be labrosaurus , and later to `` ceratosaurus '' , both known from the north american morrison formation.later studies attributed two of these teeth to a spinosaurid dinosaur , and in 2012 , ostafrikasaurus crassiserratus was named by french palaeontologist eric buffetaut , with one tooth as the holotype , and the other referred to the same species .
denton burn is an area in the west of the city centre of newcastle upon tyne , england . it is a suburb of the city .
manuel `` el loco '' valdés ( born 29 january 1931 ) is a mexican actor and comedian . he is a member of the valdés family . he is the brother of ramón valdés ( a.k.a . `` don ramón '' ) , from the sitcom `` el chavo '' , and germán valdés ( a.k.a . `` tin tan '' ) . he is also the father of singer cristian castro and marcos valdés .
jizya ( ) is a per capita yearly tax imposed on non-muslim subjects ( dhimmi ) of a state governed by islamic law . muslim jurists required adult , free , sane males among the dhimma community to pay the jizya , while exempting women , children , elders , handicapped , the ill , the insane , monks , hermits , slaves , and musta'mins—non-muslim foreigners who only temporarily reside in muslim lands . dhimmis who chose to join military service were also exempted from payment , as were those who could not afford to pay.the quran and hadiths mention jizya without specifying its rate or amount . however , scholars largely agree that early muslim rulers adapted existing systems of taxation and tribute that were established under previous rulers of the conquered lands , such as those of the byzantine and sasanian empires.jizya rate varied in the course of islamic history . together with kharāj , a term that was sometimes used interchangeably with jizya , taxes levied on non-muslim subjects were among the main sources of revenue collected by some islamic polities , such as the ottoman empire and indian muslim sultanates . jizya rate was usually a fixed annual amount depending on the financial capability of the payer . sources comparing taxes ranging from 5 % to 10 % depending on time , place , specific taxes under consideration , and other factors.historically , the jizya tax has been understood in islam as a fee for protection provided by the muslim ruler to non-muslims , for the exemption from military service for non-muslims , for the permission to practice a non-muslim faith with some communal autonomy in a muslim state , and as material proof of the non-muslims ' submission to the muslim state and its laws .
saint-sauveur-en-puisaye is a commune . it is found in the yonne department in the center of france .
baloži is a town in latvia with town rights since 2009 .
 steiger ( april 14 , 1925 – july 9 , 2002 ) was an american actor . he was born in westhampton , new york . he is known for playing sol nazerman in `` the pawnbroker '' and in `` in the heat of the night '' . he won five academy awards during his career.steiger died in los angeles , california from pneumonia , aged 77 .
the roseland peninsula , or just roseland , is a district of west cornwall , united kingdom . it is located in the south of the county and contains the town of st mawes and villages such as st just and gerrans . it is a peninsula , separated from the rest of cornwall by the river fal ( on the east is the english channel ) .

whist is a british trick-taking card game . it was widely played in the 18th and 19th centuries . although the rules are simple , there is scope for scientific play .

zoosemiotics is the study of the use of signs among animals . it was developed by the german-estonian biologist jakob von uexküll . the field is defined by its subject matter all of those semiotic processes that are shared by both animals and humans.the field also interprets signs that are not communicative in the traditional sense , such as camouflage , mimicry , courtship behavior . the field also studies cross-species communication , for example between humans and animals .
bernard herrmann ( born max herman ; june 29 , 1911december 24 , 1975 ) was an american composer . he is best known for his work in composing for motion pictures and for composing the music of lesser-known composers . he was born in new york city.he is known for composing the music for `` psycho '' , `` north by northwest '' , `` the man who knew too much '' , and `` vertigo '' . he also composed for many other movies , including `` citizen kane '' , `` anna and the king of siam '' , `` the day the earth stood still '' , `` the ghost and mrs. muir '' , `` cape fear '' , `` fahrenheit 451 '' , and `` taxi driver '' . he worked extensively in radio drama . he also composed the scores for several fantasy movies by ray harryhausen , and many tv programs , including rod serling 's `` the twilight zone '' and `` have gun – will travel '' .
west crossett is a census-designated place ( cdp ) in the us state of arkansas .
badwater basin is an endorheic basin in death valley national park , death valley , inyo county , california , noted as the lowest point in north america , with a depth of below sea level . mount whitney , the highest point in the contiguous 48 united states , is only to the northwest .
 frederick ii ( 26 december 1194 – 13 december 1250 ) was king of sicily from 1198 , king of germany from 1212 , holy roman emperor from 1220 and king of jerusalem from 1225 . he was the son of henry vi of the hohenstaufen dynasty and of constance , heiress to the norman kings of sicily.frederick was also a claimant to the title of king of the romans from 1212 and unopposed holder of that monarchy from 1215 . as such , he was king of germany , of italy , and of burgundy.at the age of three , frederick was crowned king of sicily as a co-ruler with his mother , constance of hauteville , the daughter of roger ii of sicily . his other royal title was king of jerusalem by marriage and his connection with the sixth crusade .
suseok ( 수석 ) , also called viewing stones or scholar 's stones , is the korean term for small naturally occurring or shaped stones . `` suseok '' can be any color . they vary widely in size – `` suseok '' can weigh hundreds of kilograms or much less than one kilogram . the term also refers to the stones which are placed in traditional korean gardens .
hypsilophodon ( meaning `` hypsilophus '' -tooth ) is an ornithischian dinosaur from the lower cretaceous of england and romania . it has traditionally been considered an early member of the group ornithopoda , but recent research has put this into question.the first remains of `` hypsilophodon '' were found in 1849 ; the type species , `` hypsilophodon foxii '' , was named in 1869 . abundant fossil discoveries were made on the isle of wight , giving a good impression of the build of the species . it was a small bipedal animal with an herbivorous or possibly omnivorous diet . `` hypsilophodon '' reached up to in length , weighed about 20 kg ( 45 lbs ) , and was an agile runner . it had a pointed head with a sharp beak used to bite off plant material , much like modern day parrots.older studies have given rise to number of misconceptions about `` hypsilophodon '' : that it would climb trees , that its name means `` high-rided tooth '' , was armoured , reached a length of , and was also found outside wight . during the past decades new research has gradually shown this to be incorrect .
baghdad ( ) is the capital city of iraq . it is also the third largest city in the arab world after cairo and riyadh . it is on the tigris river . it was founded in the 8th century and became the capital of the abbasid caliphate of baghdad . the city was largely destroyed by the mongol empire in 1258 . baghdad was a major center of arabic culture .
saulius sondeckis ( 11 october 1928 – 3 february 2016 ) was a lithuanian violinist , conductor , orchestra leader and professor . he founded the lithuanian chamber orchestra in 1960 and was its artistic director and principal conductor until 2004 . he was born in kaunas , lithuania.sondeckis died in kaunas on 3 february 2016 . he was aged 87 .
clark county is a county located in the u.s. state of south dakota . as of the 2010 census , 3,691 people lived there . its county seat is clark . it was created in 1873 .
elder love brewster ( ) was an early american settler . he was the son of elder william brewster and his wife , mary brewster . he traveled with his father , mother and brother , wrestling , on the `` mayflower '' reaching what became the plymouth colony in massachusetts in 1620 . brewster had two sisters , patience and fear , and two brothers , jonathan and wrestling , along with an unnamed sister who died young . he was a founder of the town of bridgewater , plymouth county , massachusetts .
glynis johns ( born 5 october 1923 ) is a south african-british actress , dancer , pianist , and singer . she is best known for creating the role of desiree armfeldt in `` a little night music '' on broadway , for which she won a tony award , and for playing winifred banks in walt disney 's musical motion picture `` mary poppins . '' she sang songs written specifically for her , including `` send in the clowns '' , composed by stephen sondheim , and `` sister suffragette '' , written by the sherman brothers.she was nominated for an oscar for her work in the 1960 movie `` the sundowners '' .
maxwell trowbridge gail jr. ( born april 5 , 1943 ) is an american actor . he is best known for his role as detective stan `` wojo '' wojciehowicz on the sitcom `` barney miller '' ( 1975–1982 ) .
ball lightning is an unexplained event that is said to last longer than a split-second flash of a lightning bolt . ball lightning is usually seen during thunderstorms , though it can also be seen during thunderstorms . it is believed to happen in many countries , but no one knows if it is real . it has been claimed to happen many times since the 17th century . however , no one ever knows if it has ever happened.ball lightning has been recorded in things as far back as the 13th century . before that , people thought that ball lightning was seen in the sky . however , no one ever knows if it really happened .
 the biceps is a muscle on the upper arm between the shoulder and the elbow . it is used for opening a bottle with a corkscrew : first biceps screws in the cork ( supination ) , then it pulls the cork out .
manuele blasi ( born 17 august 1980 ) is an italian football player . he plays for brescia calcio .
sappho ( c. 630 bc – 570 bc ) was an ancient greek poet from the island of lesbos . she is known for her lyric poetry , written to be sung while accompanied by a lyre . in ancient times , she was widely regarded as one of the greatest lyric poets , and was given names such as the `` tenth muse '' and `` the poetess '' . most of sappho 's poetry is now lost , and what is extant has mostly survived in fragmentary form ; two notable exceptions are the `` ode to aphrodite '' and the tithonus poem.as well as lyric poetry , ancient commentators claimed that sappho wrote elegiac and iambic poetry . three epigrams attributed to sappho are extant , but these are actually hellenistic imitations of sappho 's style.little is known of sappho 's life . she was from a rich family from lesbos , though her parents ' names are uncertain . ancient sources say that she had three brothers ; the names of two of them , charaxos and larichos , are mentioned in the brothers poem discovered in 2014 . she was exiled to sicily around 600 bc , and may have continued to work until around 570 . later legends surrounding sappho 's love for the ferryman phaon and her death are unreliable .
kalawao county is a county in the u.s. state of hawaii . it is the smallest county in the 50 states both by population and land area . the county includes the kalaupapa or makanalua peninsula , on the north coast of the island of molokai .
nikolai ivanovich pankin ( ; 2 january 1949 – 13 october 2018 ) was a russian breaststroke swimmer . he was born in moscow.pankin competed at the 1968 , 1972 and 1976 olympics in the 100 m and 200 m breaststroke and 4 × 100 m medley relay . in 1968 he won a bronze medal in the 100 m and narrowly missed a bronze in the 200 m . pankin was less successful in 1972 and 1976 , and finished close to the podium in the medley relay.at the 1970 and 1974 european championships , pankin won a medal in each of the three events he competed . his last international medal was a bronze in the 200 m breaststroke at the 1975 world championships.pankin died on 13 october 2018 in moscow at the age of 70 .
ketchikan is a city in alaska . about 8,000 people live there . it is the fifth largest city in alaska . it is on revillagigedo island.ketchikan was incorporated on august 25 , 1900 . it is the earliest city in alaska .
tracy s. letts ( born july 4 , 1965 ) is an american actor , playwright , and screenwriter . he won the 2008 pulitzer prize for drama for his play `` '' and a tony award for his portrayal of george in the revival of `` who 's afraid of virginia woolf ? '' ( 2013 ) .he is also known for his role of andrew lockhart in seasons 3 and 4 of showtime 's `` homeland '' , for which he has been nominated for two screen actors guild awards as a member of the ensemble . he played the pyramid-scheme con-artist nick on the hbo comedy `` divorce '' .in 2017 , letts starred in three critically acclaimed movies : `` the lovers '' , `` lady bird '' , and `` the post '' . the latter two movies were nominated for the academy award for best picture ; `` lady bird '' garnered letts a screen actors guild award for outstanding performance by a cast in a motion picture nomination.letts wrote the screenplays of three movies adapted from his own plays : `` bug '' and `` killer joe '' , both directed by william friedkin , and `` '' , directed by john wells.his 2009 play `` superior donuts '' was adapted into a television series of the same name . his first screenplay not to be adapted from his own work , `` the woman in the window '' , based on the 2018 novel of the same name by a. j. finn , is scheduled to be released in 2020 .
clearview is a town in the u.s. state of oklahoma .
owen william paterson ( born 24 june 1956 ) is a british conservative party politician . he was secretary of state for environment , food and rural affairs from 2012 to 2014 . he was first elected as a member of parliament for north shropshire at the 1997 general election.paterson was appointed to the shadow cabinet of david cameron in 2007 as shadow secretary of state for northern ireland , where he remained until being moved to defra in 2012 . he has since been more widely known as a leading supporter of brexit and an outspoken critic of the european union.in 2016 , paterson became part of leave means leave 's political advisory board .
russell ira crowe ( born 7 april 1964 ) is a new zealand-australian actor , movie producer , director and musician . he was born in auckland , new zealand and grew up in sydney , new south wales . he is best known for his roles in movies including `` gladiator '' ( 2000 ) , `` romper stomper '' ( 1992 ) , `` '' ( 1997 ) , `` '' ( 2003 ) , `` cinderella man '' ( 2005 ) , `` '' ( 2006 ) , `` state of play '' ( 2009 ) , `` man of steel '' ( 2013 ) and `` noah '' ( 2014 ) .crowe won a golden globe award for best actor in 1999 and a bafta award for best leading actor in 2001 .

shirley schlanger abrahamson ( born december 17 , 1933 ) is an american associate justice and former chief justice of the wisconsin supreme court.abrahamson was appointed to the court in 1976 by governor patrick lucey , becoming the first female justice to serve on wisconsin 's highest court . abrahamson was reelected in 1979 , 1989 , 1999 , and 2009 . she became the court’s first female chief justice on august 1 , 1996 , and served in that capacity until april 29 , 2015 .

steven donald dalachinsky ( september 29 , 1946 – september 16 , 2019 ) was an american poet . he was born in new york city . dalachinsky was active in the music , art , and free jazz scenes . he wrote poetry for most of his life . he read at michael dorf 's club the knitting factory , the poetry project and the vision festival.dalachinsky also read his works in japan , france and germany . he worked with william parker , susie ibarra , matthew shipp , roy campbell , daniel carter , sabir mateen , jim o'rourke and mat maneridalachinsky.dalachinsky died on september 16 , 2019 in new york city at the age of 73 .
 joe perry ( born september 10 , 1950 ) is an american musician . he is best known as a member of the rock band aerosmith . in 2001 , he was inducted into the rock and roll hall of fame as part of the band.perry was born on september 10 , 1950 in new york city , new york . he was raised in boston , massachusetts . perry studied at boston college . he has been married to carol ann miller since 1975 . they have two children . he now lives in los angeles , california .
the torres strait is a strait between australia and the melanesian island of new guinea . it is approximately wide at its narrowest extent . to the south is cape york peninsula , the northernmost extremity of the australian mainland . to the north is the western province of papua new guinea . it is named after navigator luís vaz de torres , who passed through the strait in 1606 .
roanne is a french commune . it is northwest of lyon on the loire river .
a library classification is a system of knowledge organization by which library resources are arranged and ordered systematically . library classifications use a notational system that represents the order of topics in the classification and allows items to be stored in that order . library classification systems group related materials together , typically arranged as a hierarchical tree structure . a different kind of classification system , called a faceted classification system , is also widely used , which allows the assignment of multiple classifications to an object , allowing the classifications to be ordered in many ways .

earlsboro is a town in the u.s. state of oklahoma .
david longly bernhardt ( born august 17 , 1969 ) is an american politician , attorney , energy industry lobbyist , and government administrator . he is the 53rd and current united states secretary of the interior since august 1 , 2017 . he was the acting united states secretary of the interior from january 2 , 2019 to april 11 , 2019.bernhardt was nominated by president donald trump to be the united states deputy secretary of the interior in april 2017 . he was confirmed by the u.s. senate on july 24 , 2017 , and sworn into office on august 1 , 2017 .
the first inauguration of george washington as the first president of the united states was held on thursday , april 30 , 1789 . it was held on the balcony of federal hall in new york city.the inauguration was the beginning of the first four-year term of george washington as president. chancellor of new york robert livingston gave the oath of office .
the battle of pea ridge ( march 7–8 , 1862 ) was a battle of the american civil war . it was fought near leetown , missouri . the confederates tried to bring back northern arkansas and missouri . curtis held off the confederate attack on the first day . he drove out the confederate forces . the confederates won the battle .
landshut is a city in the south-east of germany . it is on the banks of the river isar and is the capital of the district of lower bavaria .
leon jackson ( born 30 december 1988 ) is a scottish singer . he won the 2007 series of british talent show `` the x factor '' . after he won , he was the main star of his on-web series `` leon 's life '' which ran from 2007 until 2008 .

eldest is the second novel in the `` inheritance cycle '' by christopher paolini and the sequel to `` eragon '' . `` eldest '' was first published in hardcover on august 23 , 2005 , and was released in paperback in september 2006 . `` eldest '' has been released in an audiobook format , and as an ebook .
mogilev region is a voblast ( province ) of belarus . the administrative centre is mogilev . the population of mogilev region was 1,165,000 in 2002 .

oswego county is a county in the u.s. state of new york . as of the 2010 census , 122,109 people lived there . the county seat is oswego .
