all my hits/todos mis éxitos vol . 2 is the sixth compilation album by american tejano singer selena . the album was released after selena died on february 29 , 2000 .
daniel azulay ( may 30 , 1947 – march 27 , 2020 ) was a brazilian visual artist , comic book artist , and educator . he was known for his works in the press and on tv as a draftsman . he was most known for the children 's franchise `` turma do lambe-lambe '' .azulay died on march 27 , 2020 of covid-19 in rio de janeiro , aged 73 .
the sixth sense is a 1999 american psychological thriller movie . it was written and directed by m. night shyamalan . the movie tells the story of cole sear ( haley joel osment ) , a boy who is able to see and talk to the dead . malcolm crowe ( bruce willis ) is a child psychologist who tries to help him.the movie was released by hollywood pictures on august 6 , 1999 . the movie was well-received by critics . praise was given to its acting performances ( willis , osment , and toni collette ) , atmosphere , and twist conclusion . `` the sixth sense '' was the second-highest-grossing movie of 1999 ( behind `` '' ) , taking about $ 293 million in the us and $ 379 million in other markets.the movie was nominated for six academy awards , including best picture , best director and best original screenplay for shyamalan , best supporting actor for osment , and best supporting actress for collette .
richard lynch ( february 12 , 1940 – june 19 , 2012 ) was an american actor . he was known for his roles in `` battlestar galactica '' ( as wolfe ) and its sequel series `` galactica 1980 '' ( as commander xaviar ) . he also appeared in such shows as `` starsky and hutch '' , `` baretta '' , `` t. j. hooker '' , `` blue thunder '' , `` airwolf '' , `` the a-team '' , `` charmed '' and `` '' .lynch was born on february 12 , 1940 in new york city , new york . lynch died on june 19 , 2012 in his home in los angeles , california from unknown causes , aged 73 .
basque is a language that is spoken in the basque country , which is a region in northern spain and southwestern france . linguistically , basque is not a romance language . linguistically , basque is not considered to be part of any other known living language.native speakers of basque live in a large area that includes parts of four spanish provinces and the three `` ancient provinces '' in france . gipuzkoa , most of biscay , a few municipalities of álava and the northern area of navarre formed the core of the remaining basque-speaking area before measures were introduced in the 1980s to strengthen the language.in france and navarre , the basque language was strongly censored during the francoist regime , because it was not allowed to be used in official discourse , education , and publishing . in some provinces , the public use of the language was suppressed , with people fined for speaking basque . overall , in the 1960s and later , education and publishing in basque began to grow .
stardust memories is a 1980 american comedy drama movie directed by woody allen ( who also stars ) and starring charlotte rampling , jessica harper , marie-christine barrault , sharon stone . it was distributed by 20th century fox and was nominated for an academy award in 1980 .
the tribunal of the holy office of the inquisition ( ) , commonly known as the spanish inquisition ( `` inquisición española '' ) , was established in 1478 by catholic monarchs ferdinand ii of aragon and isabella i of castile.the purpose of the inquisition was to maintain catholic orthodoxy in their kingdoms and to replace the medieval inquisition , which was under papal control.the `` spanish inquisition '' may be defined broadly , operating in spain and in all spanish colonies and territories , which included the canary islands , the kingdom of naples , and all spanish possessions in north , central , and south america.according to modern estimates , around 150,000 were prosecuted for various offenses during the three-century duration of the spanish inquisition , out of which between 3,000 and 5,000 were executed ( ~2.7 % of all cases ) .
david norris brenner ( february 4 , 1936 – march 15 , 2014 ) was an american stand-up comedian , actor and author . he was known for hosting `` the tonight show starring johnny carson '' in the 1970s and 1980s . he was known for being observational comedy . he was born in new york city , new york.brenner died from complications of pneumonia on march 15 , 2014 in los angeles , california , aged 78 .
kaysone phomvihane ( ) ( 13 december 1920 – 21 november 1992 ) was a lao politician . he was the first leader of the lao people 's revolutionary party from 1955 until his death in 1992 . he also was the first prime minister of the lao people 's democratic republic from 1975 to 1991 and then as the second president from 1991 to 1992 .
northeastern university ( neu ) is a private research university in boston , massachusetts , established in 1898 . the university offers undergraduate and graduate programs on its main campus in boston.the university has satellite campuses in charlotte , north carolina , seattle , washington , san jose , california , san francisco , california , toronto , vancouver , and portland , maine that exclusively offer graduate degrees .
earl eugene scruggs ( january 6 , 1924 – march 28 , 2012 ) was an american grammy award-winning country music musician . he was known for his three-finger banjo picking style . it is now called `` scruggs style '' . the style of playing changed from the traditional way the five-string banjo had been played . this new style of playing became popular . it made the banjo popular across many genres of music.scruggs was born on january 6 , 1924 in shelby , north carolina . he was raised in shelby , north carolina . scruggs died on march 28 , 2012 in shelby , north carolina from heart failure , aged 88 .
sköldinge is a locality in katrineholm municipality in södermanland county in sweden . in 2010 , 604 people lived there .
year 241 ( ccxli ) was a common year starting on friday of the julian calendar .
yair lapid ( ; born november 5 , 1963 ) is an israeli politician and former journalist . he is the chairman of the yesh atid party and opposition leader in the knesset . he was minister of finance from 2013 to 2014.before entering politics in 2012 , lapid was an author , tv presenter and news anchor . in 2013 , lapid was ranked first on the `` most influential jews in the world '' by `` the jerusalem post '' . he was also recognized in 2013 as one of the leading foreign policy global thinkers , and ranked as one of time magazine 's 100 `` most influential people in the world . thanin kraivichien ( first name also spelled tanin , last name `` kraivixien '' or `` kraivichian '' ; , , ; born 5 april 1927 ) is a thai judge , politician and law professor . he was the prime minister of thailand between 1976 and 1977 . he was a member of the privy council until 2016 .
esther salas ( born december 29 , 1968 ) is an american judge . she is a united states district judge of the united states district court for the district of new jersey sitting in newark , new jersey . she was a united states magistrate judge of the same court from 2006 until her confirmation as a district judge in 2011.salas is the first hispanic woman to serve as a united states magistrate judge and as a united states district judge in the district of new jersey .
sutz-lattrigen is a municipality of the administrative district of biel/bienne in the canton of berne in switzerland.there are many neolithic and bronze age lake shore archeological sites in the area , including one that is part of a unesco world heritage site .
eduardo mac entyre ( 20 february 1929 – 5 may 2014 ) was an argentine artist . he was known for his geometric paintings . his work was first displayed in 1954 at buenos aires ' comte art gallery.mac entyre died in buenos aires , argentina from natural causes , aged 85 .
the oriental longhair is a breed of domestic cat . it is closely related to oriental shorthair . in some registries , such as the international cat association ( tica ) , it is a separate breed . in others , such as the cat fanciers ' association ( cfa ) , it is a division , along with the short-haired variety , of a merged breed , the oriental longhair . there is no globally recognized naming convention , so people may refer to it as foreign longhair or mandarin . it was formerly known as the british angora before being renamed in 2002 by british cat fanciers in order to avoid confusion with the turkish angora .
smilja avramov ( 15 february 1918 – 2 october 2018 ) was a serbian academician , legal scholar , social activist and educator in international law . she was a member of the senate of republika srpska from 1996 to 2009 . before she retired she was a professor of international law at the law faculty at belgrade university.avramov died in belgrade on 2 october 2018 at the age of 100 .
trapani is a city and `` comune '' on the west coast of sicily in italy . it is the capital of the province of trapani.trapani is the main town of the nearby egadi islands .
the english electric lightning is a british fighter aircraft . it was used as an interceptor during the 1960s , the 1970s and into the late 1980s . it is the only uk-designed fighter aircraft capable of mach 2 . the lightning was designed , developed , and manufactured by english electric . english electric later bought the newly-formed british aircraft corporation . later the type was marketed as the bac lightning . it was operated by the royal air force ( raf ) , the kuwait air force ( kaf ) and the royal saudi air force ( rsaf ) .a unique feature of the lightning 's design is the design of its two rolls-royce avon turbojet engines within the fuselage . the lightning was initially designed and developed as an interceptor to defend the v bomber airfields from attack by anticipated nuclear-armed supersonic soviet bombers such as the tupolev tu-22 . it was also needed to intercept other bomber aircraft such as the tupolev tu-16 and the tupolev tu-95.the lightning has exceptional rate of climb , ceiling , and speed . pilots have described flying it as `` being saddled to a skyrocket '' . this performance and the limited fuel supply meant that its missions are dictated to a high degree by its limited range . later developments provided greater range and speed along with aerial reconnaissance and ground-attack capability.following retirement by the raf in the late 1980s , many of the remaining aircraft became museum exhibits .
wallace michael shawn ( born november 12 , 1943 ) is an american character actor , playwright , and essayist . he is known for his roles as mr. james hall in `` clueless '' ( 1995 ) and as grand nagus zek in `` '' .his plays include `` aunt dan and lemon '' ( 1985 ) , `` the designated mourner '' ( 1996 ) and `` grasses of a thousand colors '' ( 2008 ) .he also co-wrote the screenplay for `` my dinner with andre '' with andre gregory , and scripted `` a master builder '' ( 2013 ) , a movie adaptation of the play by henrik ibsen , which he also starred in . his book `` essays '' was published in 2009 by haymarket books .
thomas ellis gibson ( born july 3 , 1962 ) is an american actor and director . he is known for his roles as daniel nyland in the cbs television series `` chicago hope '' ( 1994–2000 ) , greg montgomery in the abc television series `` dharma & greg '' ( 1997–2002 ) and aaron hotchner in the cbs television series `` criminal minds '' ( 2005–2016 ) .
the little carpathians ( also : `` lesser carpathians '' , ; ) are a low , about 100 km long , mountain range . they are in western slovakia , covering the area from bratislava to nové mesto nad váhom , and northeastern austria , where a small part called hundsheimer berge ( or hainburger berge ) is located south of the devín gate.the little carpathians are bordered by záhorie lowland in the west and the danubian lowland in the east . in 1976 , the little carpathians were declared a protected area under the name little carpathians protected landscape area , covering . the area is rich in flora and fauna diversity and has numerous castles , most notably the bratislava castle , and caves . driny is the only cave open to the public . the three highest mountains are záruby at , vysoká at , and vápenná at .
100 tears is a 2007 american independent slasher horror movie directed by marcus koch and produced by joe davison . it follows the story of a circus clown going on a murderous rampage after being wrongfully accused of rape . the movie stars georgia chris , joe davison ( who also produced the movie ) , jack amos , and raine brown , and was distributed by anthum pictures in 2007 . the movie was generally well received by independent horror movie critics and has since garnered a cult following .
the wwe draft is a format used by the american professional wrestling company wwe to put together its roster from the raw and smackdown brands ( 2002–2011 , 2016–present ) . before the draft , the ecw brand also took part in the 2006–2009 wwe brand split until that brand was disbanded in early 2010 . with the second brand split in 2016 , wrestlers from nxt ( 2016–present ) and 205 live ( 2019–present ) are also eligible to be drafted to raw and smackdown.the draft was first used in 2002 . it was called the wwe draft lottery ( 2004–2005 ) and later simply as the `` draft '' ( 2007–2011 ) . in 2011 , wwe ended the brand split . with `` smackdown '' moving to tuesdays and to a live broadcast starting july 19 , 2016 , wwe reintroduced the brand split with a draft held that same episode . from 2017 until may 2019 , the draft was rebranded as the superstar shake-up ; instead of a traditional draft , wrestlers were traded or moved between brands . with `` smackdown '' s move to friday nights on fox beginning october 4 , 2019 , a second draft for the year was scheduled to occur , reverting to its original name ( the `` wwe draft '' ) .
menachem begin ( , `` menaḥem begin '' ) ( 16 august 1913 – 9 march 1992 ) was an israeli politician . he was born in poland and died in israel when he was 73 . he was the leader of the zionist militant group irgun , which broke away from the larger jewish paramilitary organization haganah.begin was elected to the first knesset as head of herut , and was at first on the political fringe . he was against the mapai-led government and israeli establishment . he was in opposition in the eight consecutive elections ( except for a national unity government around the six-day war ) , but became more acceptable to the political center.begin 's most significant achievement as prime minister was the signing of a peace treaty with egypt in 1979 . after the camp david accords , the israel defense forces ( idf ) withdrew from the sinai peninsula , which was captured from egypt in the six-day war . later , begin 's government promoted the construction of israeli settlements in the west bank and the gaza strip .

zozibini tunzi ( born 18 september 1993 ) is a south african model and beauty pageant titleholder . in january 2019 , she was crowned miss universe 2019 . before this , she was crowned miss south africa 2019 . she is the third woman from south africa to win the title , and the first black woman since leila lopes was crowned miss universe 2011 .
fernando álvaro lamas y de santos ( january 9 , 1916 – october 8 , 1982 ) was an argentine-american actor and director . he was the father of actor lorenzo lamas.lamas was born on january 9 , 1916 in buenos aires , argentina . he was raised in los angeles , california . lamas died on october 8 , 1982 from a heart attack in his los angeles , california home , aged 73 .
abdullah bin abdulaziz al saud ( , `` '' ; august 1 , 1924 – january 23 , 2015 ) was king of saudi arabia and custodian of the two holy mosques from the death of his half-brother , king fahd , on august 1 , 2005 , until his own death in january 2015.abdullah died in mecca , saudi arabia from pneumonia , aged 90 .
in baseball , an at bat or time at bat is a batter 's turn batting against a pitcher . an at bat is different from a plate appearance . a batter is credited with a plate appearance regardless of what happens during their turn at bat , but a batter is credited with an at bat only if that plate appearance does not have one of the results enumerated below . while at bats are used to calculate certain statistics , a player can qualify for the season-ending rankings in these categories only if they accumulate 502 plate appearances during the season.a batter will not receive credit for an at bat if their plate appearance ends under these circumstances : in addition , if the inning ends while they are still at bat ( due to the third out being made by a runner caught stealing , for example ) , no at bat or plate appearance will result . in this case , the batter will come to bat again in the next inning , though the count will be reset to no balls and no strikes.rule 9.02 ( a ) ( 1 ) of the official rules of major league baseball defines an at bat as : `` number of times batted , except that no time at bat shall be charged when a player : ( a ) hits a sacrifice bunt or sacrifice fly ; ( b ) is awarded first base on four called balls ; ( c ) is hit by a pitched ball ; or ( d ) is awarded first base because of interference or obstruction [ ] . ''
paktia ( ) is one of the thirty-four provinces of afghanistan . it is in the east of the country . gardez is the capital of paktia .
saint-vincent-des-prés is a commune . it is found in the region pays de la loire in the sarthe department in the west of france .
 moral equivalence is a word used to criticize two sides in a conflict . it is also used to criticize the actions or tactics of the two sides . `` moral equivalence '' began to be used as a term for moral relativism . it was an indictment against political foreign policy that appeared to use only a situation-based application of widely held ethical standards.international conflicts are sometimes viewed similarly . interested parties asked both parties to conduct a ceasefire and negotiate their differences . however , these negotiations may prove difficult in that both parties in a conflict believe that they are morally superior to the other , and are unwilling to negotiate on basis of moral equivalence .
`` do n't go away '' is a song by the rock band oasis . it was released from their third album `` be here now '' . it was written by noel gallagher . `` do n't go away '' reached number 35 on the `` billboard '' hot 100 airplay chart and number 15 on the canadian `` rpm '' top singles chart in late 1997 . it was the band 's last major hit in the united states .
a community is a group of living things with commonality such as norms , religion , values , customs , or identity . communities may share a sense of place situated in a given geographical area ( e.g . a country , village , town , or neighbourhood ) or in virtual space . durable relations that extend beyond immediate genealogical ties also define a sense of community , important to their identity , practice , and roles in social institutions such as family , home , work , government , society , or humanity at large.although communities are usually small relative to personal social ties , `` community '' may also refer to large group affiliations such as national communities , international communities , and virtual communities.the english-language word `` community '' derives from the old french `` comuneté '' , which comes from the latin `` communitas '' `` community '' , `` public spirit '' ( from latin `` communis '' , `` common '' ) .
the bonnot gang ( `` la bande à bonnot '' ) was a french criminal anarchist group that operated in france and belgium during the `` belle époque '' , from 1911 to 1912 . they were made up of people who identified with the emerging illegalist `` milieu '' . the gang used cutting-edge technology ( including automobiles and repeating rifles ) not available to the french police.originally referred to by the press as simply `` the auto bandits '' , the gang was dubbed `` the bonnot gang '' after jules bonnot gave an interview at the office of `` le petit parisien '' , a popular daily paper . bonnot 's prominence within the group was later reinforced by his high-profile death during a shootout with french police in choisy-le-roi .
james anthony redden jr. ( march 13 , 1929 – march 31 , 2020 ) was an american judge and politician . he was born in portland , oregon . he was a senior united states district judge of the united states district court for the district of oregon , from 1995 to 2020 . he was a federal judge since 1980.redden jr. died on march 31 , 2020 in portland at the age of 91 .
hawaii is the largest island in the u.s. state of hawaii . it is in the southeastern part of the hawaiian islands , a chain of volcanic islands in the north pacific ocean.hawaiʻi is the largest island in the state and in the united states . it is the county seat of hawaiʻi county . there are no incorporated cities in hawaiʻi county .
take it home is the third studio album by american singer-songwriter ariana grande . the album was released on june 27 , 2010 . the album was produced by ariana grande and ryan tedder . the album peaked at number one on the `` billboard '' 200 , number two on the canadian hot 100 , and number three on the uk albums chart .
chandra bahadur dangi ( 30 november 1939 – 3 september 2015 ) was a nepali man . he was the shortest man in recorded history . dangi was a primordial dwarf . he broke the record of gul mohammed ( 1957–1997 ) , whose height was .
the northern goshawk ( `` accipiter gentilis '' ) is a medium-large raptor in the family accipitridae , which also includes other raptors , such as eagles , buzzards and harriers.the goshawk is a widespread species that lives in many of the temperate parts of the northern hemisphere . the northern goshawk is the only species in the genus `` accipiter '' found in both eurasia and north america . it may have the second widest distribution of any true member of the family accipitridae , behind arguably only the golden eagle ( `` aquila chrysaetos '' ) , which has a broader range to the south of asia than the goshawk . the only other acciptrid species to also range in both north america and eurasia according to current opinion , is the more arctic-restricted rough-legged buzzard ( `` buteo lagopus '' ) .
laigné is a former commune of 246 people ( 1999 ) . it is found in the region pays de la loire in the mayenne department in the northwest of france . on 1 january 2018 , it was merged into the new commune of prée-d'anjou .
skippy the bush kangaroo is an australian television series . it was created by australian actor john mccallum , lionel ( bob ) austin and lee robinson . it was produced from 1967 to 1969 . it is about the adventures of a young boy and his pet kangaroo , and the visitors to the fictional waratah national park in duffys forest , near sydney.there were two 30-minute episodes . a full-length movie titled `` skippy and the intruders '' was released to theatres in 1969 .
dana james boente ( bent-ë ) ( born february 7 , 1954 ) is an american attorney . he was united states attorney for the eastern district of virginia . he also was acting assistant attorney general for the national security division of the united states department of justice.on october 27 , 2017 , boente announced he would resign from the department of justice after a successor is in place.on january 23 , 2018 , boente was named general counsel to the fbi by the director christopher a. wray , filling the vacancy after james baker 's reassignment to another part of the bureau .
rock en español ( english : `` rock in your language '' ) is a type of rock music with spanish vocals . unlike english-speaking bands , very few acts reach worldwide success . they are often not even between different spanish-speaking countries because of not being taught in english-speaking countries . despite `` rock en español '' 's origins in the late 1950s , many rock acts were successful at best nationwide fame until the internet made them popular . however , some `` rock en español '' artists did become internationally popular with the help of a promotional campaign from the mid 1980s to the mid 1990s called `` '' ( `` rock in your language '' ) . some specific rock-based styles influenced by folkloric rhythms have also developed in these regions . some of the more prominent styles are `` latin rock '' , a fusion of rock music with latin american and caribbean folkloric sounds developed in latin american and caribbean folkloric sounds . `` latin alternative '' , an alternative rock scene which blended a latin sound with other genres like caribbean ska , reggae , and soca , became popular in spain .
dynamic programming is a way of solving problems . it is about simplifying a complicated problem by breaking it down into simpler sub-problems in a recursive manner . while some decision problems can not be taken apart this way , decisions that span several points in time do often break apart recursively.in computer science , a problem can be solved optimally by breaking it into sub-problems and then finding the optimal solutions to the sub-problems , then it is said to have best substructure.if sub-problems can be nested recursively inside larger problems , so that dynamic programming methods are applicable , then there is a relation between the value of the larger problem and the values of the sub-problems . in the optimization literature this relationship is called the bellman equation .
atheism is the belief that there are no gods.atheatheism is different from theism , which is the belief that there are no gods . the word `` atheism '' comes from an ancient greek word , `` atheos '' , which means `` without god '' . the word has been used many times since the 16th century bc , when people started calling themselves `` atheism '' . people started calling themselves `` atheism '' in the 18th century .
shaw is a city in bolivar and sunflower counties , mississippi , united states , located in the mississippi delta region . the name came from an old indian tribe northeast of this region . the population was 1,952 at the 2010 census .
henry leslie `` harry '' firth ( 18 april 1918 – 27 april 2014 ) was an australian racing driver and team manager . firth was a leading race and rally driver during the 1950s and 1960s and continued as an influential team manager with first the ford works team and then the famed holden dealer team ( hdt ) well into the 1970s . firth’s nickname was `` the fox '' , implying his use of cunning ploys as a team manager.firth won the bathurst 500 four times ( twice in the final two races held at the island and twice at bathurst ) . he also won the southern cross rally and the australian rally championship . he was added into the v8 supercars hall of fame in 2007.firth died peacefully in his sleep surrounded by his family , aged 96 .

shelby is a city in montana in the united states . it is the county seat of toole county . as of the 2010 united states census , there were 3,376 people.the yellowstone river flows along the town .
albert einstein ( march 14 , 1879 – april 18 , 1955 ) was a german-american theoretical physicist . he was born in berlin . he won the nobel prize in physics in 1921 for his discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect , which is one of the two pillars of modern physics along with quantum mechanics.his work is also known for its influence on the philosophy of science . he is best known to the general public for his mass–energy equivalence formula , which has been dubbed `` the world 's most famous equation '' . he received the prize because of his discovery , and especially for his discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect , a key step in the development of quantum theory.einstein published more than 300 scientific papers and more than 150 non-scientific works . his intellectual achievements and originality have made the word `` einstein '' synonymous with `` genius '' .
emerald is a town of st. croix county in the state of wisconsin in the united states . 691 people were living in emerald as of 2000 . emerald has an area of 35.5 square miles , says the united states census bureau .
baghlan ( `` baġlān '' ) is one of the thirty-four provinces of afghanistan . it is in the north of the country . as of 2013 , there were about 910,700 people . the capital is puli khumri .
bottidda ( ``bottìdde ,bottìdde '' ) is a town and `` comune '' ( municipality ) in the province of sassari in sardinia , italy . as of 2016 , 672 people lived there . its area is 19.69 km² . it is 472 meters above sea level .
james john benzelock ( born june 21 , 1947 ) is a former professional ice hockey right winger . he was drafted in the first round , fifth overall , by the minnesota north stars in the 1968 nhl amateur draft . he never played in the national hockey league ; however , he appeared in 166 world hockey association games with the alberta oilers , chicago cougars , and quebec nordiques . benzelock played the majority of his career with teams in the minor professional leagues ( chl , ihl , nahl ) .

gustav frištenský ( 18 may 1879 – 6 april 1957 ) was a czech strongman , greco-roman wrestler and professional wrestler who competed in the first half of the 20th century . during his career , he won almost 10,000 fights , the first one when he was just 19 years old and the last one when he was 72 years old . he is considered the strongest czech wrestler and a legendary symbol of strength for many czechs .
eleanor rosalynn smith carter ( born august 18 , 1927 ) is an american civil servant and former first lady of the united states . she was married to president jimmy carter from 1977 until his death in 1981 . they had four children .
 , or as he is commonly known , is one of japan 's most popular comedians and tv hosts . he is one half of the comedy duo downtown alongside masatoshi hamada . like hamada , matsumoto was born and raised in amagasaki , hyōgo prefecture.matsumoto has also directed several movies from 2007 with `` big man japan '' , in several of which he also starred as the main character . he currently hosts `` documental '' on amazon prime .

pound sterling ( symbol £ ; iso code : gbp ) , known in some contexts simply as the pound or sterling , is the official currency of the united kingdom , guernsey , isle of man , gibraltar , south georgia and the south sandwich islands , the british antarctic territory , and tristan da cunha.it is subdivided into 100 `` pence '' ( singular : `` penny '' , abbreviated : `` p '' ) . the pound sterling is the oldest currency in continuous use . a number of nations that do not use sterling also have currencies called the `` pound '' .sterling is the fourth most-traded currency in the foreign exchange market , after the united states dollar , the euro , and the japanese yen . together with those three currencies and the chinese yuan , it forms the basket of currencies which calculate the value of imf special drawing rights . , sterling is also the fourth most-held reserve currency in global reserves.the bank of england is the central bank for the pound sterling , issuing its own banknotes , and regulating issuance of banknotes by private banks in scotland and northern ireland .
herstappe is a municipality in the belgian province of limburg.in 2007 , 8915 people lived there.it is at 51° 05 north , 05° 58 east .
gomphotherium ( meaning `` welded beast '' ) is an extinct genus of proboscids from the neogene and early pleistocene of eurasia .
the toy fox terrier is a small terrier breed of dog . it descended from the larger fox terrier but is considered a separate breed.the toy fox terrier 's coat came from the toy fox terrier 's head . it was originally bred to be a hunting dog , but was later bred to be an independent breed . it is currently one of the most popular dog breeds in england .
sagitta is a constellation in the northern sky . it means `` arrow '' in latin . the astronomer ptolemy listed it in the 2nd century when he made a list of constellations . it is now one of the 88 modern constellations that were made by the international astronomical union . it is north of the equator , and can be seen from every place on earth except within the antarctic circle.the red giant gamma sagittae is the constellation 's brightest star , with an apparent magnitude of 3.47 . delta , epsilon , zeta and theta sagittae are multiple stars whose components can be seen in small telescopes . v sagittae is a binary star system that is probably going to go nova and briefly become the most luminous star in the milky way .
sainte-marie-kerque is a commune . it is found in the region nord-pas-de-calais in the pas-de-calais department in the north of france .
jakob gijsbert `` jaap '' de hoop scheffer ( ; born 3 april 1948 ) is a dutch politician . he is a member of the christian democratic appeal ( cda ) party and jurist . he was secretary general of nato from 1 january 2004 until 1 august 2009 .
charles wood ( born charles w. wood , jr. ; january 1 , 1930 – january 3 , 2019 ) was an american actor . he was born in new york city . wood was known for his roles in the television series `` wkrp in cincinnati '' , `` the wkrp in cincinnati '' , `` the wkrp in cincinnati '' , `` the wkrp in cincinnati '' , and in `` the wkrp in cincinnati '' .wood died on january 3 , 2019 in his home in new york city from cancer , aged 88 .
tiu , also known as teyew , was a predynastic ancient egyptian king who ruled in the nile delta . he is mentioned in the palermo stone inscriptions among a small number of kings of lower egypt . there is no other evidence of such ruler . he may be a mythical king only remembered in unwritten stories , or may even be completely fictitious .
chess records is an american record company . it was founded in chicago in 1950 . they focused on blues and rhythm and blues . it expanded into soul music , gospel music , early rock and roll , and occasional jazz and comedy recordings , released on the chess label , and on its subsidiary labels checker , argo/cadet and cadet concept . the entire chess catalogue is currently owned by universal music group and managed by geffen records.it was founded and run by two jewish immigrant brothers from what was then poland , leonard and phil chess . the company produced and released many singles and albums regarded as central to the rock music canon . the musician and critic cub koda described chess as `` america 's greatest blues label . `` chess was based at several different locations on the south side of chicago , initially at two different locations on south cottage grove ave . the most famous location was 2120 s. michigan avenue from may 1957 to 1965 . the rolling stones recorded there during the group 's first u.s. tour in 1964 . the rolling stones recorded at chess studios on two more occasions . the 2120 s. michigan building was officially named ter-mar studios but was commonly referred to as chess studios . the building is now the home of willie dixon 's blues heaven foundation . in the mid-1960s , chess relocated to a much larger building , the former home of revere camera company at 320 e. 21st street , the label 's final chicago home . shortly before the death of leonard chess in 1969 , the brothers sold the company .
saint-aignan-sur-roë is a commune of 360 people ( 1999 ) . it is found in the region pays de la loire in the mayenne department in the northwest of france .

the fiat 500 ( , ) was a car produced by fiat from 1957 to 1975 . it was the successor to the 500 topolino . the 500 was built on a platform made by fiat .
chondrostei is a group of primarily cartilaginous fish showing some degree of ossification . the cartilaginous condition is thought to be derived , and the ancestors of this group were bony fish with fully ossified skeletons . members of this group share with the elasmobranchii certain features such as the possession of spiracles , a heterocercal tail , and the absence of scales . nevertheless , the fossil record suggests they have more in common with the teleosts . chondrostei is probably a paraphyletic grouping ; the 52 living species are divided among two orders , the acipenseriformes ( sturgeons and paddlefishes ) , and the polypteriformes ( reedfishes and bichirs ) .
sushil koirala ( nepali : सुशील कोइराला ; 12 august 1939 – 9 february 2016 ) was a nepalese politician . he was the prime minister of nepal from 11 february 2014 to 10 october 2015 . he was also president of the nepali congress party from 2010 to 2016.koirala was elected as prime minister of nepal by the parliament on 9 february 2014 . koirala joined the nepali congress in 1952 and served in many capacities prior to becoming its president in 2010 .

a tribe called quest was an american hip hop group . it was formed in st. albans , queens , new york in 1985 . the members were q-tip , phife dawg , dj and co-producer ali shaheed muhammad , and rapper jarobi white . the group is regarded as a pioneer of alternative hip hop music.the group 's first album , `` people 's instinctive travels and the paths of rhythm '' , was released in 1990 . this album had five mics . `` the source '' gave the group 's debut album , `` people 's instinctive travels and the paths of rhythm '' , a perfect rating of five 'mics '' .
typesetting is the composition of text by means of arranging physical types or digital equivalents . stored letters and other symbols are retrieved and ordered according to a language 's orthography for visual display . typesetting requires one or more fonts ( which are widely but wrongly confused with and substituted for typefaces ) . one significant effect of typesetting was that authorship of works could be spotted more easily , making it difficult for copiers who have not gained permission .
the cornell university press is a part of cornell university . it is housed in sage house , the former residence of henry william sage . it was first established in 1869 , making it the first university publishing enterprise in the united states , but was inactive from 1884 to 1930 .
bryan lloyd danielson ( born may 22 , 1981 ) is an american professional wrestler . he is currently signed to world wrestling entertainment ( wwe ) and competes under the ring name daniel bryan . he has also wrestled for ring of honor ( roh ) from 2002 to 2009 . during his time in roh , he was a one-time roh world champion and one-time pure wrestling champion .
six flags magic mountain is a theme park in the valencia neighborhood of santa clarita , california . it is northwest of downtown los angeles . it opened on may 29 , 1971 , as a development of the newhall land and farming company and sea world inc . in 1979 , six flags purchased the park and added the name `` six flags '' to the park 's name.six flags magic mountain has 19 roller coasters . it holds the world record for most roller coasters in an amusement park . there were 3.3 million visitors in 2017 .
the gospel of luke is a book of the new testament . it is the third book of the christian bible , after the acts of the apostles and the gospel of matthew . it is the longest book of the new testament , and it tells the origins , birth , ministry , death , resurrection , and ascension of jesus .
juan miguel miranda ( born april 25 , 1983 ) is a cuban first baseman . he has played in major league baseball for the new york yankees and the arizona diamondbacks . he was born in consolación del sur , pinar del río .
the mid-continent oil field is a broad area containing hundreds of oil fields in arkansas , kansas , louisiana , new mexico , oklahoma and texas . the area , which consists of various geological strata and diverse trap types , was discovered and exploited during the first half of the 20th century . most of the crude oil found in the onshore mid-continent oil field is considered to be of the mixed base or intermediate type ( a mix of paraffin base and asphalt base crude oil types ) .

a unit of measurement is a way to measure an amount of something . if the amount of something is equal to a certain amount of matter , it is called a unit of measurement . there are many different systems of measurement , and people use them all the time . the international bureau of weights and measures ( bipm ) is in charge of working with the international system of measurement ( si ) .

marie eugène françois thomas dubois ( 28 january 1858 – 16 december 1940 ) was a dutch paleoanthropologist and geologist . he earned worldwide fame for his discovery of `` pithecanthropus erectus '' ( later redesignated `` homo erectus '' ) , or `` java man '' . although hominid fossils had been found and studied before , dubois was the first anthropologist to embark upon a purposeful search for them .
teodoro obiang nguema mbasogo ( ; born 5 june 1942 ) is an equatoguinean politician . he has been the 2nd president of equatorial guinea since 1979 . he ousted his uncle , francisco macías nguema in an august 1979 military coup and has overseen equatorial guinea 's emergence as an important oil producer , beginning in the 1990s . obiang was chairperson of the african union from 31 january 2011 to 29 january 2012 .

`` pretty vacant '' is a song by english punk rock band the sex pistols . it was released on 1 july 1977 as the band 's third single . it was later featured on their only album , `` never mind the bollocks , here 's the sex pistols '' , released during that same year.the song reached no . 6 on the uk singles chart and marked the band 's first appearance on the british chart music tv programme `` top of the pops '' .
sør-varanger is a municipality in norway . it is in troms og finnmark county . about 11,500 people lived there in 2013 . kirkenes is the centre of the municipality . other settlements in the municipality include bjørnevatn , bugøynes , elvenes , grense jakobselv , hesseng , jakobsnes , neiden , and sandnes.the municipality is the 6th largest in area out of the 422 municipalities in norway . sør-varanger is also the only municipality in norway that share a land border with russia . the only legal border crossing was at storskog .
kelley is a city of story county in the state of iowa in the united states .
charles frederick `` karch '' kiraly ( ) ( born november 3 , 1960 ) is an american volleyball player , coach and broadcast announcer.in the 1980s he was a central part of the u.s. national team that won gold medals at the 1984 and 1988 olympic games . he went on to win the gold medal again at the 1996 olympic games , the first olympic competition to feature beach volleyball . he is the only player ( man or woman ) to have won olympic gold medals in both the indoor and beach volleyball categories . he played college volleyball for the ucla bruins , where his teams won three national championships under head coach al scates.kiraly is currently the head coach of the united states women 's national volleyball team .
carl tacy ( june 18 , 1932 – april 2 , 2020 ) was an american college basketball coach . he worked at wake forest university in north carolina . he was the head coach from 1972 to 1985 . from 1971 to 1972 , he was the head basketball coach at marshall university . tacy was born in richmond , north carolina.tacy died on april 2 , 2020 in richmond , north carolina at the age of 87 .
fulton is a city in bourbon county , kansas , united states . in 2010 , 163 people lived there .
the indian rhinoceros ( `` rhinoceros unicornis '' ) , also called the greater one-horned rhinoceros and great indian rhinoceros , is a rhinoceros native to the indian subcontinent . it is listed as vulnerable on the iucn red list , as populations are fragmented and restricted to less than . the extent and quality of the rhino 's most important habitat , the alluvial terai-duar savanna and grasslands and riverine forest , is considered to be in decline due to human and livestock encroachment . as of 2008 , a total of 2,575 mature individuals were estimated to live in the wild.the indian rhinoceros once lived throughout the entire stretch of the indo-gangetic plain , but excessive hunting and agricultural development reduced its range drastically to 11 sites in northern india and southern nepal . in the early 1990s , between 1,870 and 1,895 rhinos were said to have been alive .
bollinger county is a county in missouri , united states . the county seat is marble hill . in 2010 , 12,363 people lived there . the county was organized in 1851 .
snap ! is a eurodance group . it was formed in 1989 by record producers michael münzing and luca anzilotti . the group has changed through a number of line-up changes over the years , including american singers , songwriters and rappers thea austin , turbo b , and penny ford . their best known hits are `` the power '' and `` rhythm is a dancer '' .
the lamborghini murciélago is a sports car that was built by lamborghini from 2001 to 2009 . the murciélago is the successor to the lamborghini diablo and lamborghini v12 . the murciélago was first available in north america in 2002 , and was facelifted in 2003 . the murciélago is designed by luc donckerwolke , lamborghini 's head of design from 1998 to 2005.the murciélago 's successor , the aventador , was unveiled at the 2011 geneva motor show .

 pleading is a statement of a party 's claims to another party 's claims in a civil action . the parties ' pleadings in a case define the issues to be adjudicated in the action.the civil procedure rules ( cpr ) govern pleading in england and wales . federal rules of civil procedure govern pleading in united states federal courts . each state in the united states has its own statutes and rules that govern pleading in the courts of that state .
tribune east tower is an approved mixed use supertall tower to be built on the eastern edge of the tribune tower property , in the streeterville area of chicago . the building plans received final approval on may 8 , 2020 . when completed , the skyscraper would become the second-tallest in chicago after willis tower .
various positions is the seventh studio album by leonard cohen . it was released in december 1984 ( and february 1985 ) . it was produced by leonard cohen .
the glass frogs are frogs of the amphibian family centrolenidae ( order anura ) . while the general background color of most glass frogs is lime green , the abdominal skin of some members of this family is transparent and translucent . the internal viscera , including the heart , liver , and gastrointestinal tract , are visible through the skin , hence the common name is given as glass frog . glass frogs are arboreal , meaning they mainly live in trees , and only come out for mating season .
benthos is the community of organisms that live on , in , or near the seabed , river , lake or stream bottom . this community lives in or near marine or freshwater sedimentary environments , from tidal pools along the foreshore , out to the continental shelf , and then down to the abyssal depths.many organisms adapted to deep-water pressure can not survive in the upperparts of the water column . the pressure difference can be very significant ( approximately one atmosphere for each 10 metres of water depth ) . light is absorbed before it can reach deep ocean-water . the energy source for deep benthic ecosystems is often organic matter from higher up in the water column that drifts down to the depths . this dead and decaying matter sustains the benthic food chain ; most organisms in the benthic zone are detritivores.the term `` benthos '' , coined by haeckel in 1891 , comes from the greek noun `` depth of the sea '' . `` benthos '' is used in freshwater biology to refer to organisms at the bottom of freshwater bodies of water , such as lakes , rivers , and streams .
monday is the day of the week between sunday and tuesday . in some countries , like the united states , it is the first day of the week . in other countries , like the united kingdom , it is the second day of the week .
portales is a city in the u.s. state of new mexico . it is the county seat of roosevelt county .
angeline dickinson ( born september 30 , 1931 ) is an american movie , television , stage , and voice actress . she is known for her roles in `` rio bravo '' , `` gun the man down '' , `` china gate '' , `` ocean 's 11 '' , `` the sins of rachel cade '' , `` jessica '' , `` captain newman , m.d .  fantasy vii is a fantasy role-playing video game for the playstation video game console . it was developed by square enix and published by nintendo . it was released in north america on november 8 , 1994 , in europe on november 9 , 1994 , and in japan on december 13 , 1994 . it is the first game in the `` final fantasy '' series to use full motion video and 3d computer graphics , superimposing 3d character models over 2d pre-rendered backgrounds . `` final fantasy vii '' introduced more science fiction elements and a more realistic presentation . the gameplay systems remained largely similar to previous games . the game also added new features , such as materia , limit breaks , and new minigames . nintendo had a combined development and marketing budget of around us $ 100 . `` final fantasy vii '' received widespread commercial and critical success , and is widely regarded as a landmark game , and as one of the most influential and greatest video games of all time . it won numerous game of the year awards , and was acknowledged for boosting sales of the playstation and popularizing console role-playing games worldwide . critics praised its graphics , gameplay , music , and story , but criticized its original english . its success has led to enhanced ports on various platforms , a multimedia sub-series called the `` compilation of final fantasy vii '' , and the ongoing multipart high-definition `` final fantasy vii remake '' where the first installment is to be released in 2020 .
melide is a municipality of the district lugano in the canton of ticino in switzerland . the village lies very close to the mountain monte san salvatore and is directly on the lake of lugano . the melide causeway to the east was built to make it possible to cross to bissone and to allow a north-south highway to be built.melide is known worldwide for the famous swissminiatur , a museum that shows famous buildings in switzerland presented in miniature form .

the durrells ( known in north america as the durrells in corfu ) is a 26-episode british comedy-drama series inspired by gerald durrell 's three autobiographical books about his family 's four years ( 1935–1939 ) on the greek island of corfu , which began on 3 april 2016 and ended on 12 may 2019 . the series is written by simon nye , directed by steve barron and roger goldby , and produced by christopher hall . the executive producers are lee morris and sally woodward gentle . lee durrell , gerald durrell 's widow and director of the durrell wildlife conservation trust , acted as consultant . the series was partly filmed at ealing studios and twickenham studios in london .

florence h. pendleton ( born c. 1926 ) is an american politician . she was a shadow senator from the district of columbia . pendleton was the first shadow senator of the district of columbia.her main goal was to promote the efforts of the district to gain full voting rights , alongside her counterpart in seat 2 . she was inaugurated as the first ever shadow senator on january 3 , 1991 .
polio vaccines are vaccines used to prevent poliomyelitis ( polio ) . two types are used : an inactivated poliovirus given by injection ( ipv ) and a weakened poliovirus given by mouth ( opv ) . the world health organization ( who ) recommends all children be fully vaccinated against polio . the two vaccines have eliminated polio from most of the world , and reduced the number of cases reported each year from an estimated 350,000 in 1988 to 33 in 2018 .
the arrondissement of mâcon is an arrondissement of france . it is part of the saône-et-loire `` département '' , in the bourgogne-franche-comté region . its capital is the city of mâcon .
st. louis park is a city in hennepin county , minnesota , united states . the population was 45,250 at the 2010 census .
realpolitik is a philosophical approach to politics . it is often simply referred to as `` pragmatism '' in politics , e.g. , `` pursuing pragmatic policies '' . realpolitik is sometimes used pejoratively to imply politics that are perceived as coercive , amoral , or machiavellian .
paul anthony samuelson ( may 15 , 1915 – december 13 , 2009 ) was an american economist . he was the first american to win the nobel prize in economics . `` the new york times '' called him the `` foremost academic economist of the 20th century '' . samuelson was probably the most influential economist of the later 20th century.he was an advisor to presidents john f. kennedy and lyndon b. johnson , and was a consultant to the united states treasury , the bureau of the budget and the president 's council of economic advisers . samuelson wrote a weekly column for `` newsweek '' magazine , where he `` has done more than any other contemporary economist to raise the level of scientific analysis in economic theory . ''
fahrenheit 451 is a novel by ray bradbury . it was published in 1953 . it is about a future american society where books are outlawed and `` firemen '' burn any that are found . the book 's tagline explains the title : `` fahrenheit 451 – the temperature at which book paper catches fire , and burns ... '' the lead character , guy montag , is a fireman who becomes disillusioned with his role of censoring literature and destroying knowledge . he eventually gave up his job and committed himself to the preservation of literary and cultural writings.in 1954 , `` fahrenheit 451 '' won the american academy of arts and letters award in literature and the commonwealth club of california gold medal . it later won the prometheus `` hall of fame '' award in 1984 and a `` retro hugo award , one of a limited number of best novel retro hugos ever given , in 2004 .
farmington is a city of the state of arkansas in the united states of america .
matthew roy blunt ( born november 20 , 1970 ) is an american naval officer and politician . he served as the 54th governor of missouri from 2005 to 2009 . before he election as governor , blunt served ten years in the united states navy , was elected to the missouri general assembly in 1998 , and as missouri 's secretary of state in 2000.a republican , matt blunt was elected governor on november 2 , 2004 , carrying 101 of missouri 's 114 counties . at age 33 , he became the second-youngest person ever elected to that office after kit bond . blunt did not seek a second term as governor , announcing his decision on january 22 , 2008 in an address to missourians which surprised many supporters and staff .

richard benaud ( 6 october 1930 – 10 april 2015 ) was an australian cricketer . after his retirement from international cricket in 1964 , he became a highly regarded commentator on the game.he was an all-rounder , blending leg spin bowling with lower-order batting aggression . along with fellow bowling all-rounder alan davidson , benaud helped restore australia to the top of world cricket in the late 1950s and early 1960s . in 1958 he became australia 's test captain until his retirement in 1964 . he became the first player to reach 200 wickets and 2,000 runs in test cricket , arriving at that milestone in 1963 .

el cerro mutún is an iron ore deposit in bolivia . it is in the germán busch province in the santa cruz department . it is one of the world 's largest reserves of iron ore , covering an area of about 75 square kilometers .
`` the loud house '' is an american animated television series created by chris savino that premiered on nickelodeon on may 2 , 2016 . the series focuses on lincoln loud , the only male child in a house full of girls , who is often breaking the fourth wall to explain to viewers the chaotic conditions and sibling relationships of the household .
in norse mythology , sjöfn ( or sjǫfn ) is a goddess of love . she is described in the `` prose edda '' , written in the 13th century by snorri sturluson .
yamato nadeshiko ( or ) is a japanese term meaning the `` personification of an idealized japanese woman '' . it is a floral metaphor , combining the words `` yamato '' , an ancient name for japan , and `` nadeshiko '' , a delicate frilled pink carnation called `` dianthus superbus '' , whose kanji translate into english as `` caressable child '' .the term `` yamato nadeshiko '' is often used to describe a demure young woman . it is also used to describe women with good traits which are increasingly rare . however , `` nadeshiko japan '' is also widely used as the name for the japanese national women 's football team.the term `` yamato nadeshiko '' is often used to describe a demure young woman .
john howard `` jack '' gibbons ( january 15 , 1929 – july 17 , 2015 ) was an american scientist , nuclear physicist , and internationally recognized expert in technologies for energy efficiency and energy resource conservation . he served as the assistant to the president for science and technology and director of the white house office of science and technology policy under president bill clinton from 1993 to 1998.gibbons died on july 17 , 2015 from natural causes , aged 86 .
in medicine , dialysis is the process of removing excess water , solutes , and toxins from the blood in people whose kidneys can no longer perform these functions naturally . the first successful dialysis was performed in 1943.dialysis may need to be initiated when there is a sudden loss of kidney function , known as acute renal failure ( previously called acute renal failure ) , or when a gradual decline in kidney function reaches stage 5 ( chronic renal failure ) . by stage 5 , renal failure is reached when the glomerular filtration rate is 10-15 % of normal , creatinine clearance is less than 10ml per minute and uremia is present.dialysis is used as a temporary measure in either acute kidney injury or in those awaiting kidney transplant and as a permanent measure in those for whom a transplant is not indicated or not possible.in australia , canada , the united kingdom and the united states , dialysis is paid for by the government for those who are eligible .
`` buffy the vampire slayer '' is an american television series created by joss whedon , which premiered on march 10 , 1997 , and ended on may 20 , 2003 , after seven seasons with 144 episodes in total , plus an unaired pilot episode .
the peace corps is an agency of the united states government . it was started in 1961 . it provides free health care , education , youth development , business , information technology , agriculture , and the environment to trained americans . more than 235,000 americans have joined the peace corps . its headquarters are in washington d.c.. most volunteers are volunteers .
edward adelbert doisy ( november 13 , 1893 – october 23 , 1986 ) was an american biochemist . he received the nobel prize in physiology or medicine in 1943 with henrik dam for their discovery of vitamin k ( k from `` koagulations-vitamin '' in german ) and its chemical structure .

tentaculata is a class of comb jellies . the common feature of this class is a pair of long , feathery contractile tentacles , which can be retracted into specialised ciliated sheaths . in some species , the primary tentacles are reduced and they have smaller , secondary tentacles . the tentacles have colloblasts , which are sticky-tipped cells to trap small prey.body size and shape varies widely . the group includes the small , oval sea gooseberries found on both atlantic and pacific coasts . the more flattened species of the genus `` mnemiopsis '' , about long , are common on the upper atlantic coast ; it has a large mouth and mainly feeds on larval molluscs and copepods .
 of the old provinces of japan had one or more `` ichinomiya '' , which gave rise to place names , such as the city of ichinomiya , aichi . shrines of the lower rank are called `` ninomiya '' ( 二宮 , second ) , `` sannomiya '' ( 三宮 , third ) , `` shinomiya '' ( 四宮 , fourth ) , and so forth .
arnold kopelson ( february 14 , 1935 – october 8 , 2018 ) was an american movie producer . he was known for his movies `` platoon '' , `` seven '' , `` outbreak '' , `` the fugitive '' and `` the devil 's advocate '' .kopelson died on october 8 , 2018 in los angeles , california from complications of parkinson 's disease at the age of 83 .
tropical storm jerry was the tenth tropical storm of the 1995 atlantic hurricane season . jerry formed in august from a tropical wave that moved off the african coast in the month of august . it later formed in the bahamas and florida later in the month of august . then , it struck florida in the second part of the month . the storm stayed away from land for five days . it then hit georgia and south carolina , causing $ 40 million in damage . at the time , jerry was the earliest tenth storm to form in a season on record . however , in 2005 , jerry overtook it . tropical storm jerry was also the first tropical cyclone to make landfall in south florida since hurricane andrew in 1992 .

the name army ant ( or legionary ant or marabunta ) is applied to over 200 ant species in different lineages . due to their aggressive predatory foraging groups , known as `` raids '' , a huge number of ants forage simultaneously over a certain area.another shared feature is that , unlike most ant species , army ants do not make permanent nests ; an army ant colony moves almost incessantly over the time it exists . all species are members of the true ant family , formicidae , but several groups have independently evolved the same basic behavioural and ecological syndrome . this syndrome is often referred to as `` legionary behaviour '' , and may be an example of convergent evolution.the largest genus is `` neivamyrmex '' , which contains more than 120 species ; the most predominant species is `` eciton burchellii '' ; its common name `` army ant '' is considered to be the archetype of the species . old world army ants are divided between the aenictini and dorylini tribes . aenictini contains more than 50 species of army ants in the single genus , `` aenictus '' . however , the dorylini contain the genus `` dorylus '' , the most aggressive group of driver ants ; 70 species are known.originally , some of the old world and new world lineages of army ants were thought to have evolved independently . however , genetic analysis of various species suggests that several of these groups evolved from a single common ancestor , which lived about 100 million years ago at the time of the separation of the continents of africa and south america , while other army ant lineages ( leptanillinae , plus members of ponerinae , amblyoponinae , and myrmicinae ) are still considered to represent independent evolutionary events . army ant taxonomy remains in flux , and genetic analysis will continue to provide more information about the relatedness of the various taxa .
field marshal edwin noel westby bramall , baron bramall , ( 18 december 1923 – 12 november 2019 ) was a british army officer . he was chief of the general staff , the professional head of the british army , between 1979 and 1982 , and as chief of the defence staff , professional head of the british armed forces , from 1982 to 1985.bramall died on 12 november 2019 at the age of 96 .

gliese 667 is an exoplanet orbiting within the habitable zone of the red dwarf star gliese 667 c , which is a member of the gliese 667 triple star system , about 23.62 light-years ( 6.8 parsecs , or about 217,000,000,000 km ) away in the constellation of scorpius .

the following is a list of subcamps of the sachsenhausen concentration camp created by nazi germany . the main camp , with around 50 barracks for slave-labour prisoners , was from berlin , and operated between 1938 and april 22 , 1945 . during world war ii , it is estimated that the number of victims of sachsenhausen was 30,00035,000 . dozens of subcamps of sachsenhausen existed directly in the capital city , serving individual business operators and factories .
caryophyllaceae , commonly called the pink family or carnation family , is a family of flowering plants . it is in the order caryophyllales in the apg iii system , alongside 33 other families , including amaranthaceae , cactaceae , and polygonaceae . it is a large family , with 81 genera and about 2,625 species .

in the geologic timescale , the bajocian is an age and stage in the middle jurassic . it lasted from about 170 million years ago ( mya ) to about 168 mya ( mya ) . the bajocian is after the aalenian and before the bathonian age .
the arabian or arab horse is a breed of horse that originated on the arabian peninsula . they are one of the most easily recognizable horse breeds in the world . it is also one of the oldest breeds , with archaeological evidence of horses in the middle east that resemble modern arabians dating back 4,500 years.the arabian horse has spread around the world by both war and trade , used to improve other breeds by adding speed , refinement , endurance , and strong bone . today , arabian bloodlines are found in almost every modern breed of riding horse.the arabian developed in a desert climate and was prized by the bedouin people . it was often brought inside the family tent for shelter and protection from theft . selective breeding for traits , including an ability to form a cooperative relationship with humans , created a horse breed that is good-natured , quick to learn , and willing to please . the arabian also developed the high spirit and alertness needed in a horse used for raiding and war . this combination of willingness and sensitivity requires modern arabian horse owners to handle their horses with competence and respect.the arabian is a versatile breed . arabians dominate the discipline of endurance riding , and compete today in many other fields of equestrian sport . they are one of the top ten most popular horse breeds in the world . they are now found worldwide , including the united states and canada , united kingdom , australia , continental europe , south america ( especially brazil ) , and their land of origin , the middle east.the arabian is a versatile breed . arabians dominate the discipline of endurance riding , and compete today in many other fields of equestrian sport . they are one of the top ten most popular horse breeds in the world . they are now found worldwide , including the united kingdom , australia , continental europe , south america ( especially brazil ) , and their land of origin , the middle east .

a leaf blower , commonly known as a blower , is a gardening tool that propels air out of a nozzle to move debris such as leaves and grass cuttings . leaf blowers are powered by electric or gasoline motors . gasoline models have traditionally been two-stroke engines , but four-stroke engines were recently introduced to partially address air pollution concerns .

the bombay presidency was an administrative subdivision ( presidency ) of british india headquartered in the city of bombay , the bombay presidency was created when the city of bombay was leased in fee tail to the east india company by a royal charter from the king of england , charles ii , who in turn acquired it on may 11 , 1661 . the presidency was brought under british parliament control along with other parts of british india through pitt 's india act . major territorial acquisitions were made during the anglo-maratha wars when the whole of the peshwa 's dominions and much of the gaekwad 's sphere of influence were annexed to the bombay presidency in different stages till 1818 . aden was annexed in 1839 , while sindh province was annexed by the company in 1843 after defeating the talpur dynasty in the battle of hyderabad and it was made a part of the bombay presidency .
when a man loves a woman is a 1992 romantic comedy-drama movie . it is about when a man loves a woman . this movie was released in the united states in 1992 . it received mixed reviews . roger ebert of the chicago sun-times gave the movie three out of four stars .
the 1941–42 nhl season was the 25th season of the national hockey league . seven teams played 48 games each . the toronto maple leafs would win the stanley cup defeating the detroit red wings winning four straight after losing the first three in a best-of-seven series , a feat only repeated three times in nhl history ( 1975 , 2010 , 2014 ) and once in major league baseball ( 2004 ) as of 2017 .
john thomas o'brien ( born december 11 , 1930 ) is an american baseball player . he played as a backup second baseman and pitcher in major league baseball . he played for the pittsburgh pirates ( 1953 , 1955–58 ) , st. louis cardinals ( 1958 ) and milwaukee braves ( 1959 ) . o'brien batted and threw right-handed . his twin brother , eddie , was also a major league infielder.o'brien also played for the pittsburgh pirates ( 1953 , 1955–58 ) , st. louis cardinals ( 1958 ) , and milwaukee braves ( 1959 ) . he was born in amboy , maryland .

gary stanley becker ( ; december 2 , 1930 – may 3 , 2014 ) was an american economist . he received the 1992 nobel prize in economic sciences . he was a professor of economics and sociology at the university of chicago . he was a leader of the third generation of the chicago school of economics.becker was awarded the nobel memorial prize in economic sciences in 1992 and received the united states presidential medal of freedom in 2007.becker died in chicago , illinois from natural causes , aged 83 .

the incorporated village of lattingtown is a village located within the town of oyster bay in nassau county , new york in the united states . the population was 1,739 at the 2010 census . the movie `` the money pit '' was filmed partially in lattingtown .
rmjm ( robert matthew johnson marshall ) is one of the largest architecture & design networks in the world . services include architecture , development management , engineering , interior design , landscape design , lead consultancy , master planning , product design , specialist advisory services , urban design . rmjm’s first offices were based in london and edinburgh . rmjm has been a strong supporter of modern and contemporary architecture inspired by cultures around the globe since its creation .
jeep is an american automobile . it is owned by fiat chrysler automobiles . the company has been around since 1987 , when chrysler bought the jeep brand from american motors corporation ( amc ) .jeep 's product range is mainly sport utility vehicles . this includes both crossovers and fully off-road worthy suvs . jeep 's range included other pick-ups , as well as small vans , and a few roadsters . some of jeep 's vehicles— such as the grand cherokee—reach into the luxury suv segment , a market segment the 1963 wagoneer is considered to have started . in 2016 , jeep sold 1.4 million suvs globally , up from 500,000 in 2008 , two-thirds of which in north america.in the u.s. alone , over 2400 dealerships hold franchise rights to sell jeep-branded vehicles . if jeep was spun off into a separate company , it would be worth between $ 22 and $ 33.5 billion—slightly `` more '' than all of fca ( us ) .the jeep marque has been headquartered in toledo , ohio , ever since willys-overland launched production of the first cj or civilian jeep models there in 1945 . its replacement , the conceptually consistent jeep wrangler series , remains in production since 1986 .
`` this is how we do '' is a song recorded by american singer katy perry for her fourth studio album , `` prism '' . perry co-wrote the song with its producers max martin and klas åhlund and recorded it in stockholm , sweden . the song was released as the album 's fifth and final single on august 11 , 2014 .
shandong luneng taishan ( ) is a professional football club from shandong , china . they currently participate in the chinese super league under licence from the chinese football association ( cfa ) . their home stadium is jinan , shandong and they currently play at the jinan olympic sports center stadium .
mclennan county is a county in the u.s. state of texas . in 2010 , 234,906 people lived there . the county seat and largest city is waco .
herbert eser `` herb '' gray ( may 25 , 1931 – april 21 , 2014 ) was a canadian politician . he served as a member of parliament for windsor west for four decades , from 1962 to 2002 . he served as cabinet minister under three prime ministers , and as deputy prime minister from 1997 to 2002 . he was canada 's first jewish federal cabinet minister .
vahit melih halefoğlu ( 19 november 1919 – 21 january 2017 ) was a turkish politician and diplomat . he was born in ankara , turkey.halefoğlu served as ambassador in beirut ( 1962–1965 ) , kuwait city ( 1964–1965 ) , moscow ( 1965–1966 , 1982–1983 ) , den haag ( 1966–1970 ) and bonn ( 1972–1982 ) .halefoğlu died on 21 january 2017 in ankara , aged 96 .
bodcaw is a town of nevada county in the state of arkansas in the united states .
john ben `` benny '' benson , jr. ( ; october 12 , 1913 – july 2 , 1972 ) was an american architect . he designed the flag of alaska . benny was 13 years old when he won a contest in 1927 to design the flag for the territory of alaska , which became a u.s. state on january 3 , 1959 .
serres-morlaàs is a commune of the pyrénées-atlantiques `` département '' in the southwestern part of france .
simmesport is a town in avoyelles parish , louisiana , united states .
pauline hanson 's one nation ( phon or onp ) is a political party in australia . it was founded in 1997 by member of parliament pauline hanson and her advisors david ettridge and david oldfield after hanson was disendorsed as a federal candidate for the liberal party of australia . hanson sat as an independent for one year before forming pauline hanson 's one nation.no one nation candidate has ever been elected to the house of representatives . however , one candidate from the party was elected to the senate in the 1998 federal election , and four one nation senators were elected in the 2016 federal election.at the 1998 queensland state election the party gained more than 22 % of the vote in queensland 's unicameral legislative assembly , winning 11 of the 89 seats . david oldfield was elected to the new south wales legislative council as a one nation candidate , but he was expelled from the party and later formed the unsuccessful splinter group , one nation nsw . three members were elected to the western australian legislative council.at the 2016 federal election the party polled 4.3 % ( +3.8 ) of the nationwide primary vote in the senate . only queensland voted higher for the party than their nationwide percentage − the party polled 9.2 % ( +8.6 ) of the primary vote in that state . pauline hanson ( qld ) and three other one nation candidates − malcolm roberts ( qld ) , brian burston ( nsw ) , and rod culleton ( wa ) were elected to the senate .
hopkins county is a county in the u.s. state of texas . in 2010 , 35,161 people lived there . the county seat is sulphur springs.hopkins county was once known as the dairy capital of texas .
interstate 69 is an interstate highway in the united states . it goes from indianapolis , indiana northeast to the canada–us border in port huron , michigan , at . the remaining parts are going to be completed and posted or unposted sections of an extension southwest to the mexican border in texas . of this extension is called the nafta superhighway because it would help trade with canada and mexico spurred by the north american free trade agreement . five pieces of the interstate have been built or upgraded and signposted as i-69 . a sixth part of i-69 through kentucky using that state 's existing parkway system and a section of i-24 was established by federal legislation in 2008 , but only a part is signposted as i-69 . this brings the total length to about .
an observation deck or viewing platform is an elevated sightseeing platform . it is usually placed at a tall architectural structure , such as a skyscraper or observation tower . observation decks are sometimes enclosed from weather . some may include coin-operated telescopes for viewing distant features .
khufu ( , full name khnum khufu ) was an ancient egyptian king . he was the second pharaoh of the fourth dynasty , in the first half of the old kingdom period ( 26th century bc ) . khufu succeeded his father sneferu as king . he is generally accepted as having commissioned the great pyramid of giza , one of the seven wonders of the ancient world , but many other aspects of his reign are poorly documented.the only completely preserved portrait of the king is a three-inch high ivory figurine found in a temple ruin of a later period at abydos in 1903 . all other reliefs and statues were found in fragments , and many buildings of khufu are lost . everything known about khufu comes from inscriptions in his necropolis at giza and later documents . for example , khufu is the main character noted in the westcar papyrus from the 13th dynasty.most documents that mention king khufu were written by ancient egyptian and greek historians around 300 bc . khufu 's obituary is presented there in a conflicting way : while the king enjoyed a long-lasting cultural heritage preservation during the period of the old kingdom and the new kingdom , the ancient historians manetho , diodorus and herodotus hand down a very negative picture of khufu 's character . thanks to these documents , an obscure and critical picture of khufu 's personality persists.khufu 's obituary is presented there in a conflicting way : while the king enjoyed a long-lasting cultural heritage preservation during the period of the old kingdom and the new kingdom , the ancient historians manetho , diodorus and herodotus hand down a very negative depiction of khufu 's character . thanks to these documents , an obscure and critical picture of khufu 's personality persists .
